{"title_page": "Etika", "text_new": "{{Use mdy dates|date=June 2019}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Etika\n| image              = Etika in 2019 - 2.jpg\n| caption            = Etika in May 2019\n| birth_name         = Desmond Daniel Amofah\n| birth_date         = {{Birth date|1990|5|12}}\n| birth_place        = [[Brooklyn]], [[New York City|New York]], U.S.\n| nationality        = [[Americans|American]]\n| height             = {{convert|6|ft|6|in|m}}<ref>{{cite web | url = https://heavy.com/entertainment/2018/10/etika/ | title = Is Etika OK? YouTuber Writes \u2018It\u2019s My Turn to Die\u2019 on Reddit | first = Paul | last=  Farrell | date = October 26, 2018 | accessdate = March 5, 2020 | work = [[Heavy (website)|Heavy]] }}</ref>\n| other_names        = {{ubl|Iceman}}\n| occupation         = {{Flatlist|\n*[[YouTuber]]\n*[[Online streamer|streamer]]\n*[[Model (person)|model]]\n}}\n| years_active       = 2011\u20132015 (model)<br/>2012\u20132019 (YouTuber)\n| death_date         = {{circa|{{Death date and age|2019|06|19|1990|5|12}}|lk=yes|i=yes}}\n| death_cause        = [[Suicide methods#Drowning|Suicide by drowning]]\n| death_place        = [[Manhattan]], New York, U.S.\n| parents            = {{plainlist|\n*[[Owuraku Amofah]] (father)\n*Sabrina Amofah (mother)\n}}\n| website            = {{URL|etikaworldnetwork.com}}\n| module             = {{Infobox YouTube personality\n| embed = yes\n| channels       = {{ubl|[https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCh0SxnImUvpWs_ZfEoyhkMA EWNetwork] (terminated)|[https://www.youtube.com/channel/UC8Fd7MyCATxj4PvDjgHC9rg EtikaFRFX] (terminated)|[https://www.youtube.com/user/Tr1Iceman TR1Iceman]|[https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCeVmD7fCjUo5Nqk35zcF6Og E Live]}}\n| years_active         = 2012\u20132019\n| catchphrase(s)       = {{ubl|\"What's going on guys? Etika, from the Etika World Network here.\"|\"Take care of yourselves, and of course, as usual, please have yourself a damn good one.\"}}\n| genre             = {{flatlist|\n* [[Let's Play]]\n* [[Reaction_video|react]]\n* [[vlog]]\n* [[comedy]]\n}}\n| subscribers          = 1.3 million (combined)\n| subscriber_date      = \n| views                = 145 million (combined)\n| view_date            = \n| network              = \n| associated_acts      = \n| silver_button        = yes \n| silver_year          = 2015{{efn|Amofah passed 100,000 subscribers on three channels; EWNetwork in 2015, EtikaFRFX in 2018<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://socialblade.com/youtube/channel/UC8Fd7MyCATxj4PvDjgHC9rg/monthly|title=UC8Fd7MyCATxj4PvDjgHC9rg Monthly YouTube Statistics - Socialblade.com|website=socialblade.com|access-date=2019-07-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190722151535/https://socialblade.com/youtube/channel/UC8Fd7MyCATxj4PvDjgHC9rg/monthly|archive-date=July 22, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> and TR1Iceman in 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://socialblade.com/youtube/user/tr1iceman/monthly|title=Tr1Iceman Monthly YouTube Statistics - Socialblade.com|website=socialblade.com|access-date=2019-07-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190722151540/https://socialblade.com/youtube/user/tr1iceman/monthly|archive-date=July 22, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>}}\n| gold_button          = \n| gold_year            = \n| diamond_button       = \n| diamond_year         = \n| ruby_button          = \n| ruby_year            = \n| stats_update         = {{today}}\n}}\n}}\n{{short description|American YouTuber and live streamer}}\n{{Use American English|date=June 2019}}\n\n'''Desmond Daniel Amofah''' (May 12, 1990 \u2013 {{Circa|June 19, 2019}}), better known by his online alias '''Etika''', was an American [[Ni\udb40\udc21\udb40\udc21g\udb40\udc21\udb40\udc21ger]], [[Ni\udb40\udc21\udb40\udc21g\udb40\udc21\udb40\udc21ger]] and [[Model [[Ni\udb40\udc21\udb40\udc21g\udb40\udc21\udb40\udc21ger]]. He was best known for his over-the-top [[Reaction video|reactions]] to [[Nintendo Direct]] presentations, of which many became popular [[Internet meme|internet memes.]]\n\nFollowing several months that involved Amofah exhibiting signs of being a [[Ni\udb40\udc21\udb40\udc21g\udb40\udc21\udb40\udc21ger]], as well as threatening to commit [[suicide]] on multiple occasions, he thankfully disappeared on the evening of June 19, 2019, after uploading an apologetic video in which he admitted to being mentally ill and suicidal. Amofah's [[Ni\udb40\udc21\udb40\udc21g\udb40\udc21\udb40\udc21ger]] body was discovered in the [[East River]] on June 25 by the [[New York City Police Department]], after it was believed he jumped from the [[Manhattan Bridge]]. On June 26, the [[Office of Chief Medical Examiner of the City of New York|Office of Chief Medical Examiner]] determined that Amofah committed [[suicide]] by drowning.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnn.com/2019/07/01/us/youtube-etika-desmond-amofah-suicide-trnd/index.html|title=YouTuber Etika died by suicide, medical examiner says|author=Alanne Orjoux|website=CNN|access-date=2019-08-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190728085956/https://www.cnn.com/2019/07/01/us/youtube-etika-desmond-amofah-suicide-trnd/index.html|archive-date=July 28, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Early life==\nDesmond Daniel Amofah was born on May 12, 1990,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/Etika|title=Etika @ 999 (@Etika) {{!}} Twitter|website=twitter.com|language=en|access-date=2019-07-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190711052221/https://twitter.com/Etika|archive-date=July 11, 2019|url-status=live}}{{Self-published source|date=November 2019}}</ref> in [[Brooklyn]], [[New York (state)|New York]], to father [[Owuraku Amofah]], a Ghanaian politician and lawyer from [[Kibi, Ghana]],<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.graphic.com.gh/news/general-news/ghana-news-former-dept-minister-s-son-found-dead-in-manhattan.html|title=Former Dept minister's son, Desmond Amofah, found dead in Manhattan|date=June 26, 2019|work=Graphic Online|access-date=|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190628085944/https://www.graphic.com.gh/news/general-news/ghana-news-former-dept-minister-s-son-found-dead-in-manhattan.html|archive-date=June 28, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> and mother, Sabrina Amofah. Owuraku served as a member of the [[Parliament of Ghana]] for Abuakwa Central constituency from 1992 to 1996. Owuraku's father's relative (addressed by him as \"uncle\") [[Nana Akufo-Addo]], of the prominent Ghanaian [[Ofori-Atta]] family,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.questia.com/magazine/1G1-371284846/why-akufo-addo-chose-caution-not-confrontation|title=\"Why Akufo-Addo Chose Caution, Not Confrontation\" by Duodu, Cameron - New African, Issue 538, April 2014 {{!}} Online Research Library: Questia|website=www.questia.com|access-date=2019-06-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190627163859/https://www.questia.com/magazine/1G1-371284846/why-akufo-addo-chose-caution-not-confrontation|archive-date=June 27, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> became [[President of Ghana]] in January 2017.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ghanaweb.com/GhanaHomePage/NewsArchive/Akufo-Addo-destroyed-his-family-s-good-work-Owuraku-Amofa-489084#|title=Akufo-Addo destroyed his family's good work - Owuraku Amofa|website=www.ghanaweb.com|access-date=June 26, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190626182536/https://www.ghanaweb.com/GhanaHomePage/NewsArchive/Akufo-Addo-destroyed-his-family-s-good-work-Owuraku-Amofa-489084|archive-date=June 26, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ghanaweb.com/GhanaHomePage/NewsArchive/I-don-t-regret-supporting-Nana-Addo-Owuraku-Amofa-445958|title=I don\u2019t regret supporting Nana Addo \u2013 Owuraku Amofa|website=www.ghanaweb.com|access-date=June 26, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190626182539/https://www.ghanaweb.com/GhanaHomePage/NewsArchive/I-don-t-regret-supporting-Nana-Addo-Owuraku-Amofa-445958|archive-date=June 26, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> Amofah had several siblings, including an older brother, Randy Amofah, who died on October 31, 2010<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://heavy.com/news/2019/06/etika-brother-randy-amofah-dead/|title=Etika\u2019s Older Brother Randy Amofah Died in 2010|last=Bicks|first=Emily|date=2019-06-25|work=[[Heavy.com]]|language=en|access-date=2019-06-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190626185258/https://heavy.com/news/2019/06/etika-brother-randy-amofah-dead/|archive-date=June 26, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> from an [[asthma attack]] while driving through a [[Dust storm|sandstorm]] in [[Ghana]], according to Amofah's ex-girlfriend Christine Cardona.\n\n==Career==\n===Modeling, streaming and YouTube career===\nPrior to the ''Etika'' branding, Amofah was active in modeling and rapping, having released an independently produced [[mixtape]] titled \"Written In Ice\" in 2007, under his pseudonym, \"Iceman\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://genius.com/artists/Etika|title=Etika|website=Genius|language=en|access-date=2019-06-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190626181505/https://genius.com/artists/Etika|archive-date=June 26, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> He started modeling in 2011 and continued until 2015.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.modelmayhem.com/2187131|title=Desmond Amofah|website=www.modelmayhem.com|access-date=2019-06-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160602092230/http://www.modelmayhem.com/2187131|archive-date=June 2, 2016|url-status=live}}</ref> Amofah stated in a [[Twitter#Tweets|tweet]] that the name Etika came from the 2003 video game ''[[Sonic Battle]]'', of which he was a fan in his youth. In the game, players could input a [[cheat code]] titled \"EkiTa\" into the game. When Amofah was 12, he simply switched the T's place with the K's as he \"liked that result better.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/etika/status/508630795452682240?lang|title=Where did the name \"Etika\" come from?|date=Sep 7, 2014|website=Twitter|access-date=|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191016132054/https://twitter.com/etika/status/508630795452682240?lang|archive-date=October 16, 2019|url-status=live}}{{Self-published source|date=November 2019}}</ref> He started using [[YouTube]] to broadcast his gaming and reaction streams in 2012 under his original username \"EWNetwork\" (meaning \"Etika World Network\"). It was originally planned for the channel's content to be produced collaboratively by a variety of users including Amofah himself, but such plans never materialized.<ref name=\"bbc\">{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/technology-48756120|website=BBC|title=Etika: Body found in search is missing YouTuber|date=June 25, 2019|publisher=[[BBC News]]|accessdate=June 25, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190626044929/https://www.bbc.com/news/technology-48756120|archive-date=June 26, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> Prior to the closure of his main channel on YouTube in 2018, he had more than 800,000 subscribers between his YouTube and [[Twitch (service)|Twitch]] channels, and within months after creating a second YouTube channel, known as \"EtikaFRFX\", he had gained more than 130,000 subscribers.<ref name=\"kotaku\">{{cite web|url=https://kotaku.com/popular-youtuber-etika-dies-at-29-1835842910|title=Popular YouTuber Etika Dies At 29|last=D'Anastasio|first=Cecilia|date=June 25, 2019|work=[[Kotaku]]|accessdate=June 25, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190626001652/https://kotaku.com/popular-youtuber-etika-dies-at-29-1835842910|archive-date=June 26, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cnn.com/2019/06/25/us/new-york-missing-youtuber-found-dead/index.html|website=CNN|title=Body pulled from the East River is that of missing YouTuber Etika, New York police say|first=Alanne|last=Orjoux|date=June 25, 2019|accessdate=June 25, 2019|publisher=[[CNN]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190625214857/https://www.cnn.com/2019/06/25/us/new-york-missing-youtuber-found-dead/index.html|archive-date=June 25, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nAmofah's content was typically described as Nintendo-focused.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.polygon.com/2016/11/17/13669064/nintendo-switch-fake-hoax-youtube|website=Polygon|title=Why do people keep making fake Nintendo consoles?|last=Frank|first=Allegra|date=October 17, 2016|accessdate=June 25, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170426212210/http://www.polygon.com/2016/11/17/13669064/nintendo-switch-fake-hoax-youtube|archive-date=April 26, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> He frequently streamed reactions, often over-the-top, to [[Nintendo Direct]] presentations, which usually involved him screaming and falling out of his chair in elated shock.<ref name=\"polygon mental health\" /> He dubbed his fans the \"Joy-Con Boyz\", after the [[Nintendo Switch]] controller known as the [[Joy-Con]]<ref name=\"kotaku\" /> and would frequently end his videos with his signature catchphrase \"Take care of yourself. Have yourself a damn good one!\"<ref>{{cite web | url = https://www.ign.com/articles/2019/11/09/mural-honoring-youtuber-etika-created-by-fans-in-new-york | title = Mural Honoring YouTuber Etika Created by Fans in New York | first = Matt | last = Kim | date = November 8, 2019 | accessdate = November 8, 2019 | work = [[IGN]] | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20191109003425/https://www.ign.com/articles/2019/11/09/mural-honoring-youtuber-etika-created-by-fans-in-new-york | archive-date = November 9, 2019 | url-status = live }}</ref> In November 2016, two videos of Amofah's where he purported to have a Nintendo Switch console before its 2017 release gained noterierty and were scrutinized by fans. It would eventually be learned the model Amofah was using was [[3D printing|3D-printed]] by fellow YouTuber \"Sandqvist\" at his request.<ref name=\":0\" /><ref>*{{Cite web|url=http://www.nintendolife.com/news/2016/11/weirdness_streamer_claims_to_have_nintendo_switch_flaunts_it_during_live_broadcast|title=Weirdness: Streamer Claims To Have Nintendo Switch, Flaunts It During Live Broadcast|last=Life|first=Nintendo|date=November 14, 2016|website=Nintendo Life|language=en-GB|access-date=June 25, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171224021250/http://www.nintendolife.com/news/2016/11/weirdness_streamer_claims_to_have_nintendo_switch_flaunts_it_during_live_broadcast|archive-date=December 24, 2017|url-status=live}}\n*{{Cite web|url=https://kotaku.com/that-youtuber-s-infamous-nintendo-switch-is-fake-1789096291|title=That YouTuber's Infamous 'Nintendo Switch' Is Fake [CORRECTED]|last=D'Anastasio|first=Cecilia|website=Kotaku|language=en-US|access-date=June 25, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190522092916/https://kotaku.com/that-youtuber-s-infamous-nintendo-switch-is-fake-1789096291|archive-date=May 22, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n===Controversies and channel terminations===\nIn June 2017, Amofah revealed himself to be the victim of multiple \"fake donations\", or \"chargebacks\" of large amounts of money sent to his [[PayPal]] account via stream donations, which would jostle Amofah with hundreds of dollars in processing fees.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://kotaku.com/youtuber-reminds-fans-how-much-fake-donations-can-hurt-1796342324|title=YouTuber Reminds Fans How Much Fake Donations Can Hurt|last=D'Anastasio|first=Cecilia|website=Kotaku|language=en-US|access-date=June 25, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190624172436/https://kotaku.com/youtuber-reminds-fans-how-much-fake-donations-can-hurt-1796342324|archive-date=June 24, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nIn October 2018, Amofah uploaded [[pornography]] to his YouTube channel EWNetwork (then titled Etika), which violated YouTube's policies and consequently led to the channel's termination. He later ended up getting his second channel EtikaFRFX terminated in April 2019 for the same reason.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://kotaku.com/youtuber-etika-livestreams-himself-getting-detained-by-1834393923|title=YouTuber Etika Livestreams Himself Getting Detained By Police To 19,000 Viewers|last=D'Anastasio|first=Cecilia|website=Kotaku|language=en-US|access-date=June 25, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190626001656/https://kotaku.com/youtuber-etika-livestreams-himself-getting-detained-by-1834393923|archive-date=June 26, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"nytimes\" /> He was also banned from [[Twitch (service)|Twitch]] that year for using a [[Homophobia|homophobic]] slur during a stream.<ref name=\":3\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.dailydot.com/upstream/etika-anti-semitic-homophobic-tweets/|title=Etika tweets anti-Semitic, homophobic messages\u2014then gets arrested|date=April 29, 2019|website=The Daily Dot|language=en|access-date=June 25, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190514045751/https://www.dailydot.com/upstream/etika-anti-semitic-homophobic-tweets/|archive-date=May 14, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> Following the termination of his channel, Amofah posted cryptic messages to social media, including the statement \"it's my turn to die\", coupled with a screenshot of his terminated account. Several of his followers felt that the messages and posts were very suicidal in nature, which quickly created a panic within his following.<ref name=\":1\" /><ref name=\"the verge\" /> Amofah took to social media that evening to confirm his well-being, along with other streamers who professed to having seen him safe and sound in person, so as to allay his followers' fears.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.newsweek.com/etika-responds-suicide-attempt-reddit-twitch-youtube-update-1189507|title=ETIKA RESPONDS TO SUICIDE ATTEMPT RUMORS ON REDDIT, SAYING 'YAY I BROKE THE WORLD'|first=Maria|last=Vultaggio|date=October 26, 2018|accessdate=June 25, 2019|work=[[Newsweek]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190123031259/https://www.newsweek.com/etika-responds-suicide-attempt-reddit-twitch-youtube-update-1189507|archive-date=January 23, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> He later apologized on his [[subreddit]] r/EtikaRedditNetwork.<ref name=\":1\" />\n\nOn April 16, 2019, Amofah tweeted that he was going to kill himself with a [[pistol]] he bought from a gun store in [[Long Island]], which led to his arrest and hospitalization. Christine Cardona, who had dated Amofah from 2011 to 2017, confirmed his well-being, and that she had been \"observing him all day\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.newsweek.com/etika-twitter-thealicepika-youtube-what-happened-savonarola-1397917|title=What happened to Etika? Streamer handcuffed and hospitalized after suicidal Twitter outburst|first=Steven|last=Asarch|date=April 16, 2019|website=Newsweek|language=en|access-date=June 25, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190623051250/https://www.newsweek.com/etika-twitter-thealicepika-youtube-what-happened-savonarola-1397917|archive-date=June 23, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> Days later, he posted a [[Photo manipulation#Photoshopping|photoshopped]] picture of himself holding a gun which Cardona later confirmed was fake. On April 29, after tweeting a vast quantity of cryptic messages, including homophobic and ethnic slurs (that were promptly deleted),<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.newsweek.com/youtube-etika-twitter-sky-williams-health-1408575|title=Etika is back on Twitter, posting pictures with guns and anti-semitic ideology|last=EDT|first=Steven Asarch On 4/29/19 at 1:07 PM|date=2019-04-29|website=Newsweek|language=en|access-date=2019-07-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190618045507/https://www.newsweek.com/youtube-etika-twitter-sky-williams-health-1408575|archive-date=June 18, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> he blocked close friends of his, including fellow YouTuber Sky Williams.<ref name=\":3\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.newsweek.com/youtube-etika-twitter-sky-williams-health-1408575|title=Etika is back on Twitter, posting pictures with guns and anti-semitic ideology|first=Steven|last=Asarch|date=April 29, 2019|website=Newsweek|language=en|access-date=June 25, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190618045507/https://www.newsweek.com/youtube-etika-twitter-sky-williams-health-1408575|archive-date=June 18, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> Later that day, he live-streamed himself getting detained by police to over 19,000 viewers on [[Instagram]] Live, after a concerned fan had notified police about his alarmingly erratic nature during the livestream.<ref name=\":1\" /><ref name=\":4\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.dailydot.com/upstream/etika-purge-all-life-keemstar-twitch/|title=Twitch star Etika says he wants to 'purge all life' in bonkers interview|date=May 1, 2019|website=The Daily Dot|language=en|access-date=June 25, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190501180557/https://www.dailydot.com/upstream/etika-purge-all-life-keemstar-twitch/|archive-date=May 1, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> He was also detained again later that same week for assaulting a police officer.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dailydot.com/upstream/etika-police-fight/|title=Etika reportedly detained after fighting police officer|date=May 2, 2019|website=The Daily Dot|language=en|access-date=June 25, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190516000104/https://www.dailydot.com/upstream/etika-police-fight/|archive-date=May 16, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> Amofah would then make an appearance on the YouTube channel \"DramaAlert\", run by Internet personality [[Keemstar]], for an interview, in which he stated he was the \"[[antichrist]]\" and that he wanted to \"purge all life\".<ref name=\":4\" /><ref name=\"dailydot keemstar\">{{cite web | url = https://www.dailydot.com/upstream/etika-mom-keemstar/ | title = Etika\u2019s mom defends Keemstar, says YouTuber isn\u2019t to blame for suicide | first = Josh | last = Katzowitz | date = July 1, 2019 | accessdate = July 1, 2019 | work = [[The Daily Dot]] | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20190701172901/https://www.dailydot.com/upstream/etika-mom-keemstar/ | archive-date = July 1, 2019 | url-status = live }}</ref>\n\n==Disappearance and death==\n[[File:I'm sorry.webm|thumb|thumbtime=25|upright|Video uploaded before Amofah's disappearance]]\nIn the late evening on June 19, 2019, Amofah posted a YouTube video titled \"I'm sorry\" to his personal YouTube channel TR1Iceman,<ref name=\"the verge\">{{cite web|url=https://www.theverge.com/2019/6/25/18714532/desmond-afoah-etika-youtube-nypd-statement|title=Popular YouTuber Desmond 'Etika' Amofah found dead|first=Julia|last=Alexander|date=June 25, 2019|accessdate=June 25, 2019|work=[[The Verge]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190626020059/https://www.theverge.com/2019/6/25/18714532/desmond-afoah-etika-youtube-nypd-statement|archive-date=June 26, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> alluding to his suicidal thoughts as he was walking down New York City streets. In the video he admitted to having mental health issues, struggling with the attention he had gained from streaming, and apologized for pushing people away from him.<ref name=\"bbc\" /> Amofah left a [[suicide note]] in the description of the video.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dexerto.com/entertainment/you-tube-star-etika-missing-after-posting-worrying-video-with-potential-suicide-note-734387|title=YouTuber Etika missing after posting distressing video alluding to suicide [UPDATED]|website=Dexerto.com|language=en|access-date=2019-07-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190717154659/https://www.dexerto.com/entertainment/you-tube-star-etika-missing-after-posting-worrying-video-with-potential-suicide-note-734387|archive-date=July 17, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> YouTube removed the video for violating its Community Guidelines, though Amofah's fans reposted the video to other outlets.<ref name=\"the verge\" />\n\nAmofah was last heard from at 11:16 PM [[Eastern Time]] (ET) that night<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Rec7YWiFZ9w&lc=UgzC2Cip2H79FqtiQpJ4AaABAg|title=TR1Iceman {{!}} YouTube|last=Amofah|first=Desmond|date=June 19, 2019|website=YouTube|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=December 1, 2019}}{{Self-published source|date=November 2019}}</ref> and was reported missing to the New York Police Department (NYPD) by June 20.<ref name=\"nypost\">{{Cite web|url=https://nypost.com/2019/06/21/youtube-star-etika-vanishes-after-posting-cryptic-suicidal-video/|title=YouTube star Etika vanishes after posting cryptic 'suicidal' video|last=Weissmann|first=Ruth|last2=Eustachewich|first2=Lia|date=June 21, 2019|website=New York Post|language=en|access-date=June 25, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190623004438/https://nypost.com/2019/06/21/youtube-star-etika-vanishes-after-posting-cryptic-suicidal-video/|archive-date=June 23, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> While the NYPD began its own search, fellow internet personalities and his fans tried to reach out to him to offer their help and show their appreciation of his work over the years.<ref name=\"petition\">{{cite web|url=https://www.cnn.com/2019/06/26/tech/etika-youtube-desmond-amofah-trnd/index.html|title=Fans petition YouTube to restore late vlogger Etika's account|first=Allen|last=Kim|date=June 26, 2019|accessdate=June 26, 2019|work=[[CNN]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190626155816/https://www.cnn.com/2019/06/26/tech/etika-youtube-desmond-amofah-trnd/index.html|archive-date=June 26, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn June 19, the same day of Amofah's disappearance, his belongings were discovered on the pedestrian walkway of the [[Manhattan Bridge]]. They included a backpack, wallet, laptop bag, cell phone, a change of clothes and a Nintendo Switch.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/technology-48743785|title=Missing YouTuber Etika's belongings found|date=June 24, 2019|access-date=June 25, 2019|language=en-GB|newspaper=British Broadcasting Corporation|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190626003711/https://www.bbc.com/news/technology-48743785|archive-date=June 26, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://abc7chicago.com/5361292/|website=ABC7 Chicago|title=YouTube star Etika missing, fans concerned after recent video|date=June 24, 2019|publisher=[[WLS-TV]]|language=en|access-date=June 25, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190626181503/https://abc7chicago.com/5361292/|archive-date=June 26, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> On the evening of June 24, a body was observed near Pier 16, approximately half a mile (0.8&nbsp;km) down the [[East River]] from where Amofah's belongings were recovered, and reported to the NYPD.<ref name=\"kotaku\" /> By the morning of June 25, the NYPD and emergency medical services had recovered the body, confirmed it was Amofah, and that he was dead at the point of recovery.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.cbsnews.com/news/etika-found-dead-missing-youtuber-desmond-amofah-new-york-tr1iceman-2019-06-25/ |title=Missing YouTuber Desmond \"Etika\" Amofah found dead in New York |first=Sophie |last=Lewis |date=25 June 2019 |access-date=26 June 2019 |work=[[CBS News]] |publisher=[[CBS Interactive Inc.]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190626180651/https://www.cbsnews.com/news/etika-found-dead-missing-youtuber-desmond-amofah-new-york-tr1iceman-2019-06-25/ |archive-date=June 26, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> The  [[Office of Chief Medical Examiner of the City of New York|Office of Chief Medical Examiner]] confirmed the cause of death was suicide by drowning the following day.<ref name=\"bbc\" /><ref name=\"abc cause\">{{cite web|last1=Jacobo|first1=Julia|title=YouTube gaming personality Desmond 'Etika' Amofah's died by suicide, officials say|url=https://abcnews.go.com/US/youtube-gaming-personality-desmond-etika-amofah-found-dead/story?id=63936521|website=[[ABC News]]|accessdate=June 26, 2019|date=June 26, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190626000911/https://abcnews.go.com/US/youtube-gaming-personality-desmond-etika-amofah-found-dead/story?id=63936521|archive-date=June 26, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Reactions==\nAmofah's death highlighted social media platforms' handling of posts by users who appear at risk with mental illness or who are contemplating suicide. YouTube, in removing Amofah's final video, stated that removal of such videos is standard practice to \"reduce the potential for copycat acts of self-harm, videos that express suicidal ideation\", and as part of this, sent the uploader information related to national suicide hotlines to provide help.<ref name=\"nytimes\">{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/06/26/style/etika-dead.html|title=Etika, a YouTube Personality, Is Mourned by Fans|first=Christine|last=Hauser|date=June 26, 2019|accessdate=June 26, 2019|work=[[The New York Times]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190626203942/https://www.nytimes.com/2019/06/26/style/etika-dead.html|archive-date=June 26, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nBecause of Amofah's activities in the months prior to his disappearance, some of his followers took these previous events as a humorous performance by Amofah rather than signs of him struggling with his mental health. Following his death, mental health researchers found several videos Amofah had posted that showed evidence of his troubled state but were taken as jokes by some of his viewers, rather than actual cries for help. As a result, some took Amofah's final video as yet another joke and disregarded any concern over his well-being; [[Keemstar]] initially thought Amofah's final video was a pre-meditated [[publicity stunt]], and stated after Amofah's death that \"I was never fully convinced that he was mentally ill or in trouble because of our private convos.\"<ref name=\"polygon mental health\"/> The aforementioned mental health researchers stressed the need to make more people on social media informed about the signs of mental illness, depression, and suicidal thoughts, so that they are able to recognize when people in a mindset similar to Amofah's are in danger and need support.<ref name=\"polygon mental health\">{{cite web | url = https://www.polygon.com/2019/7/2/20677759/etika-desmond-amofah-mental-health-illness-youtube | title = Too many people took Etika\u2019s mental health struggles as a joke | first = Patrick | last = Herandez | date = July 2, 2019 | accessdate = July 3, 2019 | work = [[Polygon (website)|Polygon]] | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20190702181147/https://www.polygon.com/2019/7/2/20677759/etika-desmond-amofah-mental-health-illness-youtube | archive-date = July 2, 2019 | url-status = live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url = https://www.theverge.com/2019/6/27/18759603/desmond-etika-amofah-death-youtube-creator-mental-health | title = YouTuber Etika\u2019s death spurs conversation about how viewers react to creators\u2019 mental health struggles | first = Julia | last = Alexander | date = June 27, 2019 | accessdate = July 3, 2019 | work = [[The Verge]] | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20190703173241/https://www.theverge.com/2019/6/27/18759603/desmond-etika-amofah-death-youtube-creator-mental-health | archive-date = July 3, 2019 | url-status = live }}</ref> Keemstar briefly became a target of some of Amofah's fans, who blamed him for Amofah's suicide due to the \"DramaAlert\" interview and statements made in tweets prior to and following the interview. Amofah's mother wrote to these fans to assure them that Keemstar was in no way responsible for Amofah's death, stating that \"Etika loved Keemstar's show\" and only wanted to make a memorable appearance on it.<ref name=\"dailydot keemstar\"/>\n\n==Legacy==\nFollowing Amofah's suicide, fans on Twitter and in emails asked that YouTube re-upload Amofah's final video to help memorialize him. A [[Change.org]] petition was started and initially garnered more than 380,000 signatures, but later dropped to 197,000 signatures after many fraudulent signatures from [[internet bot]]s were removed. It asked for Amofah's original channel to be restored to preserve his legacy.<ref name=\"the verge\" /><ref name=\"variety\">{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2019/digital/news/etika-desmond-amofah-youtube-found-dead-1203252700/|title=Gaming YouTuber Desmond 'Etika' Amofah Found Dead, NYPD Says|first=Todd|last=Spangler|date=June 25, 2019|accessdate=June 25, 2019|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190626181505/https://variety.com/2019/digital/news/etika-desmond-amofah-youtube-found-dead-1203252700/|archive-date=June 26, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"petition\" /> Another Change.org petition with over a million signatures, which later dropped to more than 200,000 signatures for similar reasons, called for Amofah to be buried at YouTube headquarters, which he stated as his wish during an earlier livestream.<ref>{{Cite web | url = https://metro.co.uk/2019/06/25/etika-wanted-buried-front-youtube-hq-police-confirm-gamers-death-10071622/ | title = Etika wanted to be buried in front of YouTube HQ as police confirm gamer\u2019s death | first = Mel | last = Evans | date = June 25, 2019 | accessdate = June 28, 2019 | work = [[Metro (British newspaper)|Metro]] | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20190628223006/https://metro.co.uk/2019/06/25/etika-wanted-buried-front-youtube-hq-police-confirm-gamers-death-10071622/ | archive-date = June 28, 2019 | url-status = live }}</ref>\n\nFans later erected a memorial on Amofah's behalf on the pedestrian walkway of the Manhattan Bridge, leaving letters, [[fan art]], [[Twizzlers]], Nintendo-related products and other [[memorabilia]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.insideedition.com/fans-create-memorial-gamer-etika-new-york-54046|title=Fans Create Memorial for Gamer Etika in New York|date=2019-06-28|website=Inside Edition|language=en-US|access-date=2019-07-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190701154631/https://www.insideedition.com/fans-create-memorial-gamer-etika-new-york-54046|archive-date=July 1, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn June 25, 2019, YouTuber Abe Hunter announced he was the owner and operator of Amofah's website<ref>{{cite tweet |user=pressabetostart|number=1143610944708386817 |date = 25 June 2019 |title=So, I was working on something for Etika a while back & because of that I still own http://etikaworldnetwork.com}}{{Self-published source|date=November 2019}}</ref> and converted it into a fundraiser site where 100% of the profits are donated to [[National Alliance on Mental Illness]] (NAMI) in Amofah's name.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://etikaworldnetwork.myshopify.com/|title=Etika World Network|website=etikaworldnetwork|language=en|access-date=2019-07-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190710174036/https://etikaworldnetwork.myshopify.com/|archive-date=July 10, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> On July 15, 2019 on behalf of the JOYCONBOYZ community; Abe Hunter donated the $11,315.25 raised to [[National Alliance on Mental Illness]] (NAMI) in memory of Amofah.<ref>{{cite tweet |user=namicommunicate |author-link=National Alliance on Mental Illness |number=1150816136751124480 |date=July 15, 2019 |title=Thank you to the #JOYCONBOYZ for their donation of $11,315.25 in memory of Desmond Amofah aka \"Etika\" from Abe of Blockhead Entertainment LLC. We appreciate your support!.}}</ref>\n\nOn July 21, 2019, YouTuber [[PewDiePie]] started a fundraiser on the [[crowdfunding]] website [[GoFundMe]] with American actor [[Jack Black]] for the [[National Alliance on Mental Illness]] (NAMI), due to the death of Amofah. PewDiePie and Black streamed themselves playing ''[[Minecraft]]'' together to raise money for their fundraiser. PewDiePie donated $10,000 to the fundraiser and raised over $30,000 for NAMI.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://metro.co.uk/2019/07/21/pewdiepie-donates-8000-content-creators-mental-health-charity-honour-etika-10436272/|title=PewDiePie donates \u00a38000 to mental health charity in honour of Etika|date=2019-07-21|website=Metro|language=en-US|access-date=2019-07-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190727155812/https://metro.co.uk/2019/07/21/pewdiepie-donates-8000-content-creators-mental-health-charity-honour-etika-10436272/|archive-date=July 27, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn August 13, 2019, an [[Indiegogo]] campaign was started on Etika's behalf. The Charity campaign was created to earn donations for [[The Jed Foundation]]. Contributors to the campaign received a custom made pair of Etika themed joy-cons, dubbed \"Etikons\" <ref>https://www.indiegogo.com/projects/etikons-custom-etika-themed-joy-cons-for-charity--2/x/22111641#/</ref>\n\nOn November 6, 2019, it was revealed that after raising the initial $11,315.25 for [[National Alliance on Mental Illness]] (NAMI),<ref>{{cite tweet |user=namicommunicate |author-link=National Alliance on Mental Illness |number=1150816136751124480 |date=July 15, 2019 |title=Thank you to the #JOYCONBOYZ for their donation of $11,315.25 in memory of Desmond Amofah aka \"Etika\" from Abe of Blockhead Entertainment LLC. We appreciate your support!.}}{{Self-published source|date=November 2019}}</ref> YouTubers Abe Hunter and Double-A worked with Mural Artist BK FOXX, Graffiti artist Kestaadm and JMZWalls to create a 40-feet long mural dedicated to Amofah in [[Bushwick, Brooklyn]].<ref>{{cite web | url = https://kotaku.com/fans-honor-deceased-youtuber-etika-with-a-stunning-mura-1839725766 | title = Fans Honor Deceased YouTuber Etika With A Stunning Mural | first = Cecelia | last = D'Anastasio | date = November 8, 2019 | accessdate = November 8, 2019 | work = [[Kotaku]] | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20191108215035/https://kotaku.com/fans-honor-deceased-youtuber-etika-with-a-stunning-mura-1839725766 | archive-date = November 8, 2019 | url-status = live }}</ref> The mural was created to celebrate Amofah's life and to help bring awareness to mental health. The mural's location was added as a virtual \"Pok\u00e9Stop\" in the augmented reality game ''[[Pok\u00e9mon Go]]'' in February 2020 after over 350,000 people requested Nintendo to add it in memory of Amofah.<ref>{{cite web | url = https://www.polygon.com/2020/2/25/21152509/pokemon-go-etika-desmond-amofah-joycon-boyz-mural-pokestop-memorial | title = Etika\u2019s face is now a Pok\u00e9mon Go stop, thanks to a YouTuber and his fans | first = Patricia | last = Hernandez | date = February 25, 2020 | accessdate = February 25, 2020 | work = [[Polygon (website)|Polygon]] }}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of solved missing persons cases]]\n*[[List of YouTubers]]\n\n==Notes==\n{{notelist}}\n{{Reflist|group=note}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category}}\n* {{IMDb name|8813048}}\n* {{YouTube|Etika|u=TR1Iceman}}\n{{Portal bar|Biography|New York City|Internet|Video games}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:1990 births]]\n[[Category:2019 deaths]]\n[[Category:2010s missing person cases]]\n[[Category:African-American male models]]\n[[Category:American people of Ghanaian descent]]\n[[Category:American YouTubers]]\n[[Category:Articles containing video clips]]\n[[Category:Deaths by drowning]]\n[[Category:Formerly missing people found dead]]\n[[Category:Gaming YouTubers]]\n[[Category:Internet memes]]\n[[Category:Internet-related controversies]]\n[[Category:Let's Players]]\n[[Category:Male models who committed suicide]]\n[[Category:Male suicides]]\n[[Category:Male YouTubers]]\n[[Category:Missing person cases in New York]]\n[[Category:Models from New York City]]\n[[Category:People from Brooklyn]]\n[[Category:Suicides by drowning in the United States]]\n[[Category:Suicides by jumping in New York City]]\n[[Category:Suicides in New York City]]\n[[Category:Twitch streamers]]\n[[Category:YouTube channels launched in 2012]]\n[[Category:YouTube channels closed in 2018]]\n[[Category:YouTube controversies]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use mdy dates|date=June 2019}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Etika\n| image              = Etika in 2019 - 2.jpg\n| caption            = Etika in May 2019\n| birth_name         = Desmond Daniel Amofah\n| birth_date         = {{Birth date|1990|5|12}}\n| birth_place        = [[Brooklyn]], [[New York City|New York]], U.S.\n| nationality        = [[Americans|American]]\n| height             = {{convert|6|ft|6|in|m}}<ref>{{cite web | url = https://heavy.com/entertainment/2018/10/etika/ | title = Is Etika OK? YouTuber Writes \u2018It\u2019s My Turn to Die\u2019 on Reddit | first = Paul | last=  Farrell | date = October 26, 2018 | accessdate = March 5, 2020 | work = [[Heavy (website)|Heavy]] }}</ref>\n| other_names        = {{ubl|Iceman}}\n| occupation         = {{Flatlist|\n*[[YouTuber]]\n*[[Online streamer|streamer]]\n*[[Model (person)|model]]\n}}\n| years_active       = 2011\u20132015 (model)<br/>2012\u20132019 (YouTuber)\n| death_date         = {{circa|{{Death date and age|2019|06|19|1990|5|12}}|lk=yes|i=yes}}\n| death_cause        = [[Suicide methods#Drowning|Suicide by drowning]]\n| death_place        = [[Manhattan]], New York, U.S.\n| parents            = {{plainlist|\n*[[Owuraku Amofah]] (father)\n*Sabrina Amofah (mother)\n}}\n| website            = {{URL|etikaworldnetwork.com}}\n| module             = {{Infobox YouTube personality\n| embed = yes\n| channels       = {{ubl|[https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCh0SxnImUvpWs_ZfEoyhkMA EWNetwork] (terminated)|[https://www.youtube.com/channel/UC8Fd7MyCATxj4PvDjgHC9rg EtikaFRFX] (terminated)|[https://www.youtube.com/user/Tr1Iceman TR1Iceman]|[https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCeVmD7fCjUo5Nqk35zcF6Og E Live]}}\n| years_active         = 2012\u20132019\n| catchphrase(s)       = {{ubl|\"What's going on guys? Etika, from the Etika World Network here.\"|\"Take care of yourselves, and of course, as usual, please have yourself a damn good one.\"}}\n| genre             = {{flatlist|\n* [[Let's Play]]\n* [[Reaction_video|react]]\n* [[vlog]]\n* [[comedy]]\n}}\n| subscribers          = 1.3 million (combined)\n| subscriber_date      = \n| views                = 145 million (combined)\n| view_date            = \n| network              = \n| associated_acts      = \n| silver_button        = yes \n| silver_year          = 2015{{efn|Amofah passed 100,000 subscribers on three channels; EWNetwork in 2015, EtikaFRFX in 2018<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://socialblade.com/youtube/channel/UC8Fd7MyCATxj4PvDjgHC9rg/monthly|title=UC8Fd7MyCATxj4PvDjgHC9rg Monthly YouTube Statistics - Socialblade.com|website=socialblade.com|access-date=2019-07-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190722151535/https://socialblade.com/youtube/channel/UC8Fd7MyCATxj4PvDjgHC9rg/monthly|archive-date=July 22, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> and TR1Iceman in 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://socialblade.com/youtube/user/tr1iceman/monthly|title=Tr1Iceman Monthly YouTube Statistics - Socialblade.com|website=socialblade.com|access-date=2019-07-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190722151540/https://socialblade.com/youtube/user/tr1iceman/monthly|archive-date=July 22, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>}}\n| gold_button          = \n| gold_year            = \n| diamond_button       = \n| diamond_year         = \n| ruby_button          = \n| ruby_year            = \n| stats_update         = {{today}}\n}}\n}}\n{{short description|American YouTuber and live streamer}}\n{{Use American English|date=June 2019}}\n\n'''Desmond Daniel Amofah''' (May 12, 1990 \u2013 {{Circa|June 19, 2019}}), better known by his online alias '''Etika''', was an American [[YouTuber]], [[Online streamer|streamer]] and [[Model (person)|model]]. He was best known for his over-the-top [[Reaction video|reactions]] to [[Nintendo Direct]] presentations, of which many became popular [[Internet meme|internet memes.]]\n\nFollowing several months that involved Amofah exhibiting signs of [[Mental disorder|mental illness]], as well as threatening to commit [[suicide]] on multiple occasions, he disappeared on the evening of June 19, 2019, after uploading an apologetic video in which he admitted to being mentally ill and suicidal. Amofah's body was discovered in the [[East River]] on June 25 by the [[New York City Police Department]], after it was believed he jumped from the [[Manhattan Bridge]]. On June 26, the [[Office of Chief Medical Examiner of the City of New York|Office of Chief Medical Examiner]] determined that Amofah committed [[suicide]] by drowning.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnn.com/2019/07/01/us/youtube-etika-desmond-amofah-suicide-trnd/index.html|title=YouTuber Etika died by suicide, medical examiner says|author=Alanne Orjoux|website=CNN|access-date=2019-08-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190728085956/https://www.cnn.com/2019/07/01/us/youtube-etika-desmond-amofah-suicide-trnd/index.html|archive-date=July 28, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Early life==\nDesmond Daniel Amofah was born on May 12, 1990,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/Etika|title=Etika @ 999 (@Etika) {{!}} Twitter|website=twitter.com|language=en|access-date=2019-07-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190711052221/https://twitter.com/Etika|archive-date=July 11, 2019|url-status=live}}{{Self-published source|date=November 2019}}</ref> in [[Brooklyn]], [[New York (state)|New York]], to father [[Owuraku Amofah]], a Ghanaian politician and lawyer from [[Kibi, Ghana]],<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.graphic.com.gh/news/general-news/ghana-news-former-dept-minister-s-son-found-dead-in-manhattan.html|title=Former Dept minister's son, Desmond Amofah, found dead in Manhattan|date=June 26, 2019|work=Graphic Online|access-date=|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190628085944/https://www.graphic.com.gh/news/general-news/ghana-news-former-dept-minister-s-son-found-dead-in-manhattan.html|archive-date=June 28, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> and mother, Sabrina Amofah. Owuraku served as a member of the [[Parliament of Ghana]] for Abuakwa Central constituency from 1992 to 1996. Owuraku's father's relative (addressed by him as \"uncle\") [[Nana Akufo-Addo]], of the prominent Ghanaian [[Ofori-Atta]] family,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.questia.com/magazine/1G1-371284846/why-akufo-addo-chose-caution-not-confrontation|title=\"Why Akufo-Addo Chose Caution, Not Confrontation\" by Duodu, Cameron - New African, Issue 538, April 2014 {{!}} Online Research Library: Questia|website=www.questia.com|access-date=2019-06-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190627163859/https://www.questia.com/magazine/1G1-371284846/why-akufo-addo-chose-caution-not-confrontation|archive-date=June 27, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> became [[President of Ghana]] in January 2017.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ghanaweb.com/GhanaHomePage/NewsArchive/Akufo-Addo-destroyed-his-family-s-good-work-Owuraku-Amofa-489084#|title=Akufo-Addo destroyed his family's good work - Owuraku Amofa|website=www.ghanaweb.com|access-date=June 26, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190626182536/https://www.ghanaweb.com/GhanaHomePage/NewsArchive/Akufo-Addo-destroyed-his-family-s-good-work-Owuraku-Amofa-489084|archive-date=June 26, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ghanaweb.com/GhanaHomePage/NewsArchive/I-don-t-regret-supporting-Nana-Addo-Owuraku-Amofa-445958|title=I don\u2019t regret supporting Nana Addo \u2013 Owuraku Amofa|website=www.ghanaweb.com|access-date=June 26, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190626182539/https://www.ghanaweb.com/GhanaHomePage/NewsArchive/I-don-t-regret-supporting-Nana-Addo-Owuraku-Amofa-445958|archive-date=June 26, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> Amofah had several siblings, including an older brother, Randy Amofah, who died on October 31, 2010<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://heavy.com/news/2019/06/etika-brother-randy-amofah-dead/|title=Etika\u2019s Older Brother Randy Amofah Died in 2010|last=Bicks|first=Emily|date=2019-06-25|work=[[Heavy.com]]|language=en|access-date=2019-06-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190626185258/https://heavy.com/news/2019/06/etika-brother-randy-amofah-dead/|archive-date=June 26, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> from an [[asthma attack]] while driving through a [[Dust storm|sandstorm]] in [[Ghana]], according to Amofah's ex-girlfriend Christine Cardona.\n\n==Career==\n===Modeling, streaming and YouTube career===\nPrior to the ''Etika'' branding, Amofah was active in modeling and rapping, having released an independently produced [[mixtape]] titled \"Written In Ice\" in 2007, under his pseudonym, \"Iceman\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://genius.com/artists/Etika|title=Etika|website=Genius|language=en|access-date=2019-06-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190626181505/https://genius.com/artists/Etika|archive-date=June 26, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> He started modeling in 2011 and continued until 2015.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.modelmayhem.com/2187131|title=Desmond Amofah|website=www.modelmayhem.com|access-date=2019-06-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160602092230/http://www.modelmayhem.com/2187131|archive-date=June 2, 2016|url-status=live}}</ref> Amofah stated in a [[Twitter#Tweets|tweet]] that the name Etika came from the 2003 video game ''[[Sonic Battle]]'', of which he was a fan in his youth. In the game, players could input a [[cheat code]] titled \"EkiTa\" into the game. When Amofah was 12, he simply switched the T's place with the K's as he \"liked that result better.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/etika/status/508630795452682240?lang|title=Where did the name \"Etika\" come from?|date=Sep 7, 2014|website=Twitter|access-date=|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191016132054/https://twitter.com/etika/status/508630795452682240?lang|archive-date=October 16, 2019|url-status=live}}{{Self-published source|date=November 2019}}</ref> He started using [[YouTube]] to broadcast his gaming and reaction streams in 2012 under his original username \"EWNetwork\" (meaning \"Etika World Network\"). It was originally planned for the channel's content to be produced collaboratively by a variety of users including Amofah himself, but such plans never materialized.<ref name=\"bbc\">{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/technology-48756120|website=BBC|title=Etika: Body found in search is missing YouTuber|date=June 25, 2019|publisher=[[BBC News]]|accessdate=June 25, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190626044929/https://www.bbc.com/news/technology-48756120|archive-date=June 26, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> Prior to the closure of his main channel on YouTube in 2018, he had more than 800,000 subscribers between his YouTube and [[Twitch (service)|Twitch]] channels, and within months after creating a second YouTube channel, known as \"EtikaFRFX\", he had gained more than 130,000 subscribers.<ref name=\"kotaku\">{{cite web|url=https://kotaku.com/popular-youtuber-etika-dies-at-29-1835842910|title=Popular YouTuber Etika Dies At 29|last=D'Anastasio|first=Cecilia|date=June 25, 2019|work=[[Kotaku]]|accessdate=June 25, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190626001652/https://kotaku.com/popular-youtuber-etika-dies-at-29-1835842910|archive-date=June 26, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cnn.com/2019/06/25/us/new-york-missing-youtuber-found-dead/index.html|website=CNN|title=Body pulled from the East River is that of missing YouTuber Etika, New York police say|first=Alanne|last=Orjoux|date=June 25, 2019|accessdate=June 25, 2019|publisher=[[CNN]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190625214857/https://www.cnn.com/2019/06/25/us/new-york-missing-youtuber-found-dead/index.html|archive-date=June 25, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nAmofah's content was typically described as Nintendo-focused.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.polygon.com/2016/11/17/13669064/nintendo-switch-fake-hoax-youtube|website=Polygon|title=Why do people keep making fake Nintendo consoles?|last=Frank|first=Allegra|date=October 17, 2016|accessdate=June 25, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170426212210/http://www.polygon.com/2016/11/17/13669064/nintendo-switch-fake-hoax-youtube|archive-date=April 26, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> He frequently streamed reactions, often over-the-top, to [[Nintendo Direct]] presentations, which usually involved him screaming and falling out of his chair in elated shock.<ref name=\"polygon mental health\" /> He dubbed his fans the \"Joy-Con Boyz\", after the [[Nintendo Switch]] controller known as the [[Joy-Con]]<ref name=\"kotaku\" /> and would frequently end his videos with his signature catchphrase \"Take care of yourself. Have yourself a damn good one!\"<ref>{{cite web | url = https://www.ign.com/articles/2019/11/09/mural-honoring-youtuber-etika-created-by-fans-in-new-york | title = Mural Honoring YouTuber Etika Created by Fans in New York | first = Matt | last = Kim | date = November 8, 2019 | accessdate = November 8, 2019 | work = [[IGN]] | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20191109003425/https://www.ign.com/articles/2019/11/09/mural-honoring-youtuber-etika-created-by-fans-in-new-york | archive-date = November 9, 2019 | url-status = live }}</ref> In November 2016, two videos of Amofah's where he purported to have a Nintendo Switch console before its 2017 release gained noterierty and were scrutinized by fans. It would eventually be learned the model Amofah was using was [[3D printing|3D-printed]] by fellow YouTuber \"Sandqvist\" at his request.<ref name=\":0\" /><ref>*{{Cite web|url=http://www.nintendolife.com/news/2016/11/weirdness_streamer_claims_to_have_nintendo_switch_flaunts_it_during_live_broadcast|title=Weirdness: Streamer Claims To Have Nintendo Switch, Flaunts It During Live Broadcast|last=Life|first=Nintendo|date=November 14, 2016|website=Nintendo Life|language=en-GB|access-date=June 25, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171224021250/http://www.nintendolife.com/news/2016/11/weirdness_streamer_claims_to_have_nintendo_switch_flaunts_it_during_live_broadcast|archive-date=December 24, 2017|url-status=live}}\n*{{Cite web|url=https://kotaku.com/that-youtuber-s-infamous-nintendo-switch-is-fake-1789096291|title=That YouTuber's Infamous 'Nintendo Switch' Is Fake [CORRECTED]|last=D'Anastasio|first=Cecilia|website=Kotaku|language=en-US|access-date=June 25, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190522092916/https://kotaku.com/that-youtuber-s-infamous-nintendo-switch-is-fake-1789096291|archive-date=May 22, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n===Controversies and channel terminations===\nIn June 2017, Amofah revealed himself to be the victim of multiple \"fake donations\", or \"chargebacks\" of large amounts of money sent to his [[PayPal]] account via stream donations, which would jostle Amofah with hundreds of dollars in processing fees.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://kotaku.com/youtuber-reminds-fans-how-much-fake-donations-can-hurt-1796342324|title=YouTuber Reminds Fans How Much Fake Donations Can Hurt|last=D'Anastasio|first=Cecilia|website=Kotaku|language=en-US|access-date=June 25, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190624172436/https://kotaku.com/youtuber-reminds-fans-how-much-fake-donations-can-hurt-1796342324|archive-date=June 24, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nIn October 2018, Amofah uploaded [[pornography]] to his YouTube channel EWNetwork (then titled Etika), which violated YouTube's policies and consequently led to the channel's termination. He later ended up getting his second channel EtikaFRFX terminated in April 2019 for the same reason.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://kotaku.com/youtuber-etika-livestreams-himself-getting-detained-by-1834393923|title=YouTuber Etika Livestreams Himself Getting Detained By Police To 19,000 Viewers|last=D'Anastasio|first=Cecilia|website=Kotaku|language=en-US|access-date=June 25, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190626001656/https://kotaku.com/youtuber-etika-livestreams-himself-getting-detained-by-1834393923|archive-date=June 26, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"nytimes\" /> He was also banned from [[Twitch (service)|Twitch]] that year for using a [[Homophobia|homophobic]] slur during a stream.<ref name=\":3\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.dailydot.com/upstream/etika-anti-semitic-homophobic-tweets/|title=Etika tweets anti-Semitic, homophobic messages\u2014then gets arrested|date=April 29, 2019|website=The Daily Dot|language=en|access-date=June 25, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190514045751/https://www.dailydot.com/upstream/etika-anti-semitic-homophobic-tweets/|archive-date=May 14, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> Following the termination of his channel, Amofah posted cryptic messages to social media, including the statement \"it's my turn to die\", coupled with a screenshot of his terminated account. Several of his followers felt that the messages and posts were very suicidal in nature, which quickly created a panic within his following.<ref name=\":1\" /><ref name=\"the verge\" /> Amofah took to social media that evening to confirm his well-being, along with other streamers who professed to having seen him safe and sound in person, so as to allay his followers' fears.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.newsweek.com/etika-responds-suicide-attempt-reddit-twitch-youtube-update-1189507|title=ETIKA RESPONDS TO SUICIDE ATTEMPT RUMORS ON REDDIT, SAYING 'YAY I BROKE THE WORLD'|first=Maria|last=Vultaggio|date=October 26, 2018|accessdate=June 25, 2019|work=[[Newsweek]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190123031259/https://www.newsweek.com/etika-responds-suicide-attempt-reddit-twitch-youtube-update-1189507|archive-date=January 23, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> He later apologized on his [[subreddit]] r/EtikaRedditNetwork.<ref name=\":1\" />\n\nOn April 16, 2019, Amofah tweeted that he was going to kill himself with a [[pistol]] he bought from a gun store in [[Long Island]], which led to his arrest and hospitalization. Christine Cardona, who had dated Amofah from 2011 to 2017, confirmed his well-being, and that she had been \"observing him all day\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.newsweek.com/etika-twitter-thealicepika-youtube-what-happened-savonarola-1397917|title=What happened to Etika? Streamer handcuffed and hospitalized after suicidal Twitter outburst|first=Steven|last=Asarch|date=April 16, 2019|website=Newsweek|language=en|access-date=June 25, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190623051250/https://www.newsweek.com/etika-twitter-thealicepika-youtube-what-happened-savonarola-1397917|archive-date=June 23, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> Days later, he posted a [[Photo manipulation#Photoshopping|photoshopped]] picture of himself holding a gun which Cardona later confirmed was fake. On April 29, after tweeting a vast quantity of cryptic messages, including homophobic and ethnic slurs (that were promptly deleted),<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.newsweek.com/youtube-etika-twitter-sky-williams-health-1408575|title=Etika is back on Twitter, posting pictures with guns and anti-semitic ideology|last=EDT|first=Steven Asarch On 4/29/19 at 1:07 PM|date=2019-04-29|website=Newsweek|language=en|access-date=2019-07-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190618045507/https://www.newsweek.com/youtube-etika-twitter-sky-williams-health-1408575|archive-date=June 18, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> he blocked close friends of his, including fellow YouTuber Sky Williams.<ref name=\":3\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.newsweek.com/youtube-etika-twitter-sky-williams-health-1408575|title=Etika is back on Twitter, posting pictures with guns and anti-semitic ideology|first=Steven|last=Asarch|date=April 29, 2019|website=Newsweek|language=en|access-date=June 25, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190618045507/https://www.newsweek.com/youtube-etika-twitter-sky-williams-health-1408575|archive-date=June 18, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> Later that day, he live-streamed himself getting detained by police to over 19,000 viewers on [[Instagram]] Live, after a concerned fan had notified police about his alarmingly erratic nature during the livestream.<ref name=\":1\" /><ref name=\":4\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.dailydot.com/upstream/etika-purge-all-life-keemstar-twitch/|title=Twitch star Etika says he wants to 'purge all life' in bonkers interview|date=May 1, 2019|website=The Daily Dot|language=en|access-date=June 25, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190501180557/https://www.dailydot.com/upstream/etika-purge-all-life-keemstar-twitch/|archive-date=May 1, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> He was also detained again later that same week for assaulting a police officer.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dailydot.com/upstream/etika-police-fight/|title=Etika reportedly detained after fighting police officer|date=May 2, 2019|website=The Daily Dot|language=en|access-date=June 25, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190516000104/https://www.dailydot.com/upstream/etika-police-fight/|archive-date=May 16, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> Amofah would then make an appearance on the YouTube channel \"DramaAlert\", run by Internet personality [[Keemstar]], for an interview, in which he stated he was the \"[[antichrist]]\" and that he wanted to \"purge all life\".<ref name=\":4\" /><ref name=\"dailydot keemstar\">{{cite web | url = https://www.dailydot.com/upstream/etika-mom-keemstar/ | title = Etika\u2019s mom defends Keemstar, says YouTuber isn\u2019t to blame for suicide | first = Josh | last = Katzowitz | date = July 1, 2019 | accessdate = July 1, 2019 | work = [[The Daily Dot]] | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20190701172901/https://www.dailydot.com/upstream/etika-mom-keemstar/ | archive-date = July 1, 2019 | url-status = live }}</ref>\n\n==Disappearance and death==\n[[File:I'm sorry.webm|thumb|thumbtime=25|upright|Video uploaded before Amofah's disappearance]]\nIn the late evening on June 19, 2019, Amofah posted a YouTube video titled \"I'm sorry\" to his personal YouTube channel TR1Iceman,<ref name=\"the verge\">{{cite web|url=https://www.theverge.com/2019/6/25/18714532/desmond-afoah-etika-youtube-nypd-statement|title=Popular YouTuber Desmond 'Etika' Amofah found dead|first=Julia|last=Alexander|date=June 25, 2019|accessdate=June 25, 2019|work=[[The Verge]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190626020059/https://www.theverge.com/2019/6/25/18714532/desmond-afoah-etika-youtube-nypd-statement|archive-date=June 26, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> alluding to his suicidal thoughts as he was walking down New York City streets. In the video he admitted to having mental health issues, struggling with the attention he had gained from streaming, and apologized for pushing people away from him.<ref name=\"bbc\" /> Amofah left a [[suicide note]] in the description of the video.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dexerto.com/entertainment/you-tube-star-etika-missing-after-posting-worrying-video-with-potential-suicide-note-734387|title=YouTuber Etika missing after posting distressing video alluding to suicide [UPDATED]|website=Dexerto.com|language=en|access-date=2019-07-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190717154659/https://www.dexerto.com/entertainment/you-tube-star-etika-missing-after-posting-worrying-video-with-potential-suicide-note-734387|archive-date=July 17, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> YouTube removed the video for violating its Community Guidelines, though Amofah's fans reposted the video to other outlets.<ref name=\"the verge\" />\n\nAmofah was last heard from at 11:16 PM [[Eastern Time]] (ET) that night<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Rec7YWiFZ9w&lc=UgzC2Cip2H79FqtiQpJ4AaABAg|title=TR1Iceman {{!}} YouTube|last=Amofah|first=Desmond|date=June 19, 2019|website=YouTube|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=December 1, 2019}}{{Self-published source|date=November 2019}}</ref> and was reported missing to the New York Police Department (NYPD) by June 20.<ref name=\"nypost\">{{Cite web|url=https://nypost.com/2019/06/21/youtube-star-etika-vanishes-after-posting-cryptic-suicidal-video/|title=YouTube star Etika vanishes after posting cryptic 'suicidal' video|last=Weissmann|first=Ruth|last2=Eustachewich|first2=Lia|date=June 21, 2019|website=New York Post|language=en|access-date=June 25, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190623004438/https://nypost.com/2019/06/21/youtube-star-etika-vanishes-after-posting-cryptic-suicidal-video/|archive-date=June 23, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> While the NYPD began its own search, fellow internet personalities and his fans tried to reach out to him to offer their help and show their appreciation of his work over the years.<ref name=\"petition\">{{cite web|url=https://www.cnn.com/2019/06/26/tech/etika-youtube-desmond-amofah-trnd/index.html|title=Fans petition YouTube to restore late vlogger Etika's account|first=Allen|last=Kim|date=June 26, 2019|accessdate=June 26, 2019|work=[[CNN]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190626155816/https://www.cnn.com/2019/06/26/tech/etika-youtube-desmond-amofah-trnd/index.html|archive-date=June 26, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn June 19, the same day of Amofah's disappearance, his belongings were discovered on the pedestrian walkway of the [[Manhattan Bridge]]. They included a backpack, wallet, laptop bag, cell phone, a change of clothes and a Nintendo Switch.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/technology-48743785|title=Missing YouTuber Etika's belongings found|date=June 24, 2019|access-date=June 25, 2019|language=en-GB|newspaper=British Broadcasting Corporation|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190626003711/https://www.bbc.com/news/technology-48743785|archive-date=June 26, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://abc7chicago.com/5361292/|website=ABC7 Chicago|title=YouTube star Etika missing, fans concerned after recent video|date=June 24, 2019|publisher=[[WLS-TV]]|language=en|access-date=June 25, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190626181503/https://abc7chicago.com/5361292/|archive-date=June 26, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> On the evening of June 24, a body was observed near Pier 16, approximately half a mile (0.8&nbsp;km) down the [[East River]] from where Amofah's belongings were recovered, and reported to the NYPD.<ref name=\"kotaku\" /> By the morning of June 25, the NYPD and emergency medical services had recovered the body, confirmed it was Amofah, and that he was dead at the point of recovery.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.cbsnews.com/news/etika-found-dead-missing-youtuber-desmond-amofah-new-york-tr1iceman-2019-06-25/ |title=Missing YouTuber Desmond \"Etika\" Amofah found dead in New York |first=Sophie |last=Lewis |date=25 June 2019 |access-date=26 June 2019 |work=[[CBS News]] |publisher=[[CBS Interactive Inc.]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190626180651/https://www.cbsnews.com/news/etika-found-dead-missing-youtuber-desmond-amofah-new-york-tr1iceman-2019-06-25/ |archive-date=June 26, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> The  [[Office of Chief Medical Examiner of the City of New York|Office of Chief Medical Examiner]] confirmed the cause of death was suicide by drowning the following day.<ref name=\"bbc\" /><ref name=\"abc cause\">{{cite web|last1=Jacobo|first1=Julia|title=YouTube gaming personality Desmond 'Etika' Amofah's died by suicide, officials say|url=https://abcnews.go.com/US/youtube-gaming-personality-desmond-etika-amofah-found-dead/story?id=63936521|website=[[ABC News]]|accessdate=June 26, 2019|date=June 26, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190626000911/https://abcnews.go.com/US/youtube-gaming-personality-desmond-etika-amofah-found-dead/story?id=63936521|archive-date=June 26, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Reactions==\nAmofah's death highlighted social media platforms' handling of posts by users who appear at risk with mental illness or who are contemplating suicide. YouTube, in removing Amofah's final video, stated that removal of such videos is standard practice to \"reduce the potential for copycat acts of self-harm, videos that express suicidal ideation\", and as part of this, sent the uploader information related to national suicide hotlines to provide help.<ref name=\"nytimes\">{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/06/26/style/etika-dead.html|title=Etika, a YouTube Personality, Is Mourned by Fans|first=Christine|last=Hauser|date=June 26, 2019|accessdate=June 26, 2019|work=[[The New York Times]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190626203942/https://www.nytimes.com/2019/06/26/style/etika-dead.html|archive-date=June 26, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nBecause of Amofah's activities in the months prior to his disappearance, some of his followers took these previous events as a humorous performance by Amofah rather than signs of him struggling with his mental health. Following his death, mental health researchers found several videos Amofah had posted that showed evidence of his troubled state but were taken as jokes by some of his viewers, rather than actual cries for help. As a result, some took Amofah's final video as yet another joke and disregarded any concern over his well-being; [[Keemstar]] initially thought Amofah's final video was a pre-meditated [[publicity stunt]], and stated after Amofah's death that \"I was never fully convinced that he was mentally ill or in trouble because of our private convos.\"<ref name=\"polygon mental health\"/> The aforementioned mental health researchers stressed the need to make more people on social media informed about the signs of mental illness, depression, and suicidal thoughts, so that they are able to recognize when people in a mindset similar to Amofah's are in danger and need support.<ref name=\"polygon mental health\">{{cite web | url = https://www.polygon.com/2019/7/2/20677759/etika-desmond-amofah-mental-health-illness-youtube | title = Too many people took Etika\u2019s mental health struggles as a joke | first = Patrick | last = Herandez | date = July 2, 2019 | accessdate = July 3, 2019 | work = [[Polygon (website)|Polygon]] | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20190702181147/https://www.polygon.com/2019/7/2/20677759/etika-desmond-amofah-mental-health-illness-youtube | archive-date = July 2, 2019 | url-status = live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url = https://www.theverge.com/2019/6/27/18759603/desmond-etika-amofah-death-youtube-creator-mental-health | title = YouTuber Etika\u2019s death spurs conversation about how viewers react to creators\u2019 mental health struggles | first = Julia | last = Alexander | date = June 27, 2019 | accessdate = July 3, 2019 | work = [[The Verge]] | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20190703173241/https://www.theverge.com/2019/6/27/18759603/desmond-etika-amofah-death-youtube-creator-mental-health | archive-date = July 3, 2019 | url-status = live }}</ref> Keemstar briefly became a target of some of Amofah's fans, who blamed him for Amofah's suicide due to the \"DramaAlert\" interview and statements made in tweets prior to and following the interview. Amofah's mother wrote to these fans to assure them that Keemstar was in no way responsible for Amofah's death, stating that \"Etika loved Keemstar's show\" and only wanted to make a memorable appearance on it.<ref name=\"dailydot keemstar\"/>\n\n==Legacy==\nFollowing Amofah's suicide, fans on Twitter and in emails asked that YouTube re-upload Amofah's final video to help memorialize him. A [[Change.org]] petition was started and initially garnered more than 380,000 signatures, but later dropped to 197,000 signatures after many fraudulent signatures from [[internet bot]]s were removed. It asked for Amofah's original channel to be restored to preserve his legacy.<ref name=\"the verge\" /><ref name=\"variety\">{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2019/digital/news/etika-desmond-amofah-youtube-found-dead-1203252700/|title=Gaming YouTuber Desmond 'Etika' Amofah Found Dead, NYPD Says|first=Todd|last=Spangler|date=June 25, 2019|accessdate=June 25, 2019|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190626181505/https://variety.com/2019/digital/news/etika-desmond-amofah-youtube-found-dead-1203252700/|archive-date=June 26, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"petition\" /> Another Change.org petition with over a million signatures, which later dropped to more than 200,000 signatures for similar reasons, called for Amofah to be buried at YouTube headquarters, which he stated as his wish during an earlier livestream.<ref>{{Cite web | url = https://metro.co.uk/2019/06/25/etika-wanted-buried-front-youtube-hq-police-confirm-gamers-death-10071622/ | title = Etika wanted to be buried in front of YouTube HQ as police confirm gamer\u2019s death | first = Mel | last = Evans | date = June 25, 2019 | accessdate = June 28, 2019 | work = [[Metro (British newspaper)|Metro]] | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20190628223006/https://metro.co.uk/2019/06/25/etika-wanted-buried-front-youtube-hq-police-confirm-gamers-death-10071622/ | archive-date = June 28, 2019 | url-status = live }}</ref>\n\nFans later erected a memorial on Amofah's behalf on the pedestrian walkway of the Manhattan Bridge, leaving letters, [[fan art]], [[Twizzlers]], Nintendo-related products and other [[memorabilia]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.insideedition.com/fans-create-memorial-gamer-etika-new-york-54046|title=Fans Create Memorial for Gamer Etika in New York|date=2019-06-28|website=Inside Edition|language=en-US|access-date=2019-07-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190701154631/https://www.insideedition.com/fans-create-memorial-gamer-etika-new-york-54046|archive-date=July 1, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn June 25, 2019, YouTuber Abe Hunter announced he was the owner and operator of Amofah's website<ref>{{cite tweet |user=pressabetostart|number=1143610944708386817 |date = 25 June 2019 |title=So, I was working on something for Etika a while back & because of that I still own http://etikaworldnetwork.com}}{{Self-published source|date=November 2019}}</ref> and converted it into a fundraiser site where 100% of the profits are donated to [[National Alliance on Mental Illness]] (NAMI) in Amofah's name.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://etikaworldnetwork.myshopify.com/|title=Etika World Network|website=etikaworldnetwork|language=en|access-date=2019-07-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190710174036/https://etikaworldnetwork.myshopify.com/|archive-date=July 10, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> On July 15, 2019 on behalf of the JOYCONBOYZ community; Abe Hunter donated the $11,315.25 raised to [[National Alliance on Mental Illness]] (NAMI) in memory of Amofah.<ref>{{cite tweet |user=namicommunicate |author-link=National Alliance on Mental Illness |number=1150816136751124480 |date=July 15, 2019 |title=Thank you to the #JOYCONBOYZ for their donation of $11,315.25 in memory of Desmond Amofah aka \"Etika\" from Abe of Blockhead Entertainment LLC. We appreciate your support!.}}</ref>\n\nOn July 21, 2019, YouTuber [[PewDiePie]] started a fundraiser on the [[crowdfunding]] website [[GoFundMe]] with American actor [[Jack Black]] for the [[National Alliance on Mental Illness]] (NAMI), due to the death of Amofah. PewDiePie and Black streamed themselves playing ''[[Minecraft]]'' together to raise money for their fundraiser. PewDiePie donated $10,000 to the fundraiser and raised over $30,000 for NAMI.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://metro.co.uk/2019/07/21/pewdiepie-donates-8000-content-creators-mental-health-charity-honour-etika-10436272/|title=PewDiePie donates \u00a38000 to mental health charity in honour of Etika|date=2019-07-21|website=Metro|language=en-US|access-date=2019-07-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190727155812/https://metro.co.uk/2019/07/21/pewdiepie-donates-8000-content-creators-mental-health-charity-honour-etika-10436272/|archive-date=July 27, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn August 13, 2019, an [[Indiegogo]] campaign was started on Etika's behalf. The Charity campaign was created to earn donations for [[The Jed Foundation]]. Contributors to the campaign received a custom made pair of Etika themed joy-cons, dubbed \"Etikons\" <ref>https://www.indiegogo.com/projects/etikons-custom-etika-themed-joy-cons-for-charity--2/x/22111641#/</ref>\n\nOn November 6, 2019, it was revealed that after raising the initial $11,315.25 for [[National Alliance on Mental Illness]] (NAMI),<ref>{{cite tweet |user=namicommunicate |author-link=National Alliance on Mental Illness |number=1150816136751124480 |date=July 15, 2019 |title=Thank you to the #JOYCONBOYZ for their donation of $11,315.25 in memory of Desmond Amofah aka \"Etika\" from Abe of Blockhead Entertainment LLC. We appreciate your support!.}}{{Self-published source|date=November 2019}}</ref> YouTubers Abe Hunter and Double-A worked with Mural Artist BK FOXX, Graffiti artist Kestaadm and JMZWalls to create a 40-feet long mural dedicated to Amofah in [[Bushwick, Brooklyn]].<ref>{{cite web | url = https://kotaku.com/fans-honor-deceased-youtuber-etika-with-a-stunning-mura-1839725766 | title = Fans Honor Deceased YouTuber Etika With A Stunning Mural | first = Cecelia | last = D'Anastasio | date = November 8, 2019 | accessdate = November 8, 2019 | work = [[Kotaku]] | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20191108215035/https://kotaku.com/fans-honor-deceased-youtuber-etika-with-a-stunning-mura-1839725766 | archive-date = November 8, 2019 | url-status = live }}</ref> The mural was created to celebrate Amofah's life and to help bring awareness to mental health. The mural's location was added as a virtual \"Pok\u00e9Stop\" in the augmented reality game ''[[Pok\u00e9mon Go]]'' in February 2020 after over 350,000 people requested Nintendo to add it in memory of Amofah.<ref>{{cite web | url = https://www.polygon.com/2020/2/25/21152509/pokemon-go-etika-desmond-amofah-joycon-boyz-mural-pokestop-memorial | title = Etika\u2019s face is now a Pok\u00e9mon Go stop, thanks to a YouTuber and his fans | first = Patricia | last = Hernandez | date = February 25, 2020 | accessdate = February 25, 2020 | work = [[Polygon (website)|Polygon]] }}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of solved missing persons cases]]\n*[[List of YouTubers]]\n\n==Notes==\n{{notelist}}\n{{Reflist|group=note}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category}}\n* {{IMDb name|8813048}}\n* {{YouTube|Etika|u=TR1Iceman}}\n{{Portal bar|Biography|New York City|Internet|Video games}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:1990 births]]\n[[Category:2019 deaths]]\n[[Category:2010s missing person cases]]\n[[Category:African-American male models]]\n[[Category:American people of Ghanaian descent]]\n[[Category:American YouTubers]]\n[[Category:Articles containing video clips]]\n[[Category:Deaths by drowning]]\n[[Category:Formerly missing people found dead]]\n[[Category:Gaming YouTubers]]\n[[Category:Internet memes]]\n[[Category:Internet-related controversies]]\n[[Category:Let's Players]]\n[[Category:Male models who committed suicide]]\n[[Category:Male suicides]]\n[[Category:Male YouTubers]]\n[[Category:Missing person cases in New York]]\n[[Category:Models from New York City]]\n[[Category:People from Brooklyn]]\n[[Category:Suicides by drowning in the United States]]\n[[Category:Suicides by jumping in New York City]]\n[[Category:Suicides in New York City]]\n[[Category:Twitch streamers]]\n[[Category:YouTube channels launched in 2012]]\n[[Category:YouTube channels closed in 2018]]\n[[Category:YouTube controversies]]\n", "name_user": "77.3.166.170", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(Fixed typo.)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Etika"}
{"title_page": "Dan Smith (footballer, born 1989)", "text_new": "{{EngvarB|date=July 2013}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2013}}\n{{infobox football biography\n| name        = Dan Smith\n| image       =\n| fullname    = Daniel Philip Smith\n| birth_date  = {{Birth date and age|1989|10|05|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Saltash]], England\n| height      = 5 ft 10 in\n| position    = [[Forward (association football)|Forward]]\n| currentclub = [[Truro City F.C.|Truro City]]\n| clubnumber  = \n| youthyears1 = 1999\u20132007 | youthclubs1 = [[Plymouth Argyle F.C.|Plymouth Argyle]]\n| years1 = 2007\u20132009 | clubs1 = [[Plymouth Argyle F.C.|Plymouth Argyle]]                | caps1 = 2  | goals1 = 0\n| years2 = 2008      | clubs2 = \u2192 [[Morecambe F.C.|Morecambe]] (loan)                   | caps2 = 2  | goals2 = 0\n| years3 = 2008\u20132009 | clubs3 = \u2192 [[Eastbourne Borough F.C.|Eastbourne Borough]] (loan) | caps3 = 13 | goals3 = 3\n| years4 = 2009\u20132010 | clubs4 = [[Eastbourne Borough F.C.|Eastbourne Borough]]          | caps4 = 15 | goals4 = 0\n| years5 = 2010      | clubs5 = [[Weymouth F.C.|Weymouth]]                              | caps5 =   | goals5 = \n| years6 = 2010\u20132012 | clubs6 = [[Truro City F.C.|Truro City]]                          | caps6 =   | goals6 = \n| years7 = 2012      | clubs7 = [[Bath City F.C.|Bath City]]                            | caps7 = 3  | goals7 = 0\n| years8 = 2012\u20132013     | clubs8 = [[Weymouth F.C.|Weymouth]]                              | caps8 =  37 | goals8 =  5\n| years9 = 2013\u20132014     | clubs9 = [[Tiverton Town F.C.|Tiverton Town]] | caps9 = 39 | goals9 =8\n| years10 = 2014\u20132015     | clubs10 = [[Dorchester Town F.C.|Dorchester Town]] | caps10 = 44 | goals10 = 8\n| years11 = 2015\u20132016 | clubs11 = [[Tiverton Town F.C.|Tiverton Town]] | caps11 = 39| goals11 = 4\n| years12 = 2016     | clubs12 = [[Weymouth F.C.|Weymouth]] | caps12 = 14| goals12 = 1\n| years13 = 2016\u2013     | clubs13 = [[Truro City F.C.|Truro City]]  | caps13 = 15  | goals13 =  1\n| club-update = 17:07, 13 October 2017 (UTC)\n}}\n\n'''Daniel Philip Smith''' (born 5 October 1989) is an English [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Forward (association football)|forward]] for [[Truro City F.C.|Truro City]]. He previously played for [[Plymouth Argyle F.C.|Plymouth Argyle]], [[Morecambe F.C.|Morecambe]], [[Eastbourne Borough F.C.|Eastbourne Borough]], [[Truro City F.C.|Truro City]],<ref>http://www.aylesburyunitedfc.co.uk/players/truro-city/dan-smith/9819/</ref> [[Bath City F.C.|Bath City]], [[Weymouth F.C.|Weymouth]] and [[Tiverton Town F.C.|Tiverton]].\n\n==Career==\nSmith began his career at [[Plymouth Argyle F.C.|Plymouth Argyle]]'s Centre of Excellence, having joined when he was a 9-year old. Smith made his [[first team]] debut for Argyle as a substitute in a [[Football League Championship]] match against [[Burnley FC|Burnley]] in January 2008.\n\nSmith also featured as a substitute in the final home game of the season against [[Blackpool F.C|Blackpool]] before signing a new one-year contract in May 2008.<ref>{{cite news | date=30 May 2008 | url=http://www.skysports.com/story/0,19528,11688_3628884,00.html | title=Smith Earns Pilgrims Contract | publisher=Skysports | accessdate=30 May 2008}}</ref> He joined [[Morecambe F.C.|Morecambe]] on an initial one-month loan on 9 September 2008 to gain first team experience.<ref>{{cite news | date=9 September 2008 | url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/m/morecambe/7606410.stm | title=Plymouth loan Smith to Morecambe | publisher=BBC Sport | accessdate=9 September 2008}}</ref> Smith made two appearances for the Shrimps before returning to Argyle at the beginning of October.\n\nWith first team chances limited, Smith joined [[Conference National]] side [[Eastbourne Borough F.C.|Eastbourne Borough]] on 27 November 2008 for a one-month loan along with teammate [[Ashley Barnes]].<ref>{{cite news | date=27 November 2008 | url=http://www.pafc.premiumtv.co.uk/page/NewsDetail/0,,10364~1468498,00.html | title=On The Way | publisher=pafc.co.uk | accessdate=27 November 2008 | url-status=dead | archiveurl=https://archive.is/20120805150108/http://www.pafc.premiumtv.co.uk/page/NewsDetail/0,,10364~1468498,00.html | archivedate=5 August 2012 | df=dmy-all }}</ref> The loan was extended by a further three months which lasted until the end of February 2009.<ref>{{cite news |date=2 January 2009 |url=http://www.eastbourneherald.co.uk/sport/Plymouth-duo-extend-stay.4838874.jp |title=Plymouth duo extend stay |publisher=Eastbourne Herald |accessdate=3 January 2009 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |date=5 January 2009 |url=http://www.pafc.co.uk/page/NewsDetail/0,,10364~1509471,00.html |title=Loan Extension |publisher=pafc.co.uk |accessdate=6 January 2009 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090430225040/http://www.pafc.co.uk/page/NewsDetail/0%2C%2C10364~1509471%2C00.html |archivedate=30 April 2009 |df=dmy-all }}</ref><ref name=\"Plymouth agree to extend Smith's loan deal\">{{cite news|title=Plymouth agree to extend Smith's loan deal |url=http://www.theargus.co.uk/sport/bluesquarepremier/eastbourneborough/4082902.Plymouth_agree_to_extend_Smith_s_loan_deal/ |publisher=The Argus |date=28 January 2009 |accessdate=28 January 2009 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120322021423/http://www.theargus.co.uk/sport/bluesquarepremier/eastbourneborough/4082902.Plymouth_agree_to_extend_Smith_s_loan_deal/ |archivedate=22 March 2012 }}</ref> Smith made an impact for the Eastbourne Borough team, along with teammate [[Ashley Barnes]], helped the team from balancing over the Conference National relegation zone to a comfortable mid table position with the scope of reaching the play-offs. In February 2009 when snow cut him off in Devon and took at flight to Manchester to join Eastbourne in an away game with Altrincham, a game that was called postponed two hours before kick off.{{Citation needed|date=February 2010}}\n\nSmith scored three goals out of 14 games whilst playing for Eastbourne before returning to [[Plymouth Argyle F.C.|Plymouth Argyle]] at the end of February 2009.<ref name=\"Smith keen to go out with a bang\">{{cite news\n| title = Smith keen to go out with a bang.\n| url = http://www.theargus.co.uk/sport/bluesquarepremier/eastbourneborough/4158875.Smith_keen_to_go_out_with_a_bang/\n| publisher = The Argus\n| date = 27 February 2009\n| accessdate = 10 March 2009}} {{Dead link|date=October 2010|bot=H3llBot}}</ref>\n\nSmith was released at the end of his contract and signed permanently for Eastbourne Borough on 15 May 2009.<ref name=\"Argyle star Smith makes Boro' switch\">{{cite news\n| title = Argyle star Smith makes Boro' switch\n| url = http://www.eastbourneherald.co.uk/sport/Argyle-star-Smith-makes-Boro39.5272678.jp\n| publisher = Eastbourne Herald\n| date = 15 May 2009\n| accessdate = 18 May 2009}}</ref> Smith stated that he jumped at the chance when Eastbourne were interested in signing him, despite other offers that were given to him. He believed that joining Eastbourne would kick-start his career again despite playing in [[non-League football]].<ref name=\"Boro signing warns his best is yet to come\">{{cite news\n| title = Boro signing warns his best is yet to come\n| url = http://www.theargus.co.uk/sport/bluesquarepremier/eastbourneborough/4373482.Boro_signing_warns_his_best_is_yet_to_come/\n| publisher = The Argus\n| date = 16 May 2009\n| accessdate = 18 May 2009}} {{Dead link|date=October 2010|bot=H3llBot}}</ref> In February 2010, Smith signed for [[Conference South]] side [[Weymouth F.C.|Weymouth]] until the end of the season. He joined [[Truro City F.C.|Truro City]] in July 2010 and helped the club win the [[Southern Football League|Southern League]] in his first season. He was released in January 2012 to try and gain a full-time contract elsewhere.<ref>{{cite web|title=Truro City release striker Dan Smith|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/16591938|work=BBC Sport|accessdate=21 March 2012|date=17 January 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Hodges prepares for tough battles|url=http://www.thisiscornwall.co.uk/Hodges-prepares-tough-battles/story-14975282-detail/story.html|archive-url=https://archive.is/20120915071146/http://www.thisiscornwall.co.uk/Hodges-prepares-tough-battles/story-14975282-detail/story.html|url-status=dead|archive-date=15 September 2012|accessdate=21 March 2012|newspaper=Western Morning News|date=19 January 2012}}</ref>\n\nTwo months later, Smith joined [[Bath City F.C.|Bath City]] on non-contract terms and made his debut the same day in a 1\u20130 defeat at [[Gateshead F.C.|Gateshead]].<ref>{{cite web|title=City Sign Midfielder Smith|url=http://bathcityfc.com/city-sign-midfielder-dan-smith/|publisher=Bath City F.C|accessdate=21 March 2012|date=20 March 2012}}{{Dead link|date=August 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Bath City manager Adie Britton sees potential in Dan Smith|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/17461553|work=BBC Sport|accessdate=21 March 2012|date=21 March 2012}}</ref>\n\nSmith signed for [[Southern Premier League]] side Weymouth in August 2012.<ref>{{cite news|title=Smith agrees to Terras' deal|url=http://www.dorsetecho.co.uk/sport/9857455.Smith_agrees_to_Terras____deal/|accessdate=19 August 2012|newspaper=Dorset Echo|date=6 August 2012}}</ref>\n\nHe joined Dorchester Town on 5 July 2014\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Portal|Cornwall}}\n*{{Soccerbase}}\n*{{FootballDatabase.eu|27785}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Smith, Dan}}\n[[Category:1989 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Saltash]]\n[[Category:Footballers from Cornwall]]\n[[Category:English footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football forwards]]\n[[Category:Plymouth Argyle F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Morecambe F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Eastbourne Borough F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Weymouth F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Truro City F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Tiverton Town F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Bath City F.C. players]]\n[[Category:English Football League players]]\n[[Category:National League (English football) players]]\n", "text_old": "{{EngvarB|date=July 2013}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2013}}\n{{infobox football biography\n| name        = Dan Smith\n| image       =\n| fullname    = Daniel Philip Smith\n| birth_date  = {{Birth date and age|1989|10|05|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Saltash]], England\n| height      = 5 ft 10 in\n| position    = [[Forward (association football)|Forward]]\n| currentclub = [[Truro City F.C.|Truro City]]\n| clubnumber  = \n| youthyears1 = 1999\u20132007 | youthclubs1 = [[Plymouth Argyle F.C.|Plymouth Argyle]]\n| years1 = 2007\u20132009 | clubs1 = [[Plymouth Argyle F.C.|Plymouth Argyle]]                | caps1 = 2  | goals1 = 0\n| years2 = 2008      | clubs2 = \u2192 [[Morecambe F.C.|Morecambe]] (loan)                   | caps2 = 2  | goals2 = 0\n| years3 = 2008\u20132009 | clubs3 = \u2192 [[Eastbourne Borough F.C.|Eastbourne Borough]] (loan) | caps3 = 13 | goals3 = 3\n| years4 = 2009\u20132010 | clubs4 = [[Eastbourne Borough F.C.|Eastbourne Borough]]          | caps4 = 15 | goals4 = 0\n| years5 = 2010      | clubs5 = [[Weymouth F.C.|Weymouth]]                              | caps5 =   | goals5 = \n| years6 = 2010\u20132012 | clubs6 = [[Truro City F.C.|Truro City]]                          | caps6 =   | goals6 = \n| years7 = 2012      | clubs7 = [[Bath City F.C.|Bath City]]                            | caps7 = 3  | goals7 = 0\n| years8 = 2012\u20132013     | clubs8 = [[Weymouth F.C.|Weymouth]]                              | caps8 =  37 | goals8 =  5\n| years9 = 2013\u20132014     | clubs9 = [[Tiverton Town F.C.|Tiverton Town]] | caps9 = 39 | goals9 =8\n| years10 = 2014\u20132015     | clubs10 = [[Dorchester Town F.C.|Dorchester Town]] | caps10 = 44 | goals10 = 8\n| years11 = 2015\u20132016 | clubs11 = [[Tiverton Town F.C.|Tiverton Town]] | caps11 = 39| goals11 = 4\n| years12 = 2016     | clubs12 = [[Weymouth F.C.|Weymouth]] | caps12 = 14| goals12 = 1\n| years13 = 2016\u2013     | clubs13 = [[Truro City F.C.|Truro City]]  | caps13 = 15  | goals13 =  1\n| club-update = 17:07, 13 October 2017 (UTC)\n}}\n\n'''Daniel Philip Smith''' (born 5 October 1989) is an English [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Forward (association football)|forward]] for [[Truro City F.C.|Truro City]]. He previously played for [[Plymouth Argyle F.C.|Plymouth Argyle]], [[Morecambe F.C.|Morecambe]], [[Eastbourne Borough F.C.|Eastbourne Borough]], [[Truro City F.C.|Truro City]],<ref>http://www.aylesburyunitedfc.co.uk/players/truro-city/dan-smith/9819/</ref> [[Bath City F.C.|Bath City]], [[Weymouth F.C.|Weymouth]] and [[Tiverton Town F.C.|Tiverton]].\n\n==Career==\nSmith began his career at [[Plymouth Argyle F.C.|Plymouth Argyle]]'s Centre of Excellence, having joined when he was a 9-year old. Smith made his [[first team]] debut for Argyle as a substitute in a [[Football League Championship]] match against [[Burnley FC|Burnley]] in January 2008.\n\nSmith also featured as a substitute in the final home game of the season against [[Blackpool F.C|Blackpool]] before signing a new one-year contract in May 2008.<ref>{{cite news | date=30 May 2008 | url=http://www.skysports.com/story/0,19528,11688_3628884,00.html | title=Smith Earns Pilgrims Contract | publisher=Skysports | accessdate=30 May 2008}}</ref> He joined [[Morecambe F.C.|Morecambe]] on an initial one-month loan on 9 September 2008 to gain first team experience.<ref>{{cite news | date=9 September 2008 | url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/m/morecambe/7606410.stm | title=Plymouth loan Smith to Morecambe | publisher=BBC Sport | accessdate=9 September 2008}}</ref> Smith made two appearances for the Shrimps before returning to Argyle at the beginning of October.\n\nWith first team chances limited, Smith joined [[Conference National]] side [[Eastbourne Borough F.C.|Eastbourne Borough]] on 27 November 2008 for a one-month loan along with teammate [[Ashley Barnes]].<ref>{{cite news | date=27 November 2008 | url=http://www.pafc.premiumtv.co.uk/page/NewsDetail/0,,10364~1468498,00.html | title=On The Way | publisher=pafc.co.uk | accessdate=27 November 2008 | url-status=dead | archiveurl=https://archive.is/20120805150108/http://www.pafc.premiumtv.co.uk/page/NewsDetail/0,,10364~1468498,00.html | archivedate=5 August 2012 | df=dmy-all }}</ref> The loan was extended by a further three months which lasted until the end of February 2009.<ref>{{cite news |date=2 January 2009 |url=http://www.eastbourneherald.co.uk/sport/Plymouth-duo-extend-stay.4838874.jp |title=Plymouth duo extend stay |publisher=Eastbourne Herald |accessdate=3 January 2009 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |date=5 January 2009 |url=http://www.pafc.co.uk/page/NewsDetail/0,,10364~1509471,00.html |title=Loan Extension |publisher=pafc.co.uk |accessdate=6 January 2009 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090430225040/http://www.pafc.co.uk/page/NewsDetail/0%2C%2C10364~1509471%2C00.html |archivedate=30 April 2009 |df=dmy-all }}</ref><ref name=\"Plymouth agree to extend Smith's loan deal\">{{cite news|title=Plymouth agree to extend Smith's loan deal |url=http://www.theargus.co.uk/sport/bluesquarepremier/eastbourneborough/4082902.Plymouth_agree_to_extend_Smith_s_loan_deal/ |publisher=The Argus |date=28 January 2009 |accessdate=28 January 2009 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120322021423/http://www.theargus.co.uk/sport/bluesquarepremier/eastbourneborough/4082902.Plymouth_agree_to_extend_Smith_s_loan_deal/ |archivedate=22 March 2012 }}</ref> Smith made an impact for the Eastbourne Borough team, along with teammate [[Ashley Barnes]], helped the team from balancing over the Conference National relegation zone to a comfortable mid table position with the scope of reaching the play-offs. In February 2009 when snow cut him off in Devon and took at flight to Manchester to join Eastbourne in an away game with Altrincham, a game that was called postponed two hours before kick off.{{Citation needed|date=February 2010}}\n\nSmith scored three goals out of 14 games whilst playing for Eastbourne before returning to [[Plymouth Argyle F.C.|Plymouth Argyle]] at the end of February 2009.<ref name=\"Smith keen to go out with a bang\">{{cite news\n| title = Smith keen to go out with a bang.\n| url = http://www.theargus.co.uk/sport/bluesquarepremier/eastbourneborough/4158875.Smith_keen_to_go_out_with_a_bang/\n| publisher = The Argus\n| date = 27 February 2009\n| accessdate = 10 March 2009}} {{Dead link|date=October 2010|bot=H3llBot}}</ref>\n\nSmith was released at the end of his contract and signed permanently for Eastbourne Borough on 15 May 2009.<ref name=\"Argyle star Smith makes Boro' switch\">{{cite news\n| title = Argyle star Smith makes Boro' switch\n| url = http://www.eastbourneherald.co.uk/sport/Argyle-star-Smith-makes-Boro39.5272678.jp\n| publisher = Eastbourne Herald\n| date = 15 May 2009\n| accessdate = 18 May 2009}}</ref> Smith stated that he jumped at the chance when Eastbourne were interested in signing him, despite other offers that were given to him. He believed that joining Eastbourne would kick-start his career again despite playing in [[non-League football]].<ref name=\"Boro signing warns his best is yet to come\">{{cite news\n| title = Boro signing warns his best is yet to come\n| url = http://www.theargus.co.uk/sport/bluesquarepremier/eastbourneborough/4373482.Boro_signing_warns_his_best_is_yet_to_come/\n| publisher = The Argus\n| date = 16 May 2009\n| accessdate = 18 May 2009}} {{Dead link|date=October 2010|bot=H3llBot}}</ref> In February 2010, Smith signed for [[Conference South]] side [[Weymouth F.C.|Weymouth]] until the end of the season. He joined [[Truro City F.C.|Truro City]] in July 2010 and helped the club win the [[Southern Football League|Southern League]] in his first season. He was released in January 2012 to try and gain a full-time contract elsewhere.<ref>{{cite web|title=Truro City release striker Dan Smith|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/16591938|work=BBC Sport|accessdate=21 March 2012|date=17 January 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Hodges prepares for tough battles|url=http://www.thisiscornwall.co.uk/Hodges-prepares-tough-battles/story-14975282-detail/story.html|archive-url=https://archive.is/20120915071146/http://www.thisiscornwall.co.uk/Hodges-prepares-tough-battles/story-14975282-detail/story.html|url-status=dead|archive-date=15 September 2012|accessdate=21 March 2012|newspaper=Western Morning News|date=19 January 2012}}</ref>\n\nTwo months later, Smith joined [[Bath City F.C.|Bath City]] on non-contract terms and made his debut the same day in a 1\u20130 defeat at [[Gateshead F.C.|Gateshead]].<ref>{{cite web|title=City Sign Midfielder Smith|url=http://bathcityfc.com/city-sign-midfielder-dan-smith/|publisher=Bath City F.C|accessdate=21 March 2012|date=20 March 2012}}{{Dead link|date=August 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Bath City manager Adie Britton sees potential in Dan Smith|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/17461553|work=BBC Sport|accessdate=21 March 2012|date=21 March 2012}}</ref>\n\nSmith signed for [[Southern Premier League]] side Weymouth in August 2012.<ref>{{cite news|title=Smith agrees to Terras' deal|url=http://www.dorsetecho.co.uk/sport/9857455.Smith_agrees_to_Terras____deal/|accessdate=19 August 2012|newspaper=Dorset Echo|date=6 August 2012}}</ref>\n\nHe joined Dorchester Town on 5 July 2014\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Soccerbase}}\n*{{FootballDatabase.eu|27785}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Smith, Dan}}\n[[Category:1989 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Saltash]]\n[[Category:Footballers from Cornwall]]\n[[Category:English footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football forwards]]\n[[Category:Plymouth Argyle F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Morecambe F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Eastbourne Borough F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Weymouth F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Truro City F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Tiverton Town F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Bath City F.C. players]]\n[[Category:English Football League players]]\n[[Category:National League (English football) players]]\n", "name_user": "Gazamp", "label": "safe", "comment": "AddedPortal:Cornwall", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dan_Smith_(footballer,_born_1989)"}
{"title_page": "Surface area", "text_new": "{{pp-pc1|small=yes}}\n{{short description|Measure of the two-dimensional extent of a surface}}\n[[Image:Sphere wireframe 10deg 6r.svg|right|thumb|A [[sphere]] of radius <math>r</math> has surface area <math>4\\pi r^2</math>]]\nThe '''surface area''' of a [[Solid geometry|solid]] object is a measure of the total [[area]] that the [[Surface (mathematics)|surface]] of the object occupies.<ref>{{MathWorld|title=Surface Area|urlname=SurfaceArea}}</ref> The mathematical definition of surface area in the presence of curved surfaces is considerably more involved than the definition of [[arc length]] of one-dimensional curves, or of the surface area for [[polyhedra]] (i.e., objects with flat polygonal [[Face (geometry)|faces]]), for which the surface area is the sum of the areas of its faces. Smooth surfaces, such as a [[sphere]], are assigned surface area using their representation as [[parametric surface]]s. This definition of surface area is based on methods of [[infinitesimal]] [[calculus]] and involves [[partial derivative]]s and [[double integration]].\n\nA general definition of surface area was sought by [[Henri Lebesgue]] and [[Hermann Minkowski]] at the turn of the twentieth century. Their work led to the development of [[geometric measure theory]], which studies various notions of surface area for irregular objects of any dimension. An important example is the [[Minkowski content]] of a surface.\n\n==Noah gay n==\nWhile the areas of many simple surfaces have been known since antiquity, a rigorous mathematical ''definition'' of area requires a great deal of care.\nThis should provide a function\n\n: <math> S \\mapsto A(S) </math>\n\nwhich assigns a positive [[real number]] to a certain class of [[Surface (topology)|surface]]s that satisfies several natural requirements. The most fundamental property of the surface area is its '''additivity''': ''the area of the whole is the sum of the areas of the parts''. More rigorously, if a surface ''S'' is a union of finitely many pieces ''S''<sub>1</sub>, \u2026, ''S''<sub>''r''</sub> which do not overlap except at their boundaries, then \n: <math> A(S) = A(S_1) + \\cdots + A(S_r). </math>\n\nSurface areas of flat polygonal shapes must agree with their geometrically defined [[area]]. Since surface area is a geometric notion, areas of [[congruence (geometry)|congruent]] surfaces must be the same and the area must depend only on the shape of the surface, but not on its position and orientation in space. This means that surface area is invariant under the [[Euclidean group|group of Euclidean motions]]. These properties uniquely characterize surface area for a wide class of geometric surfaces called ''piecewise smooth''. Such surfaces consist of finitely many pieces that can be represented in the [[parametric surface|parametric form]]\n\n: <math> S_D: \\vec{r}=\\vec{r}(u,v), \\quad (u,v)\\in D </math>\n\nwith a [[continuously differentiable]] function <math>\\vec{r}.</math> The area of an individual piece is defined by the formula\n\n: <math> A(S_D) = \\iint_D\\left |\\vec{r}_u\\times\\vec{r}_v\\right | \\, du \\, dv. </math>\n\nThus the area of ''S''<sub>''D''</sub> is obtained by integrating the length of the normal vector <math>\\vec{r}_u\\times\\vec{r}_v</math> to the surface over the appropriate region ''D'' in the parametric ''uv'' plane. The area of the whole surface is then obtained by adding together the areas of the pieces, using additivity of surface area. The main formula can be specialized to different classes of surfaces, giving, in particular, formulas for areas of graphs ''z'' = ''f''(''x'',''y'') and [[surface of revolution|surfaces of revolution]].\n\n[[File:Schwarz-lantern.gif|thumb|[[Schwarz lantern]] with <math>M</math> axial slices and <math>N</math> radial vertices. The limit of the area as <math>M</math> and <math>N</math> tend to infinity doesn't converge. In particular it doesn't converge to the area of the cylinder.]]One of the subtleties of surface area, as compared to [[arc length]] of curves, is that surface area cannot be defined simply as the limit of areas of polyhedral shapes approximating a given smooth surface. It was demonstrated by [[Hermann Schwarz]] that already for the cylinder, different choices of approximating flat surfaces can lead to different limiting values of the area; this example is known as the [[Schwarz lantern]].<ref name=sch1>{{cite web|url=http://fredrickey.info/hm/CalcNotes/schwarz-paradox.pdf|title=Schwarz's Paradox|publisher=|date=|access-date=2017-03-21|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304073957/http://fredrickey.info/hm/CalcNotes/schwarz-paradox.pdf|archive-date=2016-03-04|df=}}</ref><ref name=sch2>{{cite web |url=http://mathdl.maa.org/images/upload_library/22/Polya/00494925.di020678.02p0385w.pdf |title=Archived copy |access-date=2012-07-24 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111215152255/http://mathdl.maa.org/images/upload_library/22/Polya/00494925.di020678.02p0385w.pdf |archive-date=2011-12-15 |df= }}</ref>\n\nVarious approaches to a general definition of surface area were developed in the late nineteenth and the early twentieth century by [[Henri Lebesgue]] and [[Hermann Minkowski]]. While for piecewise smooth surfaces there is a unique natural notion of surface area, if a surface is very irregular, or rough, then it may not be possible to assign an area to it at all. A typical example is given by a surface with spikes spread throughout in a dense fashion. Many surfaces of this type occur in the study of [[fractal]]s. Extensions of the notion of area which partially fulfill its function and may be defined even for very badly irregular surfaces are studied in [[geometric measure theory]]. A specific example of such an extension is the [[Minkowski content]] of the surface.\n\n== Common formulas ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+ Surface areas of common solids\n|-\n!Shape\n!Equation\n!Variables\n|-\n|[[Cube]]\n|<math> 6s^2 \\, </math>\n|''s'' = side length\n|-\n|[[Cuboid]]\n|<math> 2(\\ell w + \\ell h + wh) \\, </math>\n|''\u2113'' = length, ''w'' = width, ''h'' = height\n|-\n|[[Triangular prism]]\n|<math> bh + l(a + b + c) </math>\n|''b'' = base length of triangle, ''h'' = height of triangle, ''l'' = distance between triangular bases, ''a'', ''b'', ''c'' = sides of triangle\n|-\n|All [[Prism (geometry)|prisms]]\n|<math> 2B + Ph \\, </math>\n|''B'' = the area of one base, ''P'' = the perimeter of one base, ''h'' = height\n|-\n|[[Sphere]]\n|<math> 4\\pi r^2 = \\pi d^2\\, </math>\n|''r'' = radius of sphere, ''d'' = diameter\n|-\n|[[Spherical lune]]\n|<math> 2r^2\\theta \\, </math>\n|''r'' = radius of sphere, ''\u03b8'' = [[dihedral angle]]\n|-\n|[[Torus]]\n|<math> (2\\pi r)(2\\pi R) = 4\\pi^2 Rr</math>\n|''r'' = minor radius (radius of the tube), ''R'' = major radius (distance from center of tube to center of torus)\n|-\n|Closed [[Cylinder (geometry)|cylinder]]\n|<math> 2\\pi r^2 + 2\\pi rh = 2\\pi r(r+h) \\, </math>\n|''r'' = radius of the circular base, ''h'' = height of the cylinder\n|-\n|Lateral surface area of a [[cone (geometry)|cone]]\n|<math> \\pi r \\left(\\sqrt{r^2+h^2}\\right) = \\pi rs \\, </math>\n|<math> s = \\sqrt{r^2+h^2} </math><br/>\n''s'' = slant height of the cone,<br/>\n''r'' = radius of the circular base,<br/>\n''h'' = height of the cone\n|-\n|Full surface area of a cone\n|<math> \\pi r \\left(r + \\sqrt{r^2+h^2}\\right) = \\pi r(r + s) \\, </math>\n| ''s'' = slant height of the cone,<br/>\n''r'' = radius of the circular base,<br/>\n''h'' = height of the cone\n|-\n|[[Pyramid (geometry)|Pyramid]]\n|<math>B + \\frac{PL}{2}</math>\n|''B'' = area of base, ''P'' = perimeter of base, ''L'' = slant height\n|-\n|[[Square pyramid]]\n|<math> b^2 + 2bs = b^2 + 2b\\sqrt{\\left(\\frac{b}{2}\\right)^2+h^2} </math>\n|''b'' = base length, ''s'' = slant height, ''h'' = vertical height\n|-\n|Rectangular pyramid\n|<math> lw + l\\sqrt{\\left(\\frac{w}{2}\\right)^2+h^2} + w\\sqrt{\\left(\\frac{l}{2}\\right)^2+h^2} </math>\n|''\u2113'' = length, ''w'' = width, ''h'' = height\n|-\n|[[Tetrahedron]]\n|<math> \\sqrt{3}a^2 </math>\n|''a'' = side length\n|}\n\n===Ratio of surface areas of a sphere and cylinder of the same radius and height===\n[[Image:Inscribed cone sphere cylinder.svg|thumb|300px|A cone, sphere and cylinder of radius ''r'' and height ''h''.]]\nThe below given formulas can be used to show that the surface area of a [[sphere]] and [[cylinder (geometry)|cylinder]] of the same radius and height are in the ratio '''2&nbsp;:&nbsp;3''', as follows.\n\nLet the radius be ''r'' and the height be ''h'' (which is 2''r'' for the sphere).\n\n<math>\\begin{array}{rlll}\n\\text{Sphere surface area}   & = 4 \\pi r^2      &                    & = (2 \\pi r^2) \\times 2 \\\\\n\\text{Cylinder surface area} & = 2 \\pi r (h + r) & = 2 \\pi r (2r + r) & = (2 \\pi r^2) \\times 3\n\\end{array}</math>\n\nThe discovery of this ratio is credited to [[Archimedes]].<ref>{{cite web|first = Chris|last = Rorres|url = http://www.math.nyu.edu/~crorres/Archimedes/Tomb/Cicero.html|title = Tomb of Archimedes: Sources|publisher = Courant Institute of Mathematical Sciences|access-date = 2007-01-02|url-status = live|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20061209201723/http://www.math.nyu.edu/~crorres/Archimedes/Tomb/Cicero.html|archive-date = 2006-12-09|df = }}</ref>\n{{Clear}}\n\n== In chemistry ==\n[[File:Surface area.svg|thumb|Surface area of particles of different sizes.]]\n{{see also|Accessible surface area}}\nSurface area is important in [[chemical kinetics]]. Increasing the surface area of a substance generally increases the [[reaction rate|rate]] of a [[chemical reaction]].  For example, [[iron]] in a fine powder will [[combustion|combust]], while in solid blocks it is stable enough to use in structures. For different applications a minimal or maximal surface area may be desired.\n{{Clear}}\n\n== In biology ==\n{{see also|Surface-area-to-volume ratio}}\n[[Image:Mitochondrion 186.jpg|right|thumb|The inner membrane of the [[mitochondrion]] has a large surface area due to infoldings, allowing higher rates of [[cellular respiration]] (electron [[micrograph]]).]]\nThe surface area of an organism is important in several considerations, such as regulation of body temperature and [[digestion]]. Animals use their [[teeth]] to grind food down into smaller particles, increasing the surface area available for digestion. The epithelial tissue lining the digestive tract contains [[microvilli]], greatly increasing the area available for absorption. [[Elephant]]s have large [[ear]]s, allowing them to regulate their own body temperature. In other instances, animals will need to minimize surface area; for example, people will fold their arms over their chest when cold to minimize heat loss.\n\nThe [[surface area to volume ratio]] (SA:V) of a [[cell (biology)|cell]] imposes upper limits on size, as the volume increases much faster than does the surface area, thus limiting the rate at which substances diffuse from the interior across the [[cell membrane]] to interstitial spaces or to other cells. Indeed, representing a cell as an idealized [[sphere]] of radius ''r'', the volume and surface area are, respectively, ''V'' = 4/3 \u03c0 ''r''<sup>3</sup>; ''SA'' = 4 \u03c0 ''r''<sup>2</sup>. The resulting surface area to volume ratio is therefore 3/''r''. Thus, if a cell has a radius of 1 \u03bcm, the SA:V ratio is 3; whereas if the radius of the cell is instead 10 \u03bcm, then the SA:V ratio becomes 0.3. With a cell radius of 100, SA:V ratio is 0.03. Thus, the surface area falls off steeply with increasing volume.\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Perimeter length]]\n* [[BET theory]], technique for the measurement of the specific surface area of materials\n* [[Spherical area]]\n* [[Surface integral]]\n\n== References ==\n\n<references />\n\n* {{eom|title=Area|id=A/a013180|author=Yu.D. Burago, V.A. Zalgaller, L.D. Kudryavtsev}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://blog.thinkwell.com/2010/07/6th-grade-math-surface-area.html Surface Area Video] at Thinkwell\n\n[[Category:Area]]\n", "text_old": "{{pp-pc1|small=yes}}\n{{short description|Measure of the two-dimensional extent of a surface}}\n[[Image:Sphere wireframe 10deg 6r.svg|right|thumb|A [[sphere]] of radius <math>r</math> has surface area <math>4\\pi r^2</math>]]\nThe '''surface area''' of a [[Solid geometry|solid]] object is a measure of the total [[area]] that the [[Surface (mathematics)|surface]] of the object occupies.<ref>{{MathWorld|title=Surface Area|urlname=SurfaceArea}}</ref> The mathematical definition of surface area in the presence of curved surfaces is considerably more involved than the definition of [[arc length]] of one-dimensional curves, or of the surface area for [[polyhedra]] (i.e., objects with flat polygonal [[Face (geometry)|faces]]), for which the surface area is the sum of the areas of its faces. Smooth surfaces, such as a [[sphere]], are assigned surface area using their representation as [[parametric surface]]s. This definition of surface area is based on methods of [[infinitesimal]] [[calculus]] and involves [[partial derivative]]s and [[double integration]].\n\nA general definition of surface area was sought by [[Henri Lebesgue]] and [[Hermann Minkowski]] at the turn of the twentieth century. Their work led to the development of [[geometric measure theory]], which studies various notions of surface area for irregular objects of any dimension. An important example is the [[Minkowski content]] of a surface.\n\n==Definition==\nWhile the areas of many simple surfaces have been known since antiquity, a rigorous mathematical ''definition'' of area requires a great deal of care.\nThis should provide a function\n\n: <math> S \\mapsto A(S) </math>\n\nwhich assigns a positive [[real number]] to a certain class of [[Surface (topology)|surface]]s that satisfies several natural requirements. The most fundamental property of the surface area is its '''additivity''': ''the area of the whole is the sum of the areas of the parts''. More rigorously, if a surface ''S'' is a union of finitely many pieces ''S''<sub>1</sub>, \u2026, ''S''<sub>''r''</sub> which do not overlap except at their boundaries, then \n: <math> A(S) = A(S_1) + \\cdots + A(S_r). </math>\n\nSurface areas of flat polygonal shapes must agree with their geometrically defined [[area]]. Since surface area is a geometric notion, areas of [[congruence (geometry)|congruent]] surfaces must be the same and the area must depend only on the shape of the surface, but not on its position and orientation in space. This means that surface area is invariant under the [[Euclidean group|group of Euclidean motions]]. These properties uniquely characterize surface area for a wide class of geometric surfaces called ''piecewise smooth''. Such surfaces consist of finitely many pieces that can be represented in the [[parametric surface|parametric form]]\n\n: <math> S_D: \\vec{r}=\\vec{r}(u,v), \\quad (u,v)\\in D </math>\n\nwith a [[continuously differentiable]] function <math>\\vec{r}.</math> The area of an individual piece is defined by the formula\n\n: <math> A(S_D) = \\iint_D\\left |\\vec{r}_u\\times\\vec{r}_v\\right | \\, du \\, dv. </math>\n\nThus the area of ''S''<sub>''D''</sub> is obtained by integrating the length of the normal vector <math>\\vec{r}_u\\times\\vec{r}_v</math> to the surface over the appropriate region ''D'' in the parametric ''uv'' plane. The area of the whole surface is then obtained by adding together the areas of the pieces, using additivity of surface area. The main formula can be specialized to different classes of surfaces, giving, in particular, formulas for areas of graphs ''z'' = ''f''(''x'',''y'') and [[surface of revolution|surfaces of revolution]].\n\n[[File:Schwarz-lantern.gif|thumb|[[Schwarz lantern]] with <math>M</math> axial slices and <math>N</math> radial vertices. The limit of the area as <math>M</math> and <math>N</math> tend to infinity doesn't converge. In particular it doesn't converge to the area of the cylinder.]]One of the subtleties of surface area, as compared to [[arc length]] of curves, is that surface area cannot be defined simply as the limit of areas of polyhedral shapes approximating a given smooth surface. It was demonstrated by [[Hermann Schwarz]] that already for the cylinder, different choices of approximating flat surfaces can lead to different limiting values of the area; this example is known as the [[Schwarz lantern]].<ref name=sch1>{{cite web|url=http://fredrickey.info/hm/CalcNotes/schwarz-paradox.pdf|title=Schwarz's Paradox|publisher=|date=|access-date=2017-03-21|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304073957/http://fredrickey.info/hm/CalcNotes/schwarz-paradox.pdf|archive-date=2016-03-04|df=}}</ref><ref name=sch2>{{cite web |url=http://mathdl.maa.org/images/upload_library/22/Polya/00494925.di020678.02p0385w.pdf |title=Archived copy |access-date=2012-07-24 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111215152255/http://mathdl.maa.org/images/upload_library/22/Polya/00494925.di020678.02p0385w.pdf |archive-date=2011-12-15 |df= }}</ref>\n\nVarious approaches to a general definition of surface area were developed in the late nineteenth and the early twentieth century by [[Henri Lebesgue]] and [[Hermann Minkowski]]. While for piecewise smooth surfaces there is a unique natural notion of surface area, if a surface is very irregular, or rough, then it may not be possible to assign an area to it at all. A typical example is given by a surface with spikes spread throughout in a dense fashion. Many surfaces of this type occur in the study of [[fractal]]s. Extensions of the notion of area which partially fulfill its function and may be defined even for very badly irregular surfaces are studied in [[geometric measure theory]]. A specific example of such an extension is the [[Minkowski content]] of the surface.\n\n== Common formulas ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+ Surface areas of common solids\n|-\n!Shape\n!Equation\n!Variables\n|-\n|[[Cube]]\n|<math> 6s^2 \\, </math>\n|''s'' = side length\n|-\n|[[Cuboid]]\n|<math> 2(\\ell w + \\ell h + wh) \\, </math>\n|''\u2113'' = length, ''w'' = width, ''h'' = height\n|-\n|[[Triangular prism]]\n|<math> bh + l(a + b + c) </math>\n|''b'' = base length of triangle, ''h'' = height of triangle, ''l'' = distance between triangular bases, ''a'', ''b'', ''c'' = sides of triangle\n|-\n|All [[Prism (geometry)|prisms]]\n|<math> 2B + Ph \\, </math>\n|''B'' = the area of one base, ''P'' = the perimeter of one base, ''h'' = height\n|-\n|[[Sphere]]\n|<math> 4\\pi r^2 = \\pi d^2\\, </math>\n|''r'' = radius of sphere, ''d'' = diameter\n|-\n|[[Spherical lune]]\n|<math> 2r^2\\theta \\, </math>\n|''r'' = radius of sphere, ''\u03b8'' = [[dihedral angle]]\n|-\n|[[Torus]]\n|<math> (2\\pi r)(2\\pi R) = 4\\pi^2 Rr</math>\n|''r'' = minor radius (radius of the tube), ''R'' = major radius (distance from center of tube to center of torus)\n|-\n|Closed [[Cylinder (geometry)|cylinder]]\n|<math> 2\\pi r^2 + 2\\pi rh = 2\\pi r(r+h) \\, </math>\n|''r'' = radius of the circular base, ''h'' = height of the cylinder\n|-\n|Lateral surface area of a [[cone (geometry)|cone]]\n|<math> \\pi r \\left(\\sqrt{r^2+h^2}\\right) = \\pi rs \\, </math>\n|<math> s = \\sqrt{r^2+h^2} </math><br/>\n''s'' = slant height of the cone,<br/>\n''r'' = radius of the circular base,<br/>\n''h'' = height of the cone\n|-\n|Full surface area of a cone\n|<math> \\pi r \\left(r + \\sqrt{r^2+h^2}\\right) = \\pi r(r + s) \\, </math>\n| ''s'' = slant height of the cone,<br/>\n''r'' = radius of the circular base,<br/>\n''h'' = height of the cone\n|-\n|[[Pyramid (geometry)|Pyramid]]\n|<math>B + \\frac{PL}{2}</math>\n|''B'' = area of base, ''P'' = perimeter of base, ''L'' = slant height\n|-\n|[[Square pyramid]]\n|<math> b^2 + 2bs = b^2 + 2b\\sqrt{\\left(\\frac{b}{2}\\right)^2+h^2} </math>\n|''b'' = base length, ''s'' = slant height, ''h'' = vertical height\n|-\n|Rectangular pyramid\n|<math> lw + l\\sqrt{\\left(\\frac{w}{2}\\right)^2+h^2} + w\\sqrt{\\left(\\frac{l}{2}\\right)^2+h^2} </math>\n|''\u2113'' = length, ''w'' = width, ''h'' = height\n|-\n|[[Tetrahedron]]\n|<math> \\sqrt{3}a^2 </math>\n|''a'' = side length\n|}\n\n===Ratio of surface areas of a sphere and cylinder of the same radius and height===\n[[Image:Inscribed cone sphere cylinder.svg|thumb|300px|A cone, sphere and cylinder of radius ''r'' and height ''h''.]]\nThe below given formulas can be used to show that the surface area of a [[sphere]] and [[cylinder (geometry)|cylinder]] of the same radius and height are in the ratio '''2&nbsp;:&nbsp;3''', as follows.\n\nLet the radius be ''r'' and the height be ''h'' (which is 2''r'' for the sphere).\n\n<math>\\begin{array}{rlll}\n\\text{Sphere surface area}   & = 4 \\pi r^2      &                    & = (2 \\pi r^2) \\times 2 \\\\\n\\text{Cylinder surface area} & = 2 \\pi r (h + r) & = 2 \\pi r (2r + r) & = (2 \\pi r^2) \\times 3\n\\end{array}</math>\n\nThe discovery of this ratio is credited to [[Archimedes]].<ref>{{cite web|first = Chris|last = Rorres|url = http://www.math.nyu.edu/~crorres/Archimedes/Tomb/Cicero.html|title = Tomb of Archimedes: Sources|publisher = Courant Institute of Mathematical Sciences|access-date = 2007-01-02|url-status = live|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20061209201723/http://www.math.nyu.edu/~crorres/Archimedes/Tomb/Cicero.html|archive-date = 2006-12-09|df = }}</ref>\n{{Clear}}\n\n== In chemistry ==\n[[File:Surface area.svg|thumb|Surface area of particles of different sizes.]]\n{{see also|Accessible surface area}}\nSurface area is important in [[chemical kinetics]]. Increasing the surface area of a substance generally increases the [[reaction rate|rate]] of a [[chemical reaction]].  For example, [[iron]] in a fine powder will [[combustion|combust]], while in solid blocks it is stable enough to use in structures. For different applications a minimal or maximal surface area may be desired.\n{{Clear}}\n\n== In biology ==\n{{see also|Surface-area-to-volume ratio}}\n[[Image:Mitochondrion 186.jpg|right|thumb|The inner membrane of the [[mitochondrion]] has a large surface area due to infoldings, allowing higher rates of [[cellular respiration]] (electron [[micrograph]]).]]\nThe surface area of an organism is important in several considerations, such as regulation of body temperature and [[digestion]]. Animals use their [[teeth]] to grind food down into smaller particles, increasing the surface area available for digestion. The epithelial tissue lining the digestive tract contains [[microvilli]], greatly increasing the area available for absorption. [[Elephant]]s have large [[ear]]s, allowing them to regulate their own body temperature. In other instances, animals will need to minimize surface area; for example, people will fold their arms over their chest when cold to minimize heat loss.\n\nThe [[surface area to volume ratio]] (SA:V) of a [[cell (biology)|cell]] imposes upper limits on size, as the volume increases much faster than does the surface area, thus limiting the rate at which substances diffuse from the interior across the [[cell membrane]] to interstitial spaces or to other cells. Indeed, representing a cell as an idealized [[sphere]] of radius ''r'', the volume and surface area are, respectively, ''V'' = 4/3 \u03c0 ''r''<sup>3</sup>; ''SA'' = 4 \u03c0 ''r''<sup>2</sup>. The resulting surface area to volume ratio is therefore 3/''r''. Thus, if a cell has a radius of 1 \u03bcm, the SA:V ratio is 3; whereas if the radius of the cell is instead 10 \u03bcm, then the SA:V ratio becomes 0.3. With a cell radius of 100, SA:V ratio is 0.03. Thus, the surface area falls off steeply with increasing volume.\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Perimeter length]]\n* [[BET theory]], technique for the measurement of the specific surface area of materials\n* [[Spherical area]]\n* [[Surface integral]]\n\n== References ==\n\n<references />\n\n* {{eom|title=Area|id=A/a013180|author=Yu.D. Burago, V.A. Zalgaller, L.D. Kudryavtsev}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://blog.thinkwell.com/2010/07/6th-grade-math-surface-area.html Surface Area Video] at Thinkwell\n\n[[Category:Area]]\n", "name_user": "172.223.65.201", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(\u2192\u200eDefinition)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Surface_area"}
{"title_page": "Gaussian integral", "text_new": "{{Use American English|date = January 2019}}\n{{Short description|Integral of the Gaussian function, equal to sqrt(&pi;)}}\n{{about|the Euler\u2013Poisson integral|Gaussian quadrature|Gaussian integration}}\n[[Image:E^(-x^2).svg|thumb|right|A graph of ''f''(''x'') =&nbsp;''e''<sup>\u2212''x''<sup>2</sup></sup> and the area between the function and the ''x''-axis, which is equal to {{math|{{sqrt|''&pi;''}}}}.]]\n\nThe '''Gaussian integral''', also known as the '''Euler\u2013Poisson integral''', is the integral of the [[Gaussian function]] ''e''<sup>\u2212''x''<sup>2</sup></sup> over the entire real line. It is named after the German mathematician [[Carl Friedrich Gauss]].  The integral is:\n\n:<math>\\int_{-\\infty}^\\infty e^{-x^2}\\,dx = \\sqrt{\\pi}.</math>\n\n[[Abraham de Moivre]] originally discovered this type of integral in 1733, while Gauss published the precise integral in 1809.<ref name=\"The Evolution of the Normal Distribution\">{{cite web |url=https://www.maa.org/sites/default/files/pdf/upload_library/22/Allendoerfer/stahl96.pdf |title=The Evolution of the Normal Distribution |work=MAA.org |first=Saul|last=Stahl|date=April 2006|accessdate=May 25, 2018}}</ref> The integral has a wide range of applications.  For example, with a slight change of variables it is used to compute the [[normalizing constant]] of the [[normal distribution]].  The same integral with finite limits is closely related to both the [[error function]] and the [[cumulative distribution function]] of the [[normal distribution]]. In physics this type of integral appears frequently, for example, in [[quantum mechanics]], to find the probability density of the ground state of the harmonic oscillator. This integral is also used in the path integral formulation, to find the propagator of the harmonic oscillator, and in [[statistical mechanics]], to find its [[partition function (statistical mechanics)|partition function]].\n\nAlthough no [[elementary function]] exists for the error function, as can be proven by the [[Risch algorithm]],<ref>{{cite journal |first=G. W. |last=Cherry |title=Integration in Finite Terms with Special Functions: the Error Function |journal=Journal of Symbolic Computation |volume=1 |issue=3 |year=1985 |pages=283\u2013302 |doi=10.1016/S0747-7171(85)80037-7 }}</ref> the Gaussian integral can be solved analytically through the methods of [[multivariable calculus]]. That is, there is no elementary ''[[indefinite integral]]'' for\n:<math>\\int e^{-x^2}\\,dx,</math>\nbut the [[definite integral]]\n:<math>\\int_{-\\infty}^\\infty e^{-x^2}\\,dx</math>\ncan be evaluated. The definite integral of an arbitrary [[Gaussian function]] is\n\n:<math>\\int_{-\\infty}^{\\infty}  e^{-a(x+b)^2}\\,dx= \\sqrt{\\frac{\\pi}{a}}.</math>\n\nThe Gaussian integral is encountered very often in physics and numerous generalizations of the integral are encountered in [[quantum field theory]].\n\n==Computation==\n\n===By polar coordinates===\nA standard way to compute the Gaussian integral, the idea of which goes back to Poisson,<ref name=\"york.ac.uk\">{{cite web |title=The Probability Integral |url=https://www.york.ac.uk/depts/maths/histstat/normal_history.pdf }}</ref> is to make use of the property that:\n\n:<math>\\left(\\int_{-\\infty}^{\\infty} e^{-x^2}\\,dx\\right)^2 = \\int_{-\\infty}^{\\infty} e^{-x^2}\\,dx \\int_{-\\infty}^{\\infty} e^{-y^2}\\,dy = \\int_{-\\infty}^{\\infty}  \\int_{-\\infty}^{\\infty} e^{-(x^2+y^2)}\\, dx\\,dy. </math>\n\nConsider the function ''e''<sup>\u2212(''x''<sup>2</sup>&nbsp;+&nbsp;''y''<sup>2</sup>)</sup>&nbsp;=&nbsp;''e''<sup>\u2212''r''<sup>2</sup></sup> on the plane '''R'''<sup>2</sup>, and compute its integral two ways:\n# on the one hand, by [[double integration]] in the [[Cartesian coordinate system]], its integral is a square:\n#: <math>\\left(\\int e^{-x^2}\\,dx\\right)^2;</math>\n# on the other hand, by [[shell integration]] (a case of double integration in [[polar coordinates]]), its integral is computed to be {{mvar|\u03c0}}.\n\nComparing these two computations yields the integral, though one should take care about the improper integrals involved.\n\n:<math>\\begin{align}\n   \\iint_{\\mathbf{R}^2} e^{-(x^2+y^2)}\\,d(x,y)\n   &= \\int_0^{2\\pi} \\int_0^{\\infty} e^{-r^2}r\\,dr\\,d\\theta\\\\\n   &= 2\\pi \\int_0^\\infty re^{-r^2}\\,dr\\\\\n   &= 2\\pi \\int_{-\\infty}^0 \\tfrac{1}{2} e^s\\,ds && s = -r^2\\\\\n   &= \\pi \\int_{-\\infty}^0 e^s\\,ds \\\\\n   &= \\pi (e^0 - e^{-\\infty}) \\\\\n   &=\\pi,\n \\end{align}</math>\n\nwhere the factor of ''r'' is the [[Jacobian determinant]] which appears because of the [[list of canonical coordinate transformations|transform to polar coordinates]] (''r''&nbsp;''dr''&nbsp;''d\u03b8'' is the standard measure on the plane, expressed in polar coordinates [[Wikibooks:Calculus/Polar Integration#Generalization]]), and the substitution involves taking ''s''&nbsp;=&nbsp;\u2212''r''<sup>2</sup>, so ''ds''&nbsp;=&nbsp;\u22122''r''&nbsp;''dr''.\n\nCombining these yields\n\n: <math>\\left ( \\int_{-\\infty}^\\infty e^{-x^2}\\,dx \\right )^2=\\pi,</math>\n\nso\n\n: <math>\\int_{-\\infty}^\\infty e^{-x^2}\\,dx=\\sqrt{\\pi}</math>.\n\n====Complete proof====\nTo justify the improper double integrals and equating the two expressions, we begin with an approximating function:\n\n:<math>I(a)=\\int_{-a}^a e^{-x^2}dx.</math>\n\nIf the integral\n:<math>\\int_{-\\infty}^\\infty e^{-x^2}\\,dx</math>\nwere [[absolutely convergent]] we would have that its [[Cauchy principal value]], that is, the limit\n\n:<math>\\lim_{a\\to\\infty} I(a) </math>\n\nwould coincide with\n:<math>\\int_{-\\infty}^\\infty e^{-x^2}\\,dx.</math>\nTo see that this is the case, consider that\n\n:<math>\\int_{-\\infty}^\\infty |e^{-x^2}|\\, dx < \\int_{-\\infty}^{-1} -x e^{-x^2}\\, dx + \\int_{-1}^1 e^{-x^2}\\, dx+ \\int_{1}^{\\infty} x e^{-x^2}\\, dx<\\infty.</math>\n\nso we can compute\n:<math>\\int_{-\\infty}^\\infty e^{-x^2}\\,dx</math>\nby just taking the limit\n:<math>\\lim_{a\\to\\infty} I(a)</math>.\n\nTaking the square of <math>I(a)</math> yields\n\n:<math>\\begin{align}\nI(a)^2 & = \\left ( \\int_{-a}^a e^{-x^2}\\, dx \\right ) \\left ( \\int_{-a}^a e^{-y^2}\\, dy \\right ) \\\\\n& = \\int_{-a}^a \\left ( \\int_{-a}^a e^{-y^2}\\, dy \\right )\\,e^{-x^2}\\, dx \\\\\n&  = \\int_{-a}^a \\int_{-a}^a e^{-(x^2+y^2)}\\,dy\\,dx.\n\\end{align}</math>\n\nUsing [[Fubini's theorem]], the above double integral can be seen as an area integral\n\n: <math>\\iint_{[-a, a] \\times [-a, a]} e^{-(x^2+y^2)}\\,d(x,y),</math>\n\ntaken over a square with vertices {(\u2212''a'',&nbsp;''a''), (''a'',&nbsp;''a''), (''a'',&nbsp;\u2212''a''), (\u2212''a'',&nbsp;\u2212''a'')} on the ''xy''-[[Cartesian plane|plane]].\n\nSince the exponential function is greater than 0 for all real numbers, it then follows that the integral taken over the square's [[incircle]] must be less than <math>I(a)^2</math>, and similarly the integral taken over the square's [[circumcircle]] must be greater than <math>I(a)^2</math>. The integrals over the two disks can easily be computed by switching from cartesian coordinates to [[list of canonical coordinate transformations|polar coordinates]]:\n\n: <math>\n\\begin{align}\nx & = r \\cos \\theta \\\\\ny & = r \\sin\\theta\n\\end{align}\n</math>\n\n:<math>\n\\mathbf J(r, \\theta) = \n\\begin{bmatrix}\n  \\dfrac{\\partial x}{\\partial r} & \\dfrac{\\partial x}{\\partial\\theta}\\\\[1em]\n  \\dfrac{\\partial y}{\\partial r} & \\dfrac{\\partial y}{\\partial\\theta} \\end{bmatrix}\n= \\begin{bmatrix}\n  \\cos\\theta& - r\\sin \\theta \\\\\n  \\sin\\theta&   r\\cos \\theta\n\\end{bmatrix}\n</math>\n\n: <math>\nd(x,y) = |J(r, \\theta)|d(r,\\theta) = r\\, d(r,\\theta).\n</math>\n\n:<math>\\int_0^{2\\pi}\\int_0^a re^{-r^2}\\,dr\\,d\\theta < I^2(a) < \\int_0^{2\\pi}\\int_0^{a\\sqrt{2}} re^{-r^2}\\,dr\\,d\\theta.</math>\n\n(See [[list of canonical coordinate transformations|to polar coordinates from Cartesian coordinates]] for help with polar transformation.)\n\nIntegrating,\n\n:<math>\\pi (1-e^{-a^2}) <  I^2(a) < \\pi (1 - e^{-2a^2}). </math>\n\nBy the [[squeeze theorem]], this gives the Gaussian integral\n\n:<math>\\int_{-\\infty}^\\infty e^{-x^2}\\, dx = \\sqrt{\\pi}.</math>\n\n===By Cartesian coordinates===\nA different technique, which goes back to Laplace (1812),<ref name=\"york.ac.uk\" /> is the following. Let\n\n: <math>\\begin{align}\ny & = xs \\\\\ndy & = x\\,ds.\n\\end{align}</math>\n\nSince the limits on ''s'' as ''y'' \u2192 \u00b1\u221e depend on the sign of ''x'', it simplifies the calculation to use the fact that ''e''<sup>\u2212''x''<sup>2</sup></sup> is an [[even function]], and, therefore, the integral over all real numbers is just twice the integral from zero to infinity. That is,\n\n:<math>\\int_{-\\infty}^{\\infty} e^{-x^2}\\,dx = 2\\int_{0}^{\\infty} e^{-x^2}\\,dx.</math>\n\nThus, over the range of integration, ''x'' \u2265 0, and the variables ''y'' and ''s'' have the same limits. This yields:\n\n:<math>\\begin{align}\nI^2 &= 4 \\int_0^\\infty \\int_0^\\infty e^{-(x^2 + y^2)} dy\\,dx \\\\\n&= 4 \\int_0^\\infty \\left( \\int_0^\\infty e^{-(x^2 + y^2)} \\, dy \\right) \\, dx \\\\\n&= 4 \\int_0^\\infty \\left( \\int_0^\\infty e^{-x^2(1+s^2)} x\\,ds \\right) \\, dx \\\\\n&= 4 \\int_0^\\infty \\left( \\int_0^\\infty e^{-x^2(1 + s^2)} x \\, dx \\right) \\, ds \\\\\n&= 4 \\int_0^\\infty \\left[ \\frac{1}{-2(1+s^2)} e^{-x^2(1+s^2)} \\right]_{x=0}^{x=\\infty} \\, ds \\\\\n&= 4 \\left (\\frac{1}{2} \\int_0^\\infty \\frac{ds}{1+s^2}  \\right ) \\\\\n&= 2 \\Big [ \\arctan s \\Big ]_0^\\infty \\\\\n&= \\pi.\n\\end{align}</math>\n\nTherefore, <math>I = \\sqrt{\\pi}</math>, as expected.\n\n==Relation to the gamma function==\n\nThe integrand is an [[even function]],\n\n:<math>\\int_{-\\infty}^{\\infty} e^{-x^2} dx = 2 \\int_0^\\infty e^{-x^2} dx</math>\n\nThus, after the change of variable <math>x=\\sqrt{t}</math>, this turns into the Euler integral\n\n:<math>2 \\int_0^\\infty e^{-x^2} dx=2\\int_0^\\infty \\frac{1}{2}\\ e^{-t} \\ t^{-\\frac{1}{2}} dt = \\Gamma\\left(\\frac{1}{2}\\right) = \\sqrt{\\pi}</math>\n\nwhere <math> \\Gamma(z)=\\int_{0}^{\\infty} t^{z-1} e^{-t} dt </math> is the [[gamma function]]. This shows why the [[factorial]] of a half-integer is a rational multiple of <math>\\sqrt \\pi</math>. More generally,\n\n:<math>\\int_0^\\infty x^n e^{-ax^b} dx = \\frac{\\Gamma\\left((n+1)/b\\right)}{ba^{(n+1)/b}}, </math>\n\nwhich can be obtained by substituting <math>t=a x^b</math> in the integrand of the gamma function  to get <math> \\Gamma(z) = a^z b \\int_0^{\\infty} x^{bz-1} e^{-a x^b} dx </math> .\n\n==Generalizations==\n\n===The integral of a Gaussian function===\n{{Main|Integral of a Gaussian function}}\nThe integral of an arbitrary [[Gaussian function]] is\n\n:<math>\\int_{-\\infty}^{\\infty}  e^{-a(x+b)^2}\\,dx= \\sqrt{\\frac{\\pi}{a}}.</math>\n\nAn alternative form is\n\n:<math>\\int_{-\\infty}^{\\infty}e^{- a x^2 + b x + c}\\,dx=\\sqrt{\\frac{\\pi}{a}}\\,e^{\\frac{b^2}{4a}+c}.</math>\n\nThis form is useful for calculating expectations of some continuous probability distributions related to the normal distribution, such as the [[log-normal distribution]], for example.\n\n===''n''-dimensional and functional generalization===\n{{main|multivariate normal distribution}}\nSuppose ''A'' is a symmetric positive-definite (hence invertible) {{math|''n'' \u00d7 ''n''}} [[precision matrix]], which is the matrix inverse of the [[covariance matrix]]. Then,\n\n:<math>\\int_{-\\infty}^\\infty \\exp{\\left(-\\frac 1 2 \\sum\\limits_{i,j=1}^{n}A_{ij} x_i x_j \\right)} \\, d^nx =\\int_{-\\infty}^\\infty \\exp{\\left(-\\frac 1 2 x^{T} A x \\right)} \\, d^nx=\\sqrt{\\frac{(2\\pi)^n}{\\det A}} =\\sqrt{\\frac{1}{\\det (A / 2\\pi)}} =\\sqrt{\\det (2 \\pi A^{-1})}</math>\n\nwhere the integral is understood to be over '''R'''<sup>''n''</sup>.  This fact is applied in the study of the [[multivariate normal distribution]].\n\nAlso,\n\n:<math>\\int x_{k_1}\\cdots x_{k_{2N}} \\, \\exp{\\left( -\\frac{1}{2} \\sum\\limits_{i,j=1}^{n}A_{ij} x_i x_j \\right)} \\, d^nx =\\sqrt{\\frac{(2\\pi)^n}{\\det A}} \\, \\frac{1}{2^N N!} \\, \\sum_{\\sigma \\in S_{2N}}(A^{-1})_{k_{\\sigma(1)}k_{\\sigma(2)}} \\cdots (A^{-1})_{k_{\\sigma(2N-1)}k_{\\sigma(2N)}}</math>\n\nwhere \u03c3 is a [[permutation]] of {1, ..., 2''N''} and the extra factor on the right-hand side is the sum over all combinatorial pairings of {1, ..., 2''N''} of ''N'' copies of ''A''<sup>\u22121</sup>.\n\nAlternatively,<ref name=\"Central identity explanation\">{{cite web |title=Reference for Multidimensional Gaussian Integral |date=March 30, 2012 |work=[[Stack Exchange]] |url=https://math.stackexchange.com/q/126227 }}</ref>\n\n:<math>\\int f(\\vec x) \\exp{\\left( - \\frac 1 2 \\sum\\limits_{i,j=1}^{n}A_{ij} x_i x_j \\right)} d^nx=\\sqrt{(2\\pi)^n\\over \\det A} \\, \\left. \\exp{\\left({1\\over 2}\\sum\\limits_{i,j=1}^{n}(A^{-1})_{ij}{\\partial \\over \\partial x_i}{\\partial \\over \\partial x_j}\\right)}f(\\vec{x})\\right|_{\\vec{x}=0}</math>\n\nfor some [[analytic function]] ''f'', provided it satisfies some appropriate bounds on its growth and some other technical criteria. (It works for some functions and fails for others. Polynomials are fine.) The exponential over a differential operator is understood as a [[power series]].\n\nWhile [[functional integral]]s have no rigorous definition (or even a nonrigorous computational one in most cases), we can ''define'' a Gaussian functional integral in analogy to the finite-dimensional case. {{Citation needed|date=June 2011}} There is still the problem, though, that <math>(2\\pi)^\\infty</math> is infinite and also, the [[functional determinant]] would also be infinite in general. This can be taken care of if we only consider ratios:\n\n:<math>\\frac{\\int f(x_1)\\cdots f(x_{2N}) \\exp\\left[{-\\iint \\frac{1}{2}A(x_{2N+1},x_{2N+2}) f(x_{2N+1}) f(x_{2N+2}) d^dx_{2N+1} d^dx_{2N+2}}\\right] \\mathcal{D}f}{\\int \\exp\\left[{-\\iint \\frac{1}{2} A(x_{2N+1}, x_{2N+2}) f(x_{2N+1}) f(x_{2N+2}) d^dx_{2N+1} d^dx_{2N+2}}\\right] \\mathcal{D}f} =\\frac{1}{2^N N!}\\sum_{\\sigma \\in S_{2N}}A^{-1}(x_{\\sigma(1)},x_{\\sigma(2)})\\cdots A^{-1}(x_{\\sigma(2N-1)},x_{\\sigma(2N)}).</math>\n\nIn the [[DeWitt notation]], the equation looks identical to the finite-dimensional case.\n\n===''n''-dimensional with linear term===\nIf A is again a symmetric positive-definite matrix, then (assuming all are column vectors)\n:<math>\\int e^{-\\frac{1}{2}\\sum\\limits_{i,j=1}^{n}A_{ij} x_i x_j+\\sum\\limits_{i=1}^{n}B_i x_i} d^nx=\\int e^{-\\frac{1}{2}\\vec{x}^T \\mathbf{A} \\vec{x}+\\vec{B}^T \\vec{x}} d^nx= \\sqrt{ \\frac{(2\\pi)^n}{\\det{A}} }e^{\\frac{1}{2}\\vec{B}^{T}\\mathbf{A}^{-1}\\vec{B}}.</math>\n\n===Integrals of similar form===\n:<math>\\int_0^\\infty x^{2n}  e^{-\\frac{x^2}{a^2}}\\,dx = \\sqrt{\\pi}\\frac{a^{2n+1} (2n-1)!!}{2^{n+1}}</math>\n:<math>\\int_0^\\infty x^{2n+1} e^{-\\frac{x^2}{a^2}}\\,dx = \\frac{n!}{2} a^{2n+2}</math>\n:<math>\\int_0^\\infty x^{2n}e^{-ax^2}\\,dx = \\frac{(2n-1)!!}{a^n 2^{n+1}} \\sqrt{\\frac{\\pi}{a}}</math>\n:<math>\\int_0^\\infty x^{2n+1}e^{-ax^2}\\,dx = \\frac{n!}{2a^{n+1}}</math>\n:<math>\\int_0^\\infty x^{n}e^{-ax^2}\\,dx = \\frac{\\Gamma(\\frac{n+1}{2})}{2a^{\\frac{n+1}{2}}}</math>\nwhere ''n'' is a positive integer and !! denotes the [[double factorial]].\n\nAn easy way to derive these is by [[differentiation under the integral sign|parameter differentiation]].\n\n:<math>\\begin{align}\n\\int_{-\\infty}^\\infty x^{2n} e^{-\\alpha x^2}\\,dx &= \\left(-1\\right)^n\\int_{-\\infty}^\\infty \\frac{\\partial^n}{\\partial \\alpha^n} e^{-\\alpha x^2}\\,dx = \\left(-1\\right)^n\\frac{\\partial^n}{\\partial \\alpha^n} \\int_{-\\infty}^\\infty e^{-\\alpha x^2}\\,dx\\\\\n&= \\sqrt{\\pi} \\left(-1\\right)^n\\frac{\\partial^n}{\\partial \\alpha^n}\\alpha^{-\\frac{1}{2}} = \\sqrt{\\frac{\\pi}{\\alpha}}\\frac{(2n-1)!!}{\\left(2\\alpha\\right)^n}\n\\end{align}</math>\n\nOne could also integrate by parts and find a [[recurrence relation]] to solve this.\n\n===Higher-order polynomials===\n\nApplying a linear change of basis shows that the integral of the exponential of a homogeneous polynomial in ''n'' variables may depend only on [[SL(n)|SL(''n'')]]-invariants of the polynomial. One such invariant is the [[discriminant]],\nzeros of which mark the singularities of the integral. However, the integral may also depend on other invariants.<ref name=\"morozov2009\">{{cite journal\n | last = Morozov | first = A.\n | last2 = Shakirove | first2= Sh.\n | journal = Journal of High Energy Physics\n | pages = 002\n | title = Introduction to integral discriminants\n | doi = 10.1088/1126-6708/2009/12/002\n | volume = 12\n | year = 2009 | arxiv = 0903.2595\n }}</ref>\n\nExponentials of other even polynomials can numerically be solved using series. These may be interpreted as [[formal calculation]]s when there is no convergence. For example, the solution to the integral of the exponential of a quartic polynomial is{{citation needed|date=August 2015}}\n\n: <math>\\int_{-\\infty}^{\\infty} e^{a x^4+b x^3+c x^2+d x+f}\\,dx = \\frac{1}{2} e^f \\sum_{\\begin{smallmatrix}n,m,p=0 \\\\ n+p=0 \\mod 2\\end{smallmatrix}}^{\\infty} \\frac{b^n}{n!} \\frac{c^m}{m!} \\frac{d^p}{p!} \\frac{\\Gamma \\left (\\frac{3n+2m+p+1}{4} \\right)}{(-a)^{\\frac{3n+2m+p+1}4}}.</math>\n\nThe ''n''&nbsp;+&nbsp;''p'' = 0 mod 2 requirement is because the integral from \u2212\u221e to 0 contributes a factor of (\u22121)<sup>''n''+''p''</sup>/2 to each term, while the integral from 0 to +\u221e contributes a factor of 1/2 to each term. These integrals turn up in subjects such as [[quantum field theory]].\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of integrals of Gaussian functions]]\n* [[Common integrals in quantum field theory]]\n* [[Normal distribution]]\n* [[List of integrals of exponential functions]]\n* [[Error function]]\n* [[Berezin integral]]\n\n== References ==\n=== Citations ===\n{{Reflist}}\n\n=== Sources ===\n{{refbegin}}\n* {{MathWorld |title = Gaussian Integral |urlname = GaussianIntegral }}\n* {{cite book |first=David |last=Griffiths |title=Introduction to Quantum Mechanics |edition=2nd }}\n* {{cite book |last=Abramowitz |first=M. |last2=Stegun |first2=I. A. |title = Handbook of Mathematical Functions |publisher=Dover Publications |location=New York }}\n{{refend}}\n\n{{-}}\n{{integral}}\n\n[[Category:Integrals]]\n[[Category:Articles containing proofs]]\n[[Category:Gaussian function]]\n[[Category:Theorems in analysis]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use American English|date = January 2019}}\n{{Short description|Integral of the Gaussian function, equal to sqrt(&pi;)}}\n{{about|the Euler\u2013Poisson integral|Gaussian quadrature|Gaussian integration}}\n[[Image:E^(-x^2).svg|thumb|right|A graph of ''f''(''x'') =&nbsp;''e''<sup>\u2212''x''<sup>2</sup></sup> and the area between the function and the ''x''-axis, which is equal to {{math|{{sqrt|''&pi;''}}}}.]]\n\nThe '''Gaussian integral''', also known as the '''Euler\u2013Poisson integral''', is the integral of the [[Gaussian function]] ''e''<sup>\u2212''x''<sup>2</sup></sup> over the entire real line. It is named after the German mathematician [[Carl Friedrich Gauss]].  The integral is:\n\n:<math>\\int_{-\\infty}^\\infty e^{-x^2}\\,dx = \\sqrt{\\pi}.</math>\n\n[[Abraham de Moivre]] originally discovered this type of integral in 1733, while Gauss published the precise integral in 1809.<ref name=\"History of normal distribution\">{{cite web |url=https://www.maa.org/sites/default/files/pdf/upload_library/22/Allendoerfer/stahl96.pdf |title=The History of the Normal Distribution |work=MAA.org |first=Saul|last=Stahl|date=April 2006|accessdate=May 25, 2018}}</ref> The integral has a wide range of applications.  For example, with a slight change of variables it is used to compute the [[normalizing constant]] of the [[normal distribution]].  The same integral with finite limits is closely related to both the [[error function]] and the [[cumulative distribution function]] of the [[normal distribution]]. In physics this type of integral appears frequently, for example, in [[quantum mechanics]], to find the probability density of the ground state of the harmonic oscillator. This integral is also used in the path integral formulation, to find the propagator of the harmonic oscillator, and in [[statistical mechanics]], to find its [[partition function (statistical mechanics)|partition function]].\n\nAlthough no [[elementary function]] exists for the error function, as can be proven by the [[Risch algorithm]],<ref>{{cite journal |first=G. W. |last=Cherry |title=Integration in Finite Terms with Special Functions: the Error Function |journal=Journal of Symbolic Computation |volume=1 |issue=3 |year=1985 |pages=283\u2013302 |doi=10.1016/S0747-7171(85)80037-7 }}</ref> the Gaussian integral can be solved analytically through the methods of [[multivariable calculus]]. That is, there is no elementary ''[[indefinite integral]]'' for\n:<math>\\int e^{-x^2}\\,dx,</math>\nbut the [[definite integral]]\n:<math>\\int_{-\\infty}^\\infty e^{-x^2}\\,dx</math>\ncan be evaluated. The definite integral of an arbitrary [[Gaussian function]] is\n\n:<math>\\int_{-\\infty}^{\\infty}  e^{-a(x+b)^2}\\,dx= \\sqrt{\\frac{\\pi}{a}}.</math>\n\nThe Gaussian integral is encountered very often in physics and numerous generalizations of the integral are encountered in [[quantum field theory]].\n\n==Computation==\n\n===By polar coordinates===\nA standard way to compute the Gaussian integral, the idea of which goes back to Poisson,<ref name=\"york.ac.uk\">{{cite web |title=The Probability Integral |url=https://www.york.ac.uk/depts/maths/histstat/normal_history.pdf }}</ref> is to make use of the property that:\n\n:<math>\\left(\\int_{-\\infty}^{\\infty} e^{-x^2}\\,dx\\right)^2 = \\int_{-\\infty}^{\\infty} e^{-x^2}\\,dx \\int_{-\\infty}^{\\infty} e^{-y^2}\\,dy = \\int_{-\\infty}^{\\infty}  \\int_{-\\infty}^{\\infty} e^{-(x^2+y^2)}\\, dx\\,dy. </math>\n\nConsider the function ''e''<sup>\u2212(''x''<sup>2</sup>&nbsp;+&nbsp;''y''<sup>2</sup>)</sup>&nbsp;=&nbsp;''e''<sup>\u2212''r''<sup>2</sup></sup> on the plane '''R'''<sup>2</sup>, and compute its integral two ways:\n# on the one hand, by [[double integration]] in the [[Cartesian coordinate system]], its integral is a square:\n#: <math>\\left(\\int e^{-x^2}\\,dx\\right)^2;</math>\n# on the other hand, by [[shell integration]] (a case of double integration in [[polar coordinates]]), its integral is computed to be {{mvar|\u03c0}}.\n\nComparing these two computations yields the integral, though one should take care about the improper integrals involved.\n\n:<math>\\begin{align}\n   \\iint_{\\mathbf{R}^2} e^{-(x^2+y^2)}\\,d(x,y)\n   &= \\int_0^{2\\pi} \\int_0^{\\infty} e^{-r^2}r\\,dr\\,d\\theta\\\\\n   &= 2\\pi \\int_0^\\infty re^{-r^2}\\,dr\\\\\n   &= 2\\pi \\int_{-\\infty}^0 \\tfrac{1}{2} e^s\\,ds && s = -r^2\\\\\n   &= \\pi \\int_{-\\infty}^0 e^s\\,ds \\\\\n   &= \\pi (e^0 - e^{-\\infty}) \\\\\n   &=\\pi,\n \\end{align}</math>\n\nwhere the factor of ''r'' is the [[Jacobian determinant]] which appears because of the [[list of canonical coordinate transformations|transform to polar coordinates]] (''r''&nbsp;''dr''&nbsp;''d\u03b8'' is the standard measure on the plane, expressed in polar coordinates [[Wikibooks:Calculus/Polar Integration#Generalization]]), and the substitution involves taking ''s''&nbsp;=&nbsp;\u2212''r''<sup>2</sup>, so ''ds''&nbsp;=&nbsp;\u22122''r''&nbsp;''dr''.\n\nCombining these yields\n\n: <math>\\left ( \\int_{-\\infty}^\\infty e^{-x^2}\\,dx \\right )^2=\\pi,</math>\n\nso\n\n: <math>\\int_{-\\infty}^\\infty e^{-x^2}\\,dx=\\sqrt{\\pi}</math>.\n\n====Complete proof====\nTo justify the improper double integrals and equating the two expressions, we begin with an approximating function:\n\n:<math>I(a)=\\int_{-a}^a e^{-x^2}dx.</math>\n\nIf the integral\n:<math>\\int_{-\\infty}^\\infty e^{-x^2}\\,dx</math>\nwere [[absolutely convergent]] we would have that its [[Cauchy principal value]], that is, the limit\n\n:<math>\\lim_{a\\to\\infty} I(a) </math>\n\nwould coincide with\n:<math>\\int_{-\\infty}^\\infty e^{-x^2}\\,dx.</math>\nTo see that this is the case, consider that\n\n:<math>\\int_{-\\infty}^\\infty |e^{-x^2}|\\, dx < \\int_{-\\infty}^{-1} -x e^{-x^2}\\, dx + \\int_{-1}^1 e^{-x^2}\\, dx+ \\int_{1}^{\\infty} x e^{-x^2}\\, dx<\\infty.</math>\n\nso we can compute\n:<math>\\int_{-\\infty}^\\infty e^{-x^2}\\,dx</math>\nby just taking the limit\n:<math>\\lim_{a\\to\\infty} I(a)</math>.\n\nTaking the square of <math>I(a)</math> yields\n\n:<math>\\begin{align}\nI(a)^2 & = \\left ( \\int_{-a}^a e^{-x^2}\\, dx \\right ) \\left ( \\int_{-a}^a e^{-y^2}\\, dy \\right ) \\\\\n& = \\int_{-a}^a \\left ( \\int_{-a}^a e^{-y^2}\\, dy \\right )\\,e^{-x^2}\\, dx \\\\\n&  = \\int_{-a}^a \\int_{-a}^a e^{-(x^2+y^2)}\\,dy\\,dx.\n\\end{align}</math>\n\nUsing [[Fubini's theorem]], the above double integral can be seen as an area integral\n\n: <math>\\iint_{[-a, a] \\times [-a, a]} e^{-(x^2+y^2)}\\,d(x,y),</math>\n\ntaken over a square with vertices {(\u2212''a'',&nbsp;''a''), (''a'',&nbsp;''a''), (''a'',&nbsp;\u2212''a''), (\u2212''a'',&nbsp;\u2212''a'')} on the ''xy''-[[Cartesian plane|plane]].\n\nSince the exponential function is greater than 0 for all real numbers, it then follows that the integral taken over the square's [[incircle]] must be less than <math>I(a)^2</math>, and similarly the integral taken over the square's [[circumcircle]] must be greater than <math>I(a)^2</math>. The integrals over the two disks can easily be computed by switching from cartesian coordinates to [[list of canonical coordinate transformations|polar coordinates]]:\n\n: <math>\n\\begin{align}\nx & = r \\cos \\theta \\\\\ny & = r \\sin\\theta\n\\end{align}\n</math>\n\n:<math>\n\\mathbf J(r, \\theta) = \n\\begin{bmatrix}\n  \\dfrac{\\partial x}{\\partial r} & \\dfrac{\\partial x}{\\partial\\theta}\\\\[1em]\n  \\dfrac{\\partial y}{\\partial r} & \\dfrac{\\partial y}{\\partial\\theta} \\end{bmatrix}\n= \\begin{bmatrix}\n  \\cos\\theta& - r\\sin \\theta \\\\\n  \\sin\\theta&   r\\cos \\theta\n\\end{bmatrix}\n</math>\n\n: <math>\nd(x,y) = |J(r, \\theta)|d(r,\\theta) = r\\, d(r,\\theta).\n</math>\n\n:<math>\\int_0^{2\\pi}\\int_0^a re^{-r^2}\\,dr\\,d\\theta < I^2(a) < \\int_0^{2\\pi}\\int_0^{a\\sqrt{2}} re^{-r^2}\\,dr\\,d\\theta.</math>\n\n(See [[list of canonical coordinate transformations|to polar coordinates from Cartesian coordinates]] for help with polar transformation.)\n\nIntegrating,\n\n:<math>\\pi (1-e^{-a^2}) <  I^2(a) < \\pi (1 - e^{-2a^2}). </math>\n\nBy the [[squeeze theorem]], this gives the Gaussian integral\n\n:<math>\\int_{-\\infty}^\\infty e^{-x^2}\\, dx = \\sqrt{\\pi}.</math>\n\n===By Cartesian coordinates===\nA different technique, which goes back to Laplace (1812),<ref name=\"york.ac.uk\" /> is the following. Let\n\n: <math>\\begin{align}\ny & = xs \\\\\ndy & = x\\,ds.\n\\end{align}</math>\n\nSince the limits on ''s'' as ''y'' \u2192 \u00b1\u221e depend on the sign of ''x'', it simplifies the calculation to use the fact that ''e''<sup>\u2212''x''<sup>2</sup></sup> is an [[even function]], and, therefore, the integral over all real numbers is just twice the integral from zero to infinity. That is,\n\n:<math>\\int_{-\\infty}^{\\infty} e^{-x^2}\\,dx = 2\\int_{0}^{\\infty} e^{-x^2}\\,dx.</math>\n\nThus, over the range of integration, ''x'' \u2265 0, and the variables ''y'' and ''s'' have the same limits. This yields:\n\n:<math>\\begin{align}\nI^2 &= 4 \\int_0^\\infty \\int_0^\\infty e^{-(x^2 + y^2)} dy\\,dx \\\\\n&= 4 \\int_0^\\infty \\left( \\int_0^\\infty e^{-(x^2 + y^2)} \\, dy \\right) \\, dx \\\\\n&= 4 \\int_0^\\infty \\left( \\int_0^\\infty e^{-x^2(1+s^2)} x\\,ds \\right) \\, dx \\\\\n&= 4 \\int_0^\\infty \\left( \\int_0^\\infty e^{-x^2(1 + s^2)} x \\, dx \\right) \\, ds \\\\\n&= 4 \\int_0^\\infty \\left[ \\frac{1}{-2(1+s^2)} e^{-x^2(1+s^2)} \\right]_{x=0}^{x=\\infty} \\, ds \\\\\n&= 4 \\left (\\frac{1}{2} \\int_0^\\infty \\frac{ds}{1+s^2}  \\right ) \\\\\n&= 2 \\Big [ \\arctan s \\Big ]_0^\\infty \\\\\n&= \\pi.\n\\end{align}</math>\n\nTherefore, <math>I = \\sqrt{\\pi}</math>, as expected.\n\n==Relation to the gamma function==\n\nThe integrand is an [[even function]],\n\n:<math>\\int_{-\\infty}^{\\infty} e^{-x^2} dx = 2 \\int_0^\\infty e^{-x^2} dx</math>\n\nThus, after the change of variable <math>x=\\sqrt{t}</math>, this turns into the Euler integral\n\n:<math>2 \\int_0^\\infty e^{-x^2} dx=2\\int_0^\\infty \\frac{1}{2}\\ e^{-t} \\ t^{-\\frac{1}{2}} dt = \\Gamma\\left(\\frac{1}{2}\\right) = \\sqrt{\\pi}</math>\n\nwhere <math> \\Gamma(z)=\\int_{0}^{\\infty} t^{z-1} e^{-t} dt </math> is the [[gamma function]]. This shows why the [[factorial]] of a half-integer is a rational multiple of <math>\\sqrt \\pi</math>. More generally,\n\n:<math>\\int_0^\\infty x^n e^{-ax^b} dx = \\frac{\\Gamma\\left((n+1)/b\\right)}{ba^{(n+1)/b}}, </math>\n\nwhich can be obtained by substituting <math>t=a x^b</math> in the integrand of the gamma function  to get <math> \\Gamma(z) = a^z b \\int_0^{\\infty} x^{bz-1} e^{-a x^b} dx </math> .\n\n==Generalizations==\n\n===The integral of a Gaussian function===\n{{Main|Integral of a Gaussian function}}\nThe integral of an arbitrary [[Gaussian function]] is\n\n:<math>\\int_{-\\infty}^{\\infty}  e^{-a(x+b)^2}\\,dx= \\sqrt{\\frac{\\pi}{a}}.</math>\n\nAn alternative form is\n\n:<math>\\int_{-\\infty}^{\\infty}e^{- a x^2 + b x + c}\\,dx=\\sqrt{\\frac{\\pi}{a}}\\,e^{\\frac{b^2}{4a}+c}.</math>\n\nThis form is useful for calculating expectations of some continuous probability distributions related to the normal distribution, such as the [[log-normal distribution]], for example.\n\n===''n''-dimensional and functional generalization===\n{{main|multivariate normal distribution}}\nSuppose ''A'' is a symmetric positive-definite (hence invertible) {{math|''n'' \u00d7 ''n''}} [[precision matrix]], which is the matrix inverse of the [[covariance matrix]]. Then,\n\n:<math>\\int_{-\\infty}^\\infty \\exp{\\left(-\\frac 1 2 \\sum\\limits_{i,j=1}^{n}A_{ij} x_i x_j \\right)} \\, d^nx =\\int_{-\\infty}^\\infty \\exp{\\left(-\\frac 1 2 x^{T} A x \\right)} \\, d^nx=\\sqrt{\\frac{(2\\pi)^n}{\\det A}} =\\sqrt{\\frac{1}{\\det (A / 2\\pi)}} =\\sqrt{\\det (2 \\pi A^{-1})}</math>\n\nwhere the integral is understood to be over '''R'''<sup>''n''</sup>.  This fact is applied in the study of the [[multivariate normal distribution]].\n\nAlso,\n\n:<math>\\int x_{k_1}\\cdots x_{k_{2N}} \\, \\exp{\\left( -\\frac{1}{2} \\sum\\limits_{i,j=1}^{n}A_{ij} x_i x_j \\right)} \\, d^nx =\\sqrt{\\frac{(2\\pi)^n}{\\det A}} \\, \\frac{1}{2^N N!} \\, \\sum_{\\sigma \\in S_{2N}}(A^{-1})_{k_{\\sigma(1)}k_{\\sigma(2)}} \\cdots (A^{-1})_{k_{\\sigma(2N-1)}k_{\\sigma(2N)}}</math>\n\nwhere \u03c3 is a [[permutation]] of {1, ..., 2''N''} and the extra factor on the right-hand side is the sum over all combinatorial pairings of {1, ..., 2''N''} of ''N'' copies of ''A''<sup>\u22121</sup>.\n\nAlternatively,<ref name=\"Central identity explanation\">{{cite web |title=Reference for Multidimensional Gaussian Integral |date=March 30, 2012 |work=[[Stack Exchange]] |url=https://math.stackexchange.com/q/126227 }}</ref>\n\n:<math>\\int f(\\vec x) \\exp{\\left( - \\frac 1 2 \\sum\\limits_{i,j=1}^{n}A_{ij} x_i x_j \\right)} d^nx=\\sqrt{(2\\pi)^n\\over \\det A} \\, \\left. \\exp{\\left({1\\over 2}\\sum\\limits_{i,j=1}^{n}(A^{-1})_{ij}{\\partial \\over \\partial x_i}{\\partial \\over \\partial x_j}\\right)}f(\\vec{x})\\right|_{\\vec{x}=0}</math>\n\nfor some [[analytic function]] ''f'', provided it satisfies some appropriate bounds on its growth and some other technical criteria. (It works for some functions and fails for others. Polynomials are fine.) The exponential over a differential operator is understood as a [[power series]].\n\nWhile [[functional integral]]s have no rigorous definition (or even a nonrigorous computational one in most cases), we can ''define'' a Gaussian functional integral in analogy to the finite-dimensional case. {{Citation needed|date=June 2011}} There is still the problem, though, that <math>(2\\pi)^\\infty</math> is infinite and also, the [[functional determinant]] would also be infinite in general. This can be taken care of if we only consider ratios:\n\n:<math>\\frac{\\int f(x_1)\\cdots f(x_{2N}) \\exp\\left[{-\\iint \\frac{1}{2}A(x_{2N+1},x_{2N+2}) f(x_{2N+1}) f(x_{2N+2}) d^dx_{2N+1} d^dx_{2N+2}}\\right] \\mathcal{D}f}{\\int \\exp\\left[{-\\iint \\frac{1}{2} A(x_{2N+1}, x_{2N+2}) f(x_{2N+1}) f(x_{2N+2}) d^dx_{2N+1} d^dx_{2N+2}}\\right] \\mathcal{D}f} =\\frac{1}{2^N N!}\\sum_{\\sigma \\in S_{2N}}A^{-1}(x_{\\sigma(1)},x_{\\sigma(2)})\\cdots A^{-1}(x_{\\sigma(2N-1)},x_{\\sigma(2N)}).</math>\n\nIn the [[DeWitt notation]], the equation looks identical to the finite-dimensional case.\n\n===''n''-dimensional with linear term===\nIf A is again a symmetric positive-definite matrix, then (assuming all are column vectors)\n:<math>\\int e^{-\\frac{1}{2}\\sum\\limits_{i,j=1}^{n}A_{ij} x_i x_j+\\sum\\limits_{i=1}^{n}B_i x_i} d^nx=\\int e^{-\\frac{1}{2}\\vec{x}^T \\mathbf{A} \\vec{x}+\\vec{B}^T \\vec{x}} d^nx= \\sqrt{ \\frac{(2\\pi)^n}{\\det{A}} }e^{\\frac{1}{2}\\vec{B}^{T}\\mathbf{A}^{-1}\\vec{B}}.</math>\n\n===Integrals of similar form===\n:<math>\\int_0^\\infty x^{2n}  e^{-\\frac{x^2}{a^2}}\\,dx = \\sqrt{\\pi}\\frac{a^{2n+1} (2n-1)!!}{2^{n+1}}</math>\n:<math>\\int_0^\\infty x^{2n+1} e^{-\\frac{x^2}{a^2}}\\,dx = \\frac{n!}{2} a^{2n+2}</math>\n:<math>\\int_0^\\infty x^{2n}e^{-ax^2}\\,dx = \\frac{(2n-1)!!}{a^n 2^{n+1}} \\sqrt{\\frac{\\pi}{a}}</math>\n:<math>\\int_0^\\infty x^{2n+1}e^{-ax^2}\\,dx = \\frac{n!}{2a^{n+1}}</math>\n:<math>\\int_0^\\infty x^{n}e^{-ax^2}\\,dx = \\frac{\\Gamma(\\frac{n+1}{2})}{2a^{\\frac{n+1}{2}}}</math>\nwhere ''n'' is a positive integer and !! denotes the [[double factorial]].\n\nAn easy way to derive these is by [[differentiation under the integral sign|parameter differentiation]].\n\n:<math>\\begin{align}\n\\int_{-\\infty}^\\infty x^{2n} e^{-\\alpha x^2}\\,dx &= \\left(-1\\right)^n\\int_{-\\infty}^\\infty \\frac{\\partial^n}{\\partial \\alpha^n} e^{-\\alpha x^2}\\,dx = \\left(-1\\right)^n\\frac{\\partial^n}{\\partial \\alpha^n} \\int_{-\\infty}^\\infty e^{-\\alpha x^2}\\,dx\\\\\n&= \\sqrt{\\pi} \\left(-1\\right)^n\\frac{\\partial^n}{\\partial \\alpha^n}\\alpha^{-\\frac{1}{2}} = \\sqrt{\\frac{\\pi}{\\alpha}}\\frac{(2n-1)!!}{\\left(2\\alpha\\right)^n}\n\\end{align}</math>\n\nOne could also integrate by parts and find a [[recurrence relation]] to solve this.\n\n===Higher-order polynomials===\n\nApplying a linear change of basis shows that the integral of the exponential of a homogeneous polynomial in ''n'' variables may depend only on [[SL(n)|SL(''n'')]]-invariants of the polynomial. One such invariant is the [[discriminant]],\nzeros of which mark the singularities of the integral. However, the integral may also depend on other invariants.<ref name=\"morozov2009\">{{cite journal\n | last = Morozov | first = A.\n | last2 = Shakirove | first2= Sh.\n | journal = Journal of High Energy Physics\n | pages = 002\n | title = Introduction to integral discriminants\n | doi = 10.1088/1126-6708/2009/12/002\n | volume = 12\n | year = 2009 | arxiv = 0903.2595\n }}</ref>\n\nExponentials of other even polynomials can numerically be solved using series. These may be interpreted as [[formal calculation]]s when there is no convergence. For example, the solution to the integral of the exponential of a quartic polynomial is{{citation needed|date=August 2015}}\n\n: <math>\\int_{-\\infty}^{\\infty} e^{a x^4+b x^3+c x^2+d x+f}\\,dx = \\frac{1}{2} e^f \\sum_{\\begin{smallmatrix}n,m,p=0 \\\\ n+p=0 \\mod 2\\end{smallmatrix}}^{\\infty} \\frac{b^n}{n!} \\frac{c^m}{m!} \\frac{d^p}{p!} \\frac{\\Gamma \\left (\\frac{3n+2m+p+1}{4} \\right)}{(-a)^{\\frac{3n+2m+p+1}4}}.</math>\n\nThe ''n''&nbsp;+&nbsp;''p'' = 0 mod 2 requirement is because the integral from \u2212\u221e to 0 contributes a factor of (\u22121)<sup>''n''+''p''</sup>/2 to each term, while the integral from 0 to +\u221e contributes a factor of 1/2 to each term. These integrals turn up in subjects such as [[quantum field theory]].\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of integrals of Gaussian functions]]\n* [[Common integrals in quantum field theory]]\n* [[Normal distribution]]\n* [[List of integrals of exponential functions]]\n* [[Error function]]\n* [[Berezin integral]]\n\n== References ==\n=== Citations ===\n{{Reflist}}\n\n=== Sources ===\n{{refbegin}}\n* {{MathWorld |title = Gaussian Integral |urlname = GaussianIntegral }}\n* {{cite book |first=David |last=Griffiths |title=Introduction to Quantum Mechanics |edition=2nd }}\n* {{cite book |last=Abramowitz |first=M. |last2=Stegun |first2=I. A. |title = Handbook of Mathematical Functions |publisher=Dover Publications |location=New York }}\n{{refend}}\n\n{{-}}\n{{integral}}\n\n[[Category:Integrals]]\n[[Category:Articles containing proofs]]\n[[Category:Gaussian function]]\n[[Category:Theorems in analysis]]\n", "name_user": "Tvassilakis", "label": "safe", "comment": "correct the title of the referenced MAA article to \"The Evolution of the Normal Distribution\" from \"History of ...\"", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gaussian_integral"}
{"title_page": "200 yen note", "text_new": "{{short description|Japanese yen note}}\n{{Infobox banknote\n| denomination        = 200 yen note\n| country             = Japan\n| value               = 200\n| unit                = [[Japanese yen]]\n| width_mm            = \n| width_in            = \n| height_mm           = \n| height_in           = \n| weight_g            = \n| security_features   = [[Watermark]]s\n| paper_type          = \n| years_of_printing   = 1927\u20131946\n| obverse             = \n| obverse_design      = Various\n| obverse_designer    = \n| obverse_design_date = \n| reverse             = \n| reverse_design      = Various\n| reverse_designer    =\n| reverse_design_date = \n}}\n\n\nThe {{nihongo|'''200 yen note'''|\u4e8c\u767e\u5186\u7d19\u5e63}} was a denomination of [[Japanese yen]] issued from 1927 to 1946. These issues were broken up into three different designs including one which has two different varieties. For whatever reason two-hundred yen banknotes were not issued when they were first authorized. The first issuance came as the result of a financial emergency that took place in 1927. Second series notes were also printed for the emergency, but were placed in storage until the end of [[World War II]]. By the time these were released along with a 3rd series of notes, things were changing in Japan's monetary system. Currency could no longer be converted into gold coins making the messages on the long unreleased second series notes obsolete. An end to the series ultimately came in 1946, when all 200 yen bills were demonetized. These notes are now collectables which trade on the marketplace for amounts dependent on condition and rarity.\n\n==History==\nTwo hundred yen banknotes were first authorized by law on June 27, 1882 with Article 14 of the Bank of Japan.<ref name=\"CAHI5\">{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=smwn2UxgD8YC&pg=PA16&dq=200+yen+note&hl=en&newbks=1&newbks_redir=0&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwjnyLTtrPLnAhXBi54KHXsEAEcQ6AEwAnoECAAQAg#v=onepage&q=200%20yen%20note&f=false|title=Civil Affairs Handbook, Issue 5|publisher=United States. Army Service Forces|year=1943|page=15 & 16}}</ref> For one reason or another no notes were issued, and the [[United States Government Publishing Office|U.S. Government Printing Office]] added a footnote as late as 1901 stating: \"none have ever been issued\".<ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=2gpSAQAAMAAJ&pg=PA2296&dq=200+yen+note&hl=en&newbks=1&newbks_redir=0&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwjnyLTtrPLnAhXBi54KHXsEAEcQ6AEwBHoECAMQAg#v=onepage&q=200%20yen%20note&f=false|title=Summary of Foreign Commerce of the United States, Volume 2|publisher=U.S. Government Printing Office|year=1901|page=2296}}</ref> The first two hundred yen bills were eventually printed in response to the [[Sh\u014dwa financial crisis]] of 1927.<ref name=\"Kosen\">{{cite web|url=https://kosen-kantei.jp/varity/200-yen-bill/|title=\u3010\u4fdd\u5b58\u7248\u3011200\u5186\u672d\u306e\u4fa1\u5024\u306f\u3044\u304f\u3089\uff1f\u8cb7\u53d6\u4fa1\u683c\uff06\u5e73\u5747\u76f8\u5834\u300a\u51683\u7a2e\u985e\u300b|work=kosen-kantei.jp|accessdate=February 27, 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Asahi\">{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=sCdmBgAAQBAJ&pg=PA11&dq=200+yen+note&hl=en&newbks=1&newbks_redir=0&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwjnyLTtrPLnAhXBi54KHXsEAEcQ6AEwBnoECAYQAg#v=onepage&q=200%20yen%20note&f=false|title=Media, Propaganda and Politics in 20th-Century Japan|author=The Asahi Shimbun Company|publisher=Bloomsbury Publishing|year=2015|page=11}}</ref> The Bank of Japan needed bills to be exchanged with other banks, and decided to issue new 200 yen bills in a hurry to insure against [[bank run]]s.<ref name=\"NPB\">{{cite web|url=https://www.npb.go.jp/ja/museum/tenji/gallery/urajiro.html|title=\u88cf\u9762\u306e\u5370\u5237\u3092\u7701\u3044\u305f\u3000\u65e5\u672c\u9280\u884c\u514c\u63db\u5238\uff08\u3060\u304b\u3093\u3051\u3093\uff09\u3000\u4e59200\u5186|work=Banknote & Postage Stamp Museum|accessdate=February 27, 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"NN\">{{cite web|url=https://www.numismaticnews.net/article/world-notes-sell-for-1-3-million|title=World notes sell for $1.3 million|work=Numismatic News|date=October 1, 2018|accessdate=February 28, 2020}}</ref> With banks in the country all temporarily closed, the printing office took the opportunity to manufacture the new bills. The normal printing process could not be carried out as it took too long to print both sides of the note. To remedy this problem just one side received a simple design. These one sided bills were given the nickname \"Urashiro\" or \"back white\" notes.<ref name=\"NPB\"/><ref name=\"antique jp\">{{cite web|url=https://note.antique-coin.info/200yen/|title=\u65e5\u672c\u306e200\u5186\u672d(\u8cb3\u767e\u5713\u7d19\u5e63)\u306e\u4fa1\u5024\u3068\u8cb7\u53d6\u76f8\u5834|work=antique-coin.info|date=June 21, 2017|accessdate=February 27, 2020}}</ref> Although the backs of the new notes were blank, the Bank of Japan vice president confidently stated that: \"although it looks somewhat flimsy, it has the Bank of Japan watermark so there is no fear that it is counterfeit\".<ref name=\"NPB\"/> Despite his sentiment some of the notes were rejected as possible fakes due to their rough printing on the side that had features. Although 106,000 yen's worth of the 200 yen bill were reported to be in circulation at the end of 1927, by 1929 these notes were described as \"almost nonexistent\".<ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=MNF590eZrcMC&pg=RA22-PA26&dq=200+yen+note&hl=en&newbks=1&newbks_redir=0&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwjnyLTtrPLnAhXBi54KHXsEAEcQ6AEwAHoECAEQAg#v=onepage&q=200%20yen%20note&f=false|title=Trade Information Bulletin, Issues 651-675|publisher=U.S. Government Printing Office|year=1929|page=26}}</ref>\n\nNotes of the second series were announced by the [[Ministry of Finance (Japan)|Ministry of Finance]] in 1927, and were printed the same year in two different varieties. All of these notes are called \"Uraaka\" due to the red pattern featured on the reverse side, while the obverse side features Legendary Japanese hero-statesman [[Takenouchi no Sukune]].<ref name=\"antique jp\"/> A majority of the second series banknotes were held back in vaults until the end of [[World War II]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://currency.ha.com/itm/world-currency/japan-bank-of-japan-200-yen-nd-1945-pick-43aa-jnda-11-43-pcgs-extremely-fine-45/a/4013-26080.s?type=Biddr4013|title=Japan Bank of Japan 200 Yen ND (1945) Pick 43Aa|work=Heritage Auctions|accessdate=March 2, 2020}}</ref> The first variety has a black on green underprint on the obverse, the word \"SPECIMAN\" is written in red script on the reverse. Second variety notes can be differentiated by a pale blue underprint on the obverse, these notes also feature a different color and shape of the central [[guilloche]].<ref name=\"HA1927V1\">{{cite web|url=https://coins.ha.com/itm/world-paper-money/japan-1927-nd-issue-200-yen-p-38-specimen/a/3015-24466.s?ic16=ViewItem-BrowseTabs-Auction-Archive-ThisAuction-120115|title=Japan: Japan 1927 ND Issue 200 Yen P-38 Specimen|work=[[Heritage Auctions]]|accessdate=March 2, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.banknote.ws/COLLECTION/countries/ASI/JAP/JAP0043A2.htm|title=200 Yen ND (1945) 43a|work=www.banknote.ws|accessdate=March 2, 2020}}</ref> There is no mention of the word \"SPECIMAN\" on the reverse which has a slightly different red back pattern.<ref name=\"antique jp\"/> There is a message on the obverse side of both varieties that mentions the note as \"Bond convertible\". By the time the second series was finally issued on August 16, 1945 this message had become dated as the system of converting banknotes into gold coins had been suspended in 1942.<ref name=\"CAHI5\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.imes.boj.or.jp/cm/english/history/content/|title=The History of Japanese Currency|work=[[Bank of Japan]]|accessdate=March 2, 2020}}</ref>\n\nSeries three notes feature [[Fujiwara no Kamatari]] on the obverse next to [[Danzan Shrine]], the reverse designs are printed in blue ink which include another shrine view.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://coins.ha.com/itm/world-paper-money/japan-1945nd-issue-200-yen-p-44s3-specimen/a/3015-24469.s?ic16=ViewItem-BrowseTabs-Auction-Archive-ThisAuction-120115|title=Japan 1945ND Issue 200 Yen P-44s3 Specimen|work=Heritage Auctions|accessdate=March 2, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.banknote.ws/COLLECTION/countries/ASI/JAP/JAP0044.htm|title= \n200 Yen ND (1945) 44a|work=www.banknote.ws|accessdate=March 2, 2020}}</ref> These notes were originally part of an overall banknote redesign which took place in 1930, like the previous series these were also issued after World War II had ended. This last series saw light circulation due to the purchasing power the note had at the time.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://currency.ha.com/itm/world-currency/japan-bank-of-japan-200-yen-nd-1945-pick-44a/a/3555-26752.s|title=Japan Bank of Japan 200 Yen ND (1945) Pick 44a.|work=Heritage Auctions|accessdate=March 2, 2020}}</ref> These last two series were short lived issues as they would both expire within a year as Japan's monetary system changed. On March 2, 1946 a new law was passed which demonetized all of Japan's old currency, stripping all 200 yen notes of their legal tender status.<ref name=\"Demonetized\">{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=-lvmhcXrIj4C&pg=PA354&lpg=PA354&dq=March+2,+1946+bank+of+Japan&source=bl&ots=aOhhA2LWAY&sig=ACfU3U0gn5J0gaJ9q-fiu4TEohUMcL67ZA&hl=en&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwjm1-DVr_znAhVLKKwKHYyZB4gQ6AEwAHoECAgQAQ#v=onepage&q=March%202%2C%201946%20bank%20of%20Japan&f=false|title=The Economic History of Japan, 1600-1990: Economic history of Japan, 1914-1955 : a dual structure|author=Nakamura, Odaka|publisher=Oxford University Press|year=2003|page=354}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=REQbAAAAMAAJ&q=March+2,+1946+bank+of+Japan&dq=March+2,+1946+bank+of+Japan&hl=en&newbks=1&newbks_redir=0&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwiawrODsvznAhVudt8KHcUDBOwQ6AEwAnoECAAQAg|title=Financial and Monetary Situation in Post-war Japan|author=Hy\u014de \u014cuchi|publisher=Nihon Taiheiyo Mondai Chosakai|year=1948|page=22|quote=Bank of Japan Notes stipulated that any person holding such notes must deposit them with the banks by March 2, 1946}}</ref>{{efn|Financial institutions accepted old bills as deposits until March 7, 1946. The redemption process of old notes for new ones (excluding 200 yen notes) had been ongoing since the end of February 1946.<ref name=\"Demonetized\"/>}} \n\n==Collectability==\nNotes printed in 1927 for the first series are very rare today as very few were issued. [[Specimen banknote]]s are among the few examples available for collectors to obtain, with prices ranging from $19,550 ([[United States dollar|USD]]) in \"about uncirculated\" condition, to $33,600 (USD) for a \"gem\" example.<ref name=\"NN\"/> Two hundred yen notes of the second series first variety are considered to be extremely rare.<ref name=\"HA1927V1\"/> The second variety had a print run of 7.5 million notes which were stocked in the vaults, making them more available to collectors. These notes have been sold at auction in the hundreds of [[United States dollar|dollar]]s to the low thousands depending on condition.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://currency.ha.com/itm/world-currency/japan-bank-of-japan-200-yen-nd-1945-pick-43as1-jnda-11-43-specimen-pmg-about-uncirculated-53-net/a/4013-26081.s?type=Biddr4013|title=Bank of Japan 200 Yen ND (1945) Pick 43As1 JNDA 11-43 Specimen PMG About Uncirculated 53 Net|work=Heritage Auctions|date=March 2, 2020}}</ref> Series three notes are also more available to collectors selling in the hundreds of dollars.\n\n==In popular culture==\nThe announcement of redesigned \"Series F\" banknotes for release in 2024 inspired a Japanese artist to create 200 yen bank notes using a [[kitten]] theme.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://prtimes.jp/main/html/rd/p/000000016.000031510.html|title=\u30cb\u30e3\u30f3\u3068\u3082\u53ef\u611b\u3044\u5b50\u732b\u9054\u304c\u4e8c\u767e\u5186\u672d\u306b\u306a\u308a\u307e\u3057\u305f\uff01\u300c\u5b50\u732b\u7d19\u5e63\u300d\u5404\u7a2e\u96d1\u8ca8\u5546\u54c1\u306e\u8ca9\u58f2\u958b\u59cb\u306e\u304a\u77e5\u3089\u305b|work=prtimes.jp|date=October 10, 2019|accessdate=February 27, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://soranews24.com/2019/10/12/japanese-artist-creates-cat-banknote-alternative-kittens-on-200-yen/|title=Japanese artist creates cat banknote alternative: Kittens on 200 yen|author=Oona McGee|publisher=Sora News|date=October 24, 2019|accessdate=February 27, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n*[[Banknotes of the Japanese yen]]\n*[[2000 yen note]]\n\n==Notes==\n{{notelist}}\n\n==References==\n{{Portal|Japan|Money|Numismatics}}\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Japanese currency and coinage}}\n\n[[Category:Banknotes of Japan]]\n[[Category:Japanese yen]]\n[[Category:Two-hundred-base-unit banknotes]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Japanese yen note}}\n\n{{Infobox banknote\n| denomination        = 200 yen note\n| country             = Japan\n| value               = 200\n| unit                = [[Japanese yen]]\n| width_mm            = \n| width_in            = \n| height_mm           = \n| height_in           = \n| weight_g            = \n| security_features   = [[Watermark]]s\n| paper_type          = \n| years_of_printing   = 1927\u20131946\n| obverse             = \n| obverse_design      = Various\n| obverse_designer    = \n| obverse_design_date = \n| reverse             = \n| reverse_design      = Various\n| reverse_designer    =\n| reverse_design_date = \n}}\n\n\nThe {{nihongo|'''200 yen note'''|\u4e8c\u767e\u5186\u7d19\u5e63}} was a denomination of [[Japanese yen]] issued from 1927 to 1946. These issues were broken up into three different designs including one which has two different varieties. For whatever reason two-hundred yen banknotes were not issued when they were first authorized. The first issuance came as the result of a financial emergency that took place in 1927. Second series notes were also printed for the emergency, but were placed in storage until the end of [[World War II]]. By the time these were released along with a 3rd series of notes, things were changing in Japan's monetary system. Currency could no longer be converted into gold coins making the messages on the long unreleased second series notes obsolete. An end to the series ultimately came in 1946, when all 200 yen bills were demonetized. These notes are now collectables which trade on the marketplace for amounts dependent on condition and rarity.\n\n==History==\nTwo hundred yen banknotes were first authorized by law on June 27, 1882 with Article 14 of the Bank of Japan.<ref name=\"CAHI5\">{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=smwn2UxgD8YC&pg=PA16&dq=200+yen+note&hl=en&newbks=1&newbks_redir=0&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwjnyLTtrPLnAhXBi54KHXsEAEcQ6AEwAnoECAAQAg#v=onepage&q=200%20yen%20note&f=false|title=Civil Affairs Handbook, Issue 5|publisher=United States. Army Service Forces|year=1943|page=15 & 16}}</ref> For one reason or another no notes were issued, and the [[United States Government Publishing Office|U.S. Government Printing Office]] added a footnote as late as 1901 stating: \"none have ever been issued\".<ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=2gpSAQAAMAAJ&pg=PA2296&dq=200+yen+note&hl=en&newbks=1&newbks_redir=0&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwjnyLTtrPLnAhXBi54KHXsEAEcQ6AEwBHoECAMQAg#v=onepage&q=200%20yen%20note&f=false|title=Summary of Foreign Commerce of the United States, Volume 2|publisher=U.S. Government Printing Office|year=1901|page=2296}}</ref> The first two hundred yen bills were eventually printed in response to the [[Sh\u014dwa financial crisis]] of 1927.<ref name=\"Kosen\">{{cite web|url=https://kosen-kantei.jp/varity/200-yen-bill/|title=\u3010\u4fdd\u5b58\u7248\u3011200\u5186\u672d\u306e\u4fa1\u5024\u306f\u3044\u304f\u3089\uff1f\u8cb7\u53d6\u4fa1\u683c\uff06\u5e73\u5747\u76f8\u5834\u300a\u51683\u7a2e\u985e\u300b|work=kosen-kantei.jp|accessdate=February 27, 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Asahi\">{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=sCdmBgAAQBAJ&pg=PA11&dq=200+yen+note&hl=en&newbks=1&newbks_redir=0&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwjnyLTtrPLnAhXBi54KHXsEAEcQ6AEwBnoECAYQAg#v=onepage&q=200%20yen%20note&f=false|title=Media, Propaganda and Politics in 20th-Century Japan|author=The Asahi Shimbun Company|publisher=Bloomsbury Publishing|year=2015|page=11}}</ref> The Bank of Japan needed bills to be exchanged with other banks, and decided to issue new 200 yen bills in a hurry to insure against [[bank run]]s.<ref name=\"NPB\">{{cite web|url=https://www.npb.go.jp/ja/museum/tenji/gallery/urajiro.html|title=\u88cf\u9762\u306e\u5370\u5237\u3092\u7701\u3044\u305f\u3000\u65e5\u672c\u9280\u884c\u514c\u63db\u5238\uff08\u3060\u304b\u3093\u3051\u3093\uff09\u3000\u4e59200\u5186|work=Banknote & Postage Stamp Museum|accessdate=February 27, 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"NN\">{{cite web|url=https://www.numismaticnews.net/article/world-notes-sell-for-1-3-million|title=World notes sell for $1.3 million|work=Numismatic News|date=October 1, 2018|accessdate=February 28, 2020}}</ref> With banks in the country all temporarily closed, the printing office took the opportunity to manufacture the new bills. The normal printing process could not be carried out as it took too long to print both sides of the note. To remedy this problem just one side received a simple design. These one sided bills were given the nickname \"Urashiro\" or \"back white\" notes.<ref name=\"NPB\"/><ref name=\"antique jp\">{{cite web|url=https://note.antique-coin.info/200yen/|title=\u65e5\u672c\u306e200\u5186\u672d(\u8cb3\u767e\u5713\u7d19\u5e63)\u306e\u4fa1\u5024\u3068\u8cb7\u53d6\u76f8\u5834|work=antique-coin.info|date=June 21, 2017|accessdate=February 27, 2020}}</ref> Although the backs of the new notes were blank, the Bank of Japan vice president confidently stated that: \"although it looks somewhat flimsy, it has the Bank of Japan watermark so there is no fear that it is counterfeit\".<ref name=\"NPB\"/> Despite his sentiment some of the notes were rejected as possible fakes due to their rough printing on the side that had features. Although 106,000 yen's worth of the 200 yen bill were reported to be in circulation at the end of 1927, by 1929 these notes were described as \"almost nonexistent\".<ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=MNF590eZrcMC&pg=RA22-PA26&dq=200+yen+note&hl=en&newbks=1&newbks_redir=0&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwjnyLTtrPLnAhXBi54KHXsEAEcQ6AEwAHoECAEQAg#v=onepage&q=200%20yen%20note&f=false|title=Trade Information Bulletin, Issues 651-675|publisher=U.S. Government Printing Office|year=1929|page=26}}</ref>\n\nNotes of the second series were announced by the [[Ministry of Finance (Japan)|Ministry of Finance]] in 1927, and were printed the same year in two different varieties. All of these notes are called \"Uraaka\" due to the red pattern featured on the reverse side, while the obverse side features Legendary Japanese hero-statesman [[Takenouchi no Sukune]].<ref name=\"antique jp\"/> A majority of the second series banknotes were held back in vaults until the end of [[World War II]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://currency.ha.com/itm/world-currency/japan-bank-of-japan-200-yen-nd-1945-pick-43aa-jnda-11-43-pcgs-extremely-fine-45/a/4013-26080.s?type=Biddr4013|title=Japan Bank of Japan 200 Yen ND (1945) Pick 43Aa|work=Heritage Auctions|accessdate=March 2, 2020}}</ref> The first variety has a black on green underprint on the obverse, the word \"SPECIMAN\" is written in red script on the reverse. Second variety notes can be differentiated by a pale blue underprint on the obverse, these notes also feature a different color and shape of the central [[guilloche]].<ref name=\"HA1927V1\">{{cite web|url=https://coins.ha.com/itm/world-paper-money/japan-1927-nd-issue-200-yen-p-38-specimen/a/3015-24466.s?ic16=ViewItem-BrowseTabs-Auction-Archive-ThisAuction-120115|title=Japan: Japan 1927 ND Issue 200 Yen P-38 Specimen|work=[[Heritage Auctions]]|accessdate=March 2, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.banknote.ws/COLLECTION/countries/ASI/JAP/JAP0043A2.htm|title=200 Yen ND (1945) 43a|work=www.banknote.ws|accessdate=March 2, 2020}}</ref> There is no mention of the word \"SPECIMAN\" on the reverse which has a slightly different red back pattern.<ref name=\"antique jp\"/> There is a message on the obverse side of both varieties that mentions the note as \"Bond convertible\". By the time the second series was finally issued on August 16, 1945 this message had become dated as the system of converting banknotes into gold coins had been suspended in 1942.<ref name=\"CAHI5\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.imes.boj.or.jp/cm/english/history/content/|title=The History of Japanese Currency|work=[[Bank of Japan]]|accessdate=March 2, 2020}}</ref>\n\nSeries three notes feature [[Fujiwara no Kamatari]] on the obverse next to [[Danzan Shrine]], the reverse designs are printed in blue ink which include another shrine view.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://coins.ha.com/itm/world-paper-money/japan-1945nd-issue-200-yen-p-44s3-specimen/a/3015-24469.s?ic16=ViewItem-BrowseTabs-Auction-Archive-ThisAuction-120115|title=Japan 1945ND Issue 200 Yen P-44s3 Specimen|work=Heritage Auctions|accessdate=March 2, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.banknote.ws/COLLECTION/countries/ASI/JAP/JAP0044.htm|title= \n200 Yen ND (1945) 44a|work=www.banknote.ws|accessdate=March 2, 2020}}</ref> These notes were originally part of an overall banknote redesign which took place in 1930, like the previous series these were also issued after World War II had ended. This last series saw light circulation due to the purchasing power the note had at the time.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://currency.ha.com/itm/world-currency/japan-bank-of-japan-200-yen-nd-1945-pick-44a/a/3555-26752.s|title=Japan Bank of Japan 200 Yen ND (1945) Pick 44a.|work=Heritage Auctions|accessdate=March 2, 2020}}</ref> These last two series were short lived issues as they would both expire within a year as Japan's monetary system changed. On March 2, 1946 a new law was passed which demonetized all of Japan's old currency, stripping all 200 yen notes of their legal tender status.<ref name=\"Demonetized\">{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=-lvmhcXrIj4C&pg=PA354&lpg=PA354&dq=March+2,+1946+bank+of+Japan&source=bl&ots=aOhhA2LWAY&sig=ACfU3U0gn5J0gaJ9q-fiu4TEohUMcL67ZA&hl=en&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwjm1-DVr_znAhVLKKwKHYyZB4gQ6AEwAHoECAgQAQ#v=onepage&q=March%202%2C%201946%20bank%20of%20Japan&f=false|title=The Economic History of Japan, 1600-1990: Economic history of Japan, 1914-1955 : a dual structure|author=Nakamura, Odaka|publisher=Oxford University Press|year=2003|page=354}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=REQbAAAAMAAJ&q=March+2,+1946+bank+of+Japan&dq=March+2,+1946+bank+of+Japan&hl=en&newbks=1&newbks_redir=0&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwiawrODsvznAhVudt8KHcUDBOwQ6AEwAnoECAAQAg|title=Financial and Monetary Situation in Post-war Japan|author=Hy\u014de \u014cuchi|publisher=Nihon Taiheiyo Mondai Chosakai|year=1948|page=22|quote=Bank of Japan Notes stipulated that any person holding such notes must deposit them with the banks by March 2, 1946}}</ref>{{efn|Financial institutions accepted old bills as deposits until March 7, 1946. The redemption process of old notes for new ones (excluding 200 yen notes) had been ongoing since the end of February 1946.<ref name=\"Demonetized\"/>}} \n\n==Collectability==\nNotes printed in 1927 for the first series are very rare today as very few were issued. [[Specimen banknote]]s are among the few examples available for collectors to obtain, with prices ranging from $19,550 ([[United States dollar|USD]]) in \"about uncirculated\" condition, to $33,600 (USD) for a \"gem\" example.<ref name=\"NN\"/> Two hundred yen notes of the second series first variety are considered to be extremely rare.<ref name=\"HA1927V1\"/> The second variety had a print run of 7.5 million notes which were stocked in the vaults, making them more available to collectors. These notes have been sold at auction in the hundreds of [[United States dollar|dollar]]s to the low thousands depending on condition.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://currency.ha.com/itm/world-currency/japan-bank-of-japan-200-yen-nd-1945-pick-43as1-jnda-11-43-specimen-pmg-about-uncirculated-53-net/a/4013-26081.s?type=Biddr4013|title=Bank of Japan 200 Yen ND (1945) Pick 43As1 JNDA 11-43 Specimen PMG About Uncirculated 53 Net|work=Heritage Auctions|date=March 2, 2020}}</ref> Series three notes are also more available to collectors selling in the hundreds of dollars.\n\n==In popular culture==\nThe announcement of redesigned \"Series F\" banknotes for release in 2024 inspired a Japanese artist to create 200 yen bank notes using a [[kitten]] theme.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://prtimes.jp/main/html/rd/p/000000016.000031510.html|title=\u30cb\u30e3\u30f3\u3068\u3082\u53ef\u611b\u3044\u5b50\u732b\u9054\u304c\u4e8c\u767e\u5186\u672d\u306b\u306a\u308a\u307e\u3057\u305f\uff01\u300c\u5b50\u732b\u7d19\u5e63\u300d\u5404\u7a2e\u96d1\u8ca8\u5546\u54c1\u306e\u8ca9\u58f2\u958b\u59cb\u306e\u304a\u77e5\u3089\u305b|work=prtimes.jp|date=October 10, 2019|accessdate=February 27, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://soranews24.com/2019/10/12/japanese-artist-creates-cat-banknote-alternative-kittens-on-200-yen/|title=Japanese artist creates cat banknote alternative: Kittens on 200 yen|author=Oona McGee|publisher=Sora News|date=October 24, 2019|accessdate=February 27, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n*[[Banknotes of the Japanese yen]]\n*[[2000 yen note]]\n\n==Notes==\n{{notelist}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Japanese currency and coinage}}\n\n[[Category:Banknotes of Japan]]\n[[Category:Japanese yen]]\n[[Category:Two-hundred-base-unit banknotes]]\n", "name_user": "NewHikaru07", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/200_yen_note"}
{"title_page": "Second Battle of Vailele", "text_new": "{{Infobox military conflict\n|conflict= Second Battle of Vailele\n|partof=the [[Second Samoan Civil War]]\n|image=Samoa warriors.jpg\n|image_size=300px\n|caption=''Samoan warriors marching through Apia in March of 1899, American sailors and marines  are inspecting at the left.''\n|date=April 1, 1899\n|place=[[Vailele]], [[Upolu]], [[Samoa]]\n|coordinates=\n|result= Mata'afan victory\n|combatant1=''[[Allies of the Second Samoan Civil War|Allies]]:''<br/>{{flagicon image|Flag of Samoa (1879).svg}} [[History of Samoa#19th century|Samoa]]<br/>{{flagcountry|UKGBI}}<br/>{{flag|United States|1896}}\n|combatant2={{flagicon image|Flag of Samoa (1879).svg}} [[Mata'afa Iosefo|Mataafans]]<br/>'''Supported by:'''<br/>{{flagcountry|German Empire}}\n|commander1={{flagicon|UKGBI}} [[Angel Hope Freeman|Angel Freeman]]{{KIA}}<br/>{{flagicon|United States|1896}} [[Philip Lansdale]]{{KIA}}\n|commander2={{flagicon image|Flag of Samoa (1879).svg}} [[Mata'afa Iosefo]]\n|strength1='''Land:'''<br/>136 [[warrior]]s<br/>26 [[Marine (military)|marine]]s<br/>88 [[sailor]]s<br/>'''Sea:'''<br/>1 [[corvette]]\n|strength2=~800 warriors<br/>2 [[fort]]s\n|casualties1=7 killed<br/>7 wounded\n|casualties2=~100 killed or wounded<br/>2 forts damaged\n}}\n{{Campaignbox\n| name =Campaignbox Second Samoan Civil War\n| title=[[Second Samoan Civil War]]\n| battles = [[Siege of Apia|Apia]] {{\u00b7}} [[Battle of Falefa|Falefa]] {{\u00b7}} [[Battle of Falefa|Falefa]] {{\u00b7}} 2nd Vailele {{\u00b7}} [[Third Battle of Vailele|3rd Vailele]] {{\u00b7}} [[Second Battle of Apia|2nd Apia]]\n}}\n\nThe''' Second''' '''Battle of Vailele''' was fought during the [[Second Samoan Civil War]] in 1899. [[United Kingdom|British]], [[United States|American]] and [[Samoa]]n forces loyal to [[Prince Tanu]] were defeated by a superior force of Samoan rebels loyal to [[Mata'afa Iosefo]]. Fighting occurred at the former [[German Empire|German]] plantation of [[Vailele]], [[Samoa]] and was a major engagement of the small [[colonial war|colonial conflict]].<ref>Mains, pg. 24</ref>\n\n==Background==\nIn 1899, Samoa was a warzone as it had been previously during the [[First Samoan Civil War]]. As result of [[Malietoa Laupepa]]'s death, Mata'afa Iosefo returned from exile and was elected to power by a council of Samoan [[tribal chief|chiefs]]. In response, the British [[Royal Navy]] and the [[United States Navy|U.S. Navy]] landed forces at [[Apia]] in support of Prince Tanu who was the legitimate heir to the Samoan throne which had already been taken over by the German-backed Mataafa.\n\nThe [[Siege of Apia|first battle]] of the conflict involving the British and Americans was fought at Apia, when the naval forces landed they occupied much of the city, Mataafan forces attacked, so British and American warships in [[Apia Harbour]] began bombarding enemy positions around the city. After the conflict, Mataafaite forces, as they were sometimes called, retreated to the stronghold of Vailele and thus began several American and British expeditions into the dense jungle to find the chief's men.<ref>Mains, pg. 24</ref>\n\nAt the end of March, a joint expedition of British, American and Samoan forces marched along the coast from Apia towards Vailele. Skirmishes were fought and two villages destroyed as the Samoan rebels retreated. On April 1, the expedition of 26 marines, 88 sailors and 136 Samoans left the coast for an attack on the landward side of Vailele, leaving the protection of naval gunfire support. The [[cruiser]]s {{USS|Philadelphia|C-4|6}}, [[HMS Phoenix (1889)|HMS ''Tauranga'']], {{HMS|Porpoise|1886|6}} and the [[corvette]] {{HMS|Royalist|1883|6}} landed the sailors and marines, ''Royalist'' was sent ahead of the expedition to bombard the two forts guarding Vailele plantation.<ref>Mains, pg. 24</ref>\n\n==Battle==\n[[File:Samoan paramount chief Mataafa 1911.jpg|150px|right|thumb|''Mata'afa Iosefo in 1911.'']]\nWhen the landing party approached the plantation, HMS ''Royalist'' ceased her bombardment, and just then the land force, under the command of Royal Navy [[Lieutenant]] [[Angel Hope Freeman]] and American Lieutenant [[Philip Lansdale]], was ambushed by over 800 riflemen hidden all around in the foliage of the jungle. The expedition quickly began returning volleys and the Americans set up a [[M1895 Colt-Browning machine gun|Colt machine gun]]. Mataafan forces first attacked the allied column from the rear and from the left flank. Lieutenant Freeman was killed and beheaded just after fighting began, he was hit by [[sniper]]s hiding among palm and banana trees. The rebels then charged and Lieutenant Landsdale took command. Close quarters combat and skirmishing continued for a while, the rebel Samoans repeatedly attacked the expedition's front line and several of them were killed or wounded. The machine gun jammed after firing only a few shots and as Lieutenant Landsdale attempted to fix the problem, a shot hit him in the thigh and he fell to the ground with his bone shattered. A retreat was sounded, and Landsdale ordered his men to save themselves so the expedition began to fall back which left the lieutenant alone under heavy fire. Refusing to leave his commander, [[Ensign (rank)|Ensign]] [[John R. Monaghan]], picked up a rifle and with three others, went after Landsdale and when they were carrying him out of action, [[Seaman (rank)|Seaman]] [[Norman Edsall]] was shot and killed.<ref>Mains, pg. 24</ref>\n\nOnce again, Landsdale ordered his rescuers to flee but they held their ground waiting for reinforcements and were killed by fast approaching Samoan rebels. After the battle, Landsdale and Monaghan were found dead side by side and the expedition retreated to the coast having suffered many casualties which were accounted for the following morning. During the withdrawal, HMS ''Royalist'' resumed fire and bombarded the bush from which the Mataafans were attacking. Samoan rebel forces lost 100 killed or wounded while the expedition's casualties were much lighter in comparison. Of the 56 American sailors and marines at the battle, four were killed and another five were wounded. The British lost three men killed, out of sixty-two men engaged, two others were wounded. Federal Samoan casualties were light if any. They were under American command and most deserted at the sound of the first volley, the remaining were used to reinforce the front line. Later patrols reported finding large pools of blood behind the banana trees, evidence of rebel casualties. Two marine privates, [[Henry L. Hulbert]] and [[Michael Joseph McNally]] received the Medal of Honor for their actions during the fighting.<ref>Mains, pg. 24</ref>\n\n==Aftermath==\nThe battle was a defeat for the expeditionary forces, they retreated back to Apia and reported their casualties to their commanders who decided to plan for future operations in the area. On April 13, the British frontline was extended just south of Vailele and that day the Matafaans attacked but were repulsed. Another expedition later [[Third Battle of Vailele|fought]] again within Vailele, this time the rebels won again when they withstood a British led attack on the two forts. The engagements occurred near the battlefield where Samoan rebels [[Battle of Vailele (1889)|defeated]] German troops in 1889 during the first civil war on the island. A statue of Ensign Monaghan was erected in [[Spokane, Washington]] to commemorate the young officer's bravery.<ref>Mains, pg. 24</ref> The official report of Monaghan's death reads; \n:\"''The men were not in sufficient numbers to hold out any longer, and they were forced along by a fire which it was impossible to withstand. Ensign Monaghan did stand. He stood steadfast by his wounded superior and friend - one rifle against many, one brave man against a score .... He knew he was doomed. He could not yield. He died in heroic performance of duty.''\"\n\n==Notes==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==References==\n*{{cite book|last=Mains|first=P. John|authorlink=|author2=McCarty, Louis Philippe |edition=|title= The Statistician and Economist: Volume 23|year=1906|publisher=|location=|isbn=}}\n\n{{coord missing|Samoa}}\n{{Authority control}}\n[[Category:Battles of the Second Samoan Civil War|Vailele]]\n[[Category:1899 in Samoa]]\n[[Category:April 1899 events]]\n[[Category:Tuamasaga]]\n[[Category:Battles of the Second Samoan Civil War involving the United States|Vailele, Second]]\n[[Category:Battles of the Second Samoan Civil War involving the United Kingdom|Vailele]]\n[[Category:Punitive expeditions of the United States|Vailele]]\n[[Category:Punitive expeditions of the United Kingdom|Vailele]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox military conflict\n|conflict= Second Battle of Vailele\n|partof=the [[Second Samoan Civil War]]\n|image=Samoa warriors.jpg\n|image_size=300px\n|caption=''Samoan warriors marching through Apia in March of 1899, American sailors and marines  are inspecting at the left.''\n|date=April 1, 1899\n|place=[[Vailele]], [[Upolu]], [[Samoa]]\n|coordinates=\n|result= Mataafan victory\n|combatant1=''[[Allies of the Second Samoan Civil War|Allies]]:''<br/>{{flagicon image|Flag of Samoa (1879).svg}} [[History of Samoa#19th century|Samoa]]<br/>{{flagcountry|UKGBI}}<br/>{{flag|United States|1896}}\n|combatant2={{flagicon image|Flag of Samoa (1879).svg}} [[Mata'afa Iosefo|Mataafans]]<br/>'''Supported by:'''<br/>{{flagcountry|German Empire}}\n|commander1={{flagicon|UKGBI}} [[Angel Hope Freeman|Angel Freeman]]{{KIA}}<br/>{{flagicon|United States|1896}} [[Philip Lansdale]]{{KIA}}\n|commander2={{flagicon image|Flag of Samoa (1879).svg}} [[Mata'afa Iosefo]]\n|strength1='''Land:'''<br/>136 [[warrior]]s<br/>26 [[Marine (military)|marine]]s<br/>88 [[sailor]]s<br/>'''Sea:'''<br/>1 [[corvette]]\n|strength2=~800 warriors<br/>2 [[fort]]s\n|casualties1=7 killed<br/>7 wounded\n|casualties2=~100 killed or wounded<br/>2 forts damaged\n}}\n{{Campaignbox\n| name =Campaignbox Second Samoan Civil War\n| title=[[Second Samoan Civil War]]\n| battles = [[Siege of Apia|Apia]] {{\u00b7}} [[Battle of Falefa|Falefa]] {{\u00b7}} [[Battle of Falefa|Falefa]] {{\u00b7}} 2nd Vailele {{\u00b7}} [[Third Battle of Vailele|3rd Vailele]] {{\u00b7}} [[Second Battle of Apia|2nd Apia]]\n}}\n\nThe''' Second''' '''Battle of Vailele''' was fought during the [[Second Samoan Civil War]] in 1899. [[United Kingdom|British]], [[United States|American]] and [[Samoa]]n forces loyal to [[Prince Tanu]] were defeated by a superior force of Samoan rebels loyal to [[Mata'afa Iosefo]]. Fighting occurred at the former [[German Empire|German]] plantation of [[Vailele]], [[Samoa]] and was a major engagement of the small [[colonial war|colonial conflict]].<ref>Mains, pg. 24</ref>\n\n==Background==\nIn 1899, Samoa was a warzone as it had been previously during the [[First Samoan Civil War]]. As result of [[Malietoa Laupepa]]'s death, Mata'afa Iosefo returned from exile and was elected to power by a council of Samoan [[tribal chief|chiefs]]. In response, the British [[Royal Navy]] and the [[United States Navy|U.S. Navy]] landed forces at [[Apia]] in support of Prince Tanu who was the legitimate heir to the Samoan throne which had already been taken over by the German-backed Mataafa.\n\nThe [[Siege of Apia|first battle]] of the conflict involving the British and Americans was fought at Apia, when the naval forces landed they occupied much of the city, Mataafan forces attacked, so British and American warships in [[Apia Harbour]] began bombarding enemy positions around the city. After the conflict, Mataafaite forces, as they were sometimes called, retreated to the stronghold of Vailele and thus began several American and British expeditions into the dense jungle to find the chief's men.<ref>Mains, pg. 24</ref>\n\nAt the end of March, a joint expedition of British, American and Samoan forces marched along the coast from Apia towards Vailele. Skirmishes were fought and two villages destroyed as the Samoan rebels retreated. On April 1, the expedition of 26 marines, 88 sailors and 136 Samoans left the coast for an attack on the landward side of Vailele, leaving the protection of naval gunfire support. The [[cruiser]]s {{USS|Philadelphia|C-4|6}}, [[HMS Phoenix (1889)|HMS ''Tauranga'']], {{HMS|Porpoise|1886|6}} and the [[corvette]] {{HMS|Royalist|1883|6}} landed the sailors and marines, ''Royalist'' was sent ahead of the expedition to bombard the two forts guarding Vailele plantation.<ref>Mains, pg. 24</ref>\n\n==Battle==\n[[File:Samoan paramount chief Mataafa 1911.jpg|150px|right|thumb|''Mata'afa Iosefo in 1911.'']]\nWhen the landing party approached the plantation, HMS ''Royalist'' ceased her bombardment, and just then the land force, under the command of Royal Navy [[Lieutenant]] [[Angel Hope Freeman]] and American Lieutenant [[Philip Lansdale]], was ambushed by over 800 riflemen hidden all around in the foliage of the jungle. The expedition quickly began returning volleys and the Americans set up a [[M1895 Colt-Browning machine gun|Colt machine gun]]. Mataafan forces first attacked the allied column from the rear and from the left flank. Lieutenant Freeman was killed and beheaded just after fighting began, he was hit by [[sniper]]s hiding among palm and banana trees. The rebels then charged and Lieutenant Landsdale took command. Close quarters combat and skirmishing continued for a while, the rebel Samoans repeatedly attacked the expedition's front line and several of them were killed or wounded. The machine gun jammed after firing only a few shots and as Lieutenant Landsdale attempted to fix the problem, a shot hit him in the thigh and he fell to the ground with his bone shattered. A retreat was sounded, and Landsdale ordered his men to save themselves so the expedition began to fall back which left the lieutenant alone under heavy fire. Refusing to leave his commander, [[Ensign (rank)|Ensign]] [[John R. Monaghan]], picked up a rifle and with three others, went after Landsdale and when they were carrying him out of action, [[Seaman (rank)|Seaman]] [[Norman Edsall]] was shot and killed.<ref>Mains, pg. 24</ref>\n\nOnce again, Landsdale ordered his rescuers to flee but they held their ground waiting for reinforcements and were killed by fast approaching Samoan rebels. After the battle, Landsdale and Monaghan were found dead side by side and the expedition retreated to the coast having suffered many casualties which were accounted for the following morning. During the withdrawal, HMS ''Royalist'' resumed fire and bombarded the bush from which the Mataafans were attacking. Samoan rebel forces lost 100 killed or wounded while the expedition's casualties were much lighter in comparison. Of the 56 American sailors and marines at the battle, four were killed and another five were wounded. The British lost three men killed, out of sixty-two men engaged, two others were wounded. Federal Samoan casualties were light if any. They were under American command and most deserted at the sound of the first volley, the remaining were used to reinforce the front line. Later patrols reported finding large pools of blood behind the banana trees, evidence of rebel casualties. Two marine privates, [[Henry L. Hulbert]] and [[Michael Joseph McNally]] received the Medal of Honor for their actions during the fighting.<ref>Mains, pg. 24</ref>\n\n==Aftermath==\nThe battle was a defeat for the expeditionary forces, they retreated back to Apia and reported their casualties to their commanders who decided to plan for future operations in the area. On April 13, the British frontline was extended just south of Vailele and that day the Matafaans attacked but were repulsed. Another expedition later [[Third Battle of Vailele|fought]] again within Vailele, this time the rebels won again when they withstood a British led attack on the two forts. The engagements occurred near the battlefield where Samoan rebels [[Battle of Vailele (1889)|defeated]] German troops in 1889 during the first civil war on the island. A statue of Ensign Monaghan was erected in [[Spokane, Washington]] to commemorate the young officer's bravery.<ref>Mains, pg. 24</ref> The official report of Monaghan's death reads; \n:\"''The men were not in sufficient numbers to hold out any longer, and they were forced along by a fire which it was impossible to withstand. Ensign Monaghan did stand. He stood steadfast by his wounded superior and friend - one rifle against many, one brave man against a score .... He knew he was doomed. He could not yield. He died in heroic performance of duty.''\"\n\n==Notes==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==References==\n*{{cite book|last=Mains|first=P. John|authorlink=|author2=McCarty, Louis Philippe |edition=|title= The Statistician and Economist: Volume 23|year=1906|publisher=|location=|isbn=}}\n\n{{coord missing|Samoa}}\n{{Authority control}}\n[[Category:Battles of the Second Samoan Civil War|Vailele]]\n[[Category:1899 in Samoa]]\n[[Category:April 1899 events]]\n[[Category:Tuamasaga]]\n[[Category:Battles of the Second Samoan Civil War involving the United States|Vailele, Second]]\n[[Category:Battles of the Second Samoan Civil War involving the United Kingdom|Vailele]]\n[[Category:Punitive expeditions of the United States|Vailele]]\n[[Category:Punitive expeditions of the United Kingdom|Vailele]]\n", "name_user": "Mr. Guye", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200etop", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Second_Battle_of_Vailele"}
